36/// Check whether T is compatible with a wide character type (wchar_t,
37/// char16_t or char32_t).
38static bool IsWideCharCompatible(QualType T, ASTContext &Context) {
39 if (Context.typesAreCompatible(Context.getWideCharType(), T))
40 return true;
41 if (Context.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus || Context.getLangOpts().C11) {
42 return Context.typesAreCompatible(Context.Char16Ty, T) ||
43 Context.typesAreCompatible(Context.Char32Ty, T);
44 }
45 return false;
46}
47
48enum StringInitFailureKind {
49 SIF_None,
50 SIF_NarrowStringIntoWideChar,
51 SIF_WideStringIntoChar,
52 SIF_IncompatWideStringIntoWideChar,
53 SIF_UTF8StringIntoPlainChar,
54 SIF_PlainStringIntoUTF8Char,
55 SIF_Other
56};
57
58/// Check whether the array of type AT can be initialized by the Init
59/// expression by means of string initialization. Returns SIF_None if so,
60/// otherwise returns a StringInitFailureKind that describes why the
61/// initialization would not work.
62static StringInitFailureKind IsStringInit(Expr *Init, const ArrayType *AT,
63 ASTContext &Context) {
64 if (!isa<ConstantArrayType>(AT) && !isa<IncompleteArrayType>(AT))
65 return SIF_Other;
66
67 // See if this is a string literal or @encode.
68 Init = Init->IgnoreParens();
69
70 // Handle @encode, which is a narrow string.
71 if (isa<ObjCEncodeExpr>(Init) && AT->getElementType()->isCharType())
72 return SIF_None;
73
74 // Otherwise we can only handle string literals.
75 StringLiteral *SL = dyn_cast<StringLiteral>(Init);
76 if (!SL)
77 return SIF_Other;
78
79 const QualType ElemTy =
80 Context.getCanonicalType(AT->getElementType()).getUnqualifiedType();
81
82 switch (SL->getKind()) {
83 case StringLiteral::UTF8:
84 // char8_t array can be initialized with a UTF-8 string.
85 if (ElemTy->isChar8Type())
86 return SIF_None;
87 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
88 case StringLiteral::Ascii:
89 // char array can be initialized with a narrow string.
90 // Only allow char x[] = "foo"; not char x[] = L"foo";
91 if (ElemTy->isCharType())
92 return (SL->getKind() == StringLiteral::UTF8 &&
93 Context.getLangOpts().Char8)
94 ? SIF_UTF8StringIntoPlainChar
95 : SIF_None;
96 if (ElemTy->isChar8Type())
97 return SIF_PlainStringIntoUTF8Char;
98 if (IsWideCharCompatible(ElemTy, Context))
99 return SIF_NarrowStringIntoWideChar;
100 return SIF_Other;
101 // C99 6.7.8p15 (with correction from DR343), or C11 6.7.9p15:
102 // "An array with element type compatible with a qualified or unqualified
103 // version of wchar_t, char16_t, or char32_t may be initialized by a wide
104 // string literal with the corresponding encoding prefix (L, u, or U,
105 // respectively), optionally enclosed in braces.
106 case StringLiteral::UTF16:
107 if (Context.typesAreCompatible(Context.Char16Ty, ElemTy))
108 return SIF_None;
109 if (ElemTy->isCharType() || ElemTy->isChar8Type())
110 return SIF_WideStringIntoChar;
111 if (IsWideCharCompatible(ElemTy, Context))
112 return SIF_IncompatWideStringIntoWideChar;
113 return SIF_Other;
114 case StringLiteral::UTF32:
115 if (Context.typesAreCompatible(Context.Char32Ty, ElemTy))
116 return SIF_None;
117 if (ElemTy->isCharType() || ElemTy->isChar8Type())
118 return SIF_WideStringIntoChar;
119 if (IsWideCharCompatible(ElemTy, Context))
120 return SIF_IncompatWideStringIntoWideChar;
121 return SIF_Other;
122 case StringLiteral::Wide:
123 if (Context.typesAreCompatible(Context.getWideCharType(), ElemTy))
124 return SIF_None;
125 if (ElemTy->isCharType() || ElemTy->isChar8Type())
126 return SIF_WideStringIntoChar;
127 if (IsWideCharCompatible(ElemTy, Context))
128 return SIF_IncompatWideStringIntoWideChar;
129 return SIF_Other;
130 }
131
132 llvm_unreachable("missed a StringLiteral kind?");
133}
134
135static StringInitFailureKind IsStringInit(Expr *init, QualType declType,
136 ASTContext &Context) {
137 const ArrayType *arrayType = Context.getAsArrayType(declType);
138 if (!arrayType)
139 return SIF_Other;
140 return IsStringInit(init, arrayType, Context);
141}
142
143/// Update the type of a string literal, including any surrounding parentheses,
144/// to match the type of the object which it is initializing.
145static void updateStringLiteralType(Expr *E, QualType Ty) {
146 while (true) {
147 E->setType(Ty);
148 E->setValueKind(VK_RValue);
149 if (isa<StringLiteral>(E) || isa<ObjCEncodeExpr>(E)) {
150 break;
151 } else if (ParenExpr *PE = dyn_cast<ParenExpr>(E)) {
152 E = PE->getSubExpr();
153 } else if (UnaryOperator *UO = dyn_cast<UnaryOperator>(E)) {
154 assert(UO->getOpcode() == UO_Extension);
155 E = UO->getSubExpr();
156 } else if (GenericSelectionExpr *GSE = dyn_cast<GenericSelectionExpr>(E)) {
157 E = GSE->getResultExpr();
158 } else if (ChooseExpr *CE = dyn_cast<ChooseExpr>(E)) {
159 E = CE->getChosenSubExpr();
160 } else {
161 llvm_unreachable("unexpected expr in string literal init");
162 }
163 }
164}
165
166/// Fix a compound literal initializing an array so it's correctly marked
167/// as an rvalue.
168static void updateGNUCompoundLiteralRValue(Expr *E) {
169 while (true) {
170 E->setValueKind(VK_RValue);
171 if (isa<CompoundLiteralExpr>(E)) {
172 break;
173 } else if (ParenExpr *PE = dyn_cast<ParenExpr>(E)) {
174 E = PE->getSubExpr();
175 } else if (UnaryOperator *UO = dyn_cast<UnaryOperator>(E)) {
176 assert(UO->getOpcode() == UO_Extension);
177 E = UO->getSubExpr();
178 } else if (GenericSelectionExpr *GSE = dyn_cast<GenericSelectionExpr>(E)) {
179 E = GSE->getResultExpr();
180 } else if (ChooseExpr *CE = dyn_cast<ChooseExpr>(E)) {
181 E = CE->getChosenSubExpr();
182 } else {
183 llvm_unreachable("unexpected expr in array compound literal init");
184 }
185 }
186}
187
188static void CheckStringInit(Expr *Str, QualType &DeclT, const ArrayType *AT,
189 Sema &S) {
190 // Get the length of the string as parsed.
191 auto *ConstantArrayTy =
192 cast<ConstantArrayType>(Str->getType()->getAsArrayTypeUnsafe());
193 uint64_t StrLength = ConstantArrayTy->getSize().getZExtValue();
194
195 if (const IncompleteArrayType *IAT = dyn_cast<IncompleteArrayType>(AT)) {
196 // C99 6.7.8p14. We have an array of character type with unknown size
197 // being initialized to a string literal.
198 llvm::APInt ConstVal(32, StrLength);
199 // Return a new array type (C99 6.7.8p22).
200 DeclT = S.Context.getConstantArrayType(IAT->getElementType(),
201 ConstVal,
202 ArrayType::Normal, 0);
203 updateStringLiteralType(Str, DeclT);
204 return;
205 }
206
207 const ConstantArrayType *CAT = cast<ConstantArrayType>(AT);
208
209 // We have an array of character type with known size. However,
210 // the size may be smaller or larger than the string we are initializing.
211 // FIXME: Avoid truncation for 64-bit length strings.
212 if (S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
213 if (StringLiteral *SL = dyn_cast<StringLiteral>(Str->IgnoreParens())) {
214 // For Pascal strings it's OK to strip off the terminating null character,
215 // so the example below is valid:
216 //
217 // unsigned char a[2] = "\pa";
218 if (SL->isPascal())
219 StrLength--;
220 }
221
222 // [dcl.init.string]p2
223 if (StrLength > CAT->getSize().getZExtValue())
224 S.Diag(Str->getBeginLoc(),
225 diag::err_initializer_string_for_char_array_too_long)
226 << Str->getSourceRange();
227 } else {
228 // C99 6.7.8p14.
229 if (StrLength-1 > CAT->getSize().getZExtValue())
230 S.Diag(Str->getBeginLoc(),
231 diag::ext_initializer_string_for_char_array_too_long)
232 << Str->getSourceRange();
233 }
234
235 // Set the type to the actual size that we are initializing. If we have
236 // something like:
237 // char x[1] = "foo";
238 // then this will set the string literal's type to char[1].
239 updateStringLiteralType(Str, DeclT);
240}

246namespace {
247
248/// Semantic checking for initializer lists.
249///
250/// The InitListChecker class contains a set of routines that each
251/// handle the initialization of a certain kind of entity, e.g.,
252/// arrays, vectors, struct/union types, scalars, etc. The
253/// InitListChecker itself performs a recursive walk of the subobject
254/// structure of the type to be initialized, while stepping through
255/// the initializer list one element at a time. The IList and Index
256/// parameters to each of the Check* routines contain the active
257/// (syntactic) initializer list and the index into that initializer
258/// list that represents the current initializer. Each routine is
259/// responsible for moving that Index forward as it consumes elements.
260///
261/// Each Check* routine also has a StructuredList/StructuredIndex
262/// arguments, which contains the current "structured" (semantic)
263/// initializer list and the index into that initializer list where we
264/// are copying initializers as we map them over to the semantic
265/// list. Once we have completed our recursive walk of the subobject
266/// structure, we will have constructed a full semantic initializer
267/// list.
268///
269/// C99 designators cause changes in the initializer list traversal,
270/// because they make the initialization "jump" into a specific
271/// subobject and then continue the initialization from that
272/// point. CheckDesignatedInitializer() recursively steps into the
273/// designated subobject and manages backing out the recursion to
274/// initialize the subobjects after the one designated.
275class InitListChecker {
276 Sema &SemaRef;
277 bool hadError;
278 bool VerifyOnly; // no diagnostics, no structure building
279 bool TreatUnavailableAsInvalid; // Used only in VerifyOnly mode.
280 llvm::DenseMap<InitListExpr *, InitListExpr *> SyntacticToSemantic;
281 InitListExpr *FullyStructuredList;
282
283 void CheckImplicitInitList(const InitializedEntity &Entity,
284 InitListExpr *ParentIList, QualType T,
285 unsigned &Index, InitListExpr *StructuredList,
286 unsigned &StructuredIndex);
287 void CheckExplicitInitList(const InitializedEntity &Entity,
288 InitListExpr *IList, QualType &T,
289 InitListExpr *StructuredList,
290 bool TopLevelObject = false);
291 void CheckListElementTypes(const InitializedEntity &Entity,
292 InitListExpr *IList, QualType &DeclType,
293 bool SubobjectIsDesignatorContext,
294 unsigned &Index,
295 InitListExpr *StructuredList,
296 unsigned &StructuredIndex,
297 bool TopLevelObject = false);
298 void CheckSubElementType(const InitializedEntity &Entity,
299 InitListExpr *IList, QualType ElemType,
300 unsigned &Index,
301 InitListExpr *StructuredList,
302 unsigned &StructuredIndex);
303 void CheckComplexType(const InitializedEntity &Entity,
304 InitListExpr *IList, QualType DeclType,
305 unsigned &Index,
306 InitListExpr *StructuredList,
307 unsigned &StructuredIndex);
308 void CheckScalarType(const InitializedEntity &Entity,
309 InitListExpr *IList, QualType DeclType,
310 unsigned &Index,
311 InitListExpr *StructuredList,
312 unsigned &StructuredIndex);
313 void CheckReferenceType(const InitializedEntity &Entity,
314 InitListExpr *IList, QualType DeclType,
315 unsigned &Index,
316 InitListExpr *StructuredList,
317 unsigned &StructuredIndex);
318 void CheckVectorType(const InitializedEntity &Entity,
319 InitListExpr *IList, QualType DeclType, unsigned &Index,
320 InitListExpr *StructuredList,
321 unsigned &StructuredIndex);
322 void CheckStructUnionTypes(const InitializedEntity &Entity,
323 InitListExpr *IList, QualType DeclType,
324 CXXRecordDecl::base_class_range Bases,
325 RecordDecl::field_iterator Field,
326 bool SubobjectIsDesignatorContext, unsigned &Index,
327 InitListExpr *StructuredList,
328 unsigned &StructuredIndex,
329 bool TopLevelObject = false);
330 void CheckArrayType(const InitializedEntity &Entity,
331 InitListExpr *IList, QualType &DeclType,
332 llvm::APSInt elementIndex,
333 bool SubobjectIsDesignatorContext, unsigned &Index,
334 InitListExpr *StructuredList,
335 unsigned &StructuredIndex);
336 bool CheckDesignatedInitializer(const InitializedEntity &Entity,
337 InitListExpr *IList, DesignatedInitExpr *DIE,
338 unsigned DesigIdx,
339 QualType &CurrentObjectType,
340 RecordDecl::field_iterator *NextField,
341 llvm::APSInt *NextElementIndex,
342 unsigned &Index,
343 InitListExpr *StructuredList,
344 unsigned &StructuredIndex,
345 bool FinishSubobjectInit,
346 bool TopLevelObject);
347 InitListExpr *getStructuredSubobjectInit(InitListExpr *IList, unsigned Index,
348 QualType CurrentObjectType,
349 InitListExpr *StructuredList,
350 unsigned StructuredIndex,
351 SourceRange InitRange,
352 bool IsFullyOverwritten = false);
353 void UpdateStructuredListElement(InitListExpr *StructuredList,
354 unsigned &StructuredIndex,
355 Expr *expr);
356 int numArrayElements(QualType DeclType);
357 int numStructUnionElements(QualType DeclType);
358
359 static ExprResult PerformEmptyInit(Sema &SemaRef,
360 SourceLocation Loc,
361 const InitializedEntity &Entity,
362 bool VerifyOnly,
363 bool TreatUnavailableAsInvalid);
364
365 // Explanation on the "FillWithNoInit" mode:
366 //
367 // Assume we have the following definitions (Case#1):
368 // struct P { char x[6][6]; } xp = { .x[1] = "bar" };
369 // struct PP { struct P lp; } l = { .lp = xp, .lp.x[1][2] = 'f' };
370 //
371 // l.lp.x[1][0..1] should not be filled with implicit initializers because the
372 // "base" initializer "xp" will provide values for them; l.lp.x[1] will be "baf".
373 //
374 // But if we have (Case#2):
375 // struct PP l = { .lp = xp, .lp.x[1] = { [2] = 'f' } };
376 //
377 // l.lp.x[1][0..1] are implicitly initialized and do not use values from the
378 // "base" initializer; l.lp.x[1] will be "\0\0f\0\0\0".
379 //
380 // To distinguish Case#1 from Case#2, and also to avoid leaving many "holes"
381 // in the InitListExpr, the "holes" in Case#1 are filled not with empty
382 // initializers but with special "NoInitExpr" place holders, which tells the
383 // CodeGen not to generate any initializers for these parts.
384 void FillInEmptyInitForBase(unsigned Init, const CXXBaseSpecifier &Base,
385 const InitializedEntity &ParentEntity,
386 InitListExpr *ILE, bool &RequiresSecondPass,
387 bool FillWithNoInit);
388 void FillInEmptyInitForField(unsigned Init, FieldDecl *Field,
389 const InitializedEntity &ParentEntity,
390 InitListExpr *ILE, bool &RequiresSecondPass,
391 bool FillWithNoInit = false);
392 void FillInEmptyInitializations(const InitializedEntity &Entity,
393 InitListExpr *ILE, bool &RequiresSecondPass,
394 InitListExpr *OuterILE, unsigned OuterIndex,
395 bool FillWithNoInit = false);
396 bool CheckFlexibleArrayInit(const InitializedEntity &Entity,
397 Expr *InitExpr, FieldDecl *Field,
398 bool TopLevelObject);
399 void CheckEmptyInitializable(const InitializedEntity &Entity,
400 SourceLocation Loc);
401
402 bool isCapNarrowing(Expr* expr, QualType DeclType, unsigned *Index,
403 unsigned *StructuredIndex);
404
405public:
406 InitListChecker(Sema &S, const InitializedEntity &Entity,
407 InitListExpr *IL, QualType &T, bool VerifyOnly,
408 bool TreatUnavailableAsInvalid);
409 bool HadError() { return hadError; }
410
411 // Retrieves the fully-structured initializer list used for
412 // semantic analysis and code generation.
413 InitListExpr *getFullyStructuredList() const { return FullyStructuredList; }
414};
415
416} // end anonymous namespace
417
418ExprResult InitListChecker::PerformEmptyInit(Sema &SemaRef,
419 SourceLocation Loc,
420 const InitializedEntity &Entity,
421 bool VerifyOnly,
422 bool TreatUnavailableAsInvalid) {
423 InitializationKind Kind = InitializationKind::CreateValue(Loc, Loc, Loc,
424 true);
425 MultiExprArg SubInit;
426 Expr *InitExpr;
427 InitListExpr DummyInitList(SemaRef.Context, Loc, None, Loc);
428
429 // C++ [dcl.init.aggr]p7:
430 // If there are fewer initializer-clauses in the list than there are
431 // members in the aggregate, then each member not explicitly initialized
432 // ...
433 bool EmptyInitList = SemaRef.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11 &&
434 Entity.getType()->getBaseElementTypeUnsafe()->isRecordType();
435 if (EmptyInitList) {
436 // C++1y / DR1070:
437 // shall be initialized [...] from an empty initializer list.
438 //
439 // We apply the resolution of this DR to C++11 but not C++98, since C++98
440 // does not have useful semantics for initialization from an init list.
441 // We treat this as copy-initialization, because aggregate initialization
442 // always performs copy-initialization on its elements.
443 //
444 // Only do this if we're initializing a class type, to avoid filling in
445 // the initializer list where possible.
446 InitExpr = VerifyOnly ? &DummyInitList : new (SemaRef.Context)
447 InitListExpr(SemaRef.Context, Loc, None, Loc);
448 InitExpr->setType(SemaRef.Context.VoidTy);
449 SubInit = InitExpr;
450 Kind = InitializationKind::CreateCopy(Loc, Loc);
451 } else {
452 // C++03:
453 // shall be value-initialized.
454 }
455
456 InitializationSequence InitSeq(SemaRef, Entity, Kind, SubInit);
457 // libstdc++4.6 marks the vector default constructor as explicit in
458 // _GLIBCXX_DEBUG mode, so recover using the C++03 logic in that case.
459 // stlport does so too. Look for std::__debug for libstdc++, and for
460 // std:: for stlport. This is effectively a compiler-side implementation of
461 // LWG2193.
462 if (!InitSeq && EmptyInitList && InitSeq.getFailureKind() ==
463 InitializationSequence::FK_ExplicitConstructor) {
464 OverloadCandidateSet::iterator Best;
465 OverloadingResult O =
466 InitSeq.getFailedCandidateSet()
467 .BestViableFunction(SemaRef, Kind.getLocation(), Best);
468 (void)O;
469 assert(O == OR_Success && "Inconsistent overload resolution");
470 CXXConstructorDecl *CtorDecl = cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(Best->Function);
471 CXXRecordDecl *R = CtorDecl->getParent();
472
473 if (CtorDecl->getMinRequiredArguments() == 0 &&
474 CtorDecl->isExplicit() && R->getDeclName() &&
475 SemaRef.SourceMgr.isInSystemHeader(CtorDecl->getLocation())) {
476 bool IsInStd = false;
477 for (NamespaceDecl *ND = dyn_cast<NamespaceDecl>(R->getDeclContext());
478 ND && !IsInStd; ND = dyn_cast<NamespaceDecl>(ND->getParent())) {
479 if (SemaRef.getStdNamespace()->InEnclosingNamespaceSetOf(ND))
480 IsInStd = true;
481 }
482
483 if (IsInStd && llvm::StringSwitch<bool>(R->getName())
484 .Cases("basic_string", "deque", "forward_list", true)
485 .Cases("list", "map", "multimap", "multiset", true)
486 .Cases("priority_queue", "queue", "set", "stack", true)
487 .Cases("unordered_map", "unordered_set", "vector", true)
488 .Default(false)) {
489 InitSeq.InitializeFrom(
490 SemaRef, Entity,
491 InitializationKind::CreateValue(Loc, Loc, Loc, true),
492 MultiExprArg(), /*TopLevelOfInitList=*/false,
493 TreatUnavailableAsInvalid);
494 // Emit a warning for this. System header warnings aren't shown
495 // by default, but people working on system headers should see it.
496 if (!VerifyOnly) {
497 SemaRef.Diag(CtorDecl->getLocation(),
498 diag::warn_invalid_initializer_from_system_header);
499 if (Entity.getKind() == InitializedEntity::EK_Member)
500 SemaRef.Diag(Entity.getDecl()->getLocation(),
501 diag::note_used_in_initialization_here);
502 else if (Entity.getKind() == InitializedEntity::EK_ArrayElement)
503 SemaRef.Diag(Loc, diag::note_used_in_initialization_here);
504 }
505 }
506 }
507 }
508 if (!InitSeq) {
509 if (!VerifyOnly) {
510 InitSeq.Diagnose(SemaRef, Entity, Kind, SubInit);
511 if (Entity.getKind() == InitializedEntity::EK_Member)
512 SemaRef.Diag(Entity.getDecl()->getLocation(),
513 diag::note_in_omitted_aggregate_initializer)
514 << /*field*/1 << Entity.getDecl();
515 else if (Entity.getKind() == InitializedEntity::EK_ArrayElement) {
516 bool IsTrailingArrayNewMember =
517 Entity.getParent() &&
518 Entity.getParent()->isVariableLengthArrayNew();
519 SemaRef.Diag(Loc, diag::note_in_omitted_aggregate_initializer)
520 << (IsTrailingArrayNewMember ? 2 : /*array element*/0)
521 << Entity.getElementIndex();
522 }
523 }
524 return ExprError();
525 }
526
527 return VerifyOnly ? ExprResult(static_cast<Expr *>(nullptr))
528 : InitSeq.Perform(SemaRef, Entity, Kind, SubInit);
529}
530
531void InitListChecker::CheckEmptyInitializable(const InitializedEntity &Entity,
532 SourceLocation Loc) {
533 assert(VerifyOnly &&
534 "CheckEmptyInitializable is only inteded for verification mode.");
535 if (PerformEmptyInit(SemaRef, Loc, Entity, /*VerifyOnly*/true,
536 TreatUnavailableAsInvalid).isInvalid())
537 hadError = true;
538}
539
540void InitListChecker::FillInEmptyInitForBase(
541 unsigned Init, const CXXBaseSpecifier &Base,
542 const InitializedEntity &ParentEntity, InitListExpr *ILE,
543 bool &RequiresSecondPass, bool FillWithNoInit) {
544 assert(Init < ILE->getNumInits() && "should have been expanded");
545
546 InitializedEntity BaseEntity = InitializedEntity::InitializeBase(
547 SemaRef.Context, &Base, false, &ParentEntity);
548
549 if (!ILE->getInit(Init)) {
550 ExprResult BaseInit =
551 FillWithNoInit
552 ? new (SemaRef.Context) NoInitExpr(Base.getType())
553 : PerformEmptyInit(SemaRef, ILE->getEndLoc(), BaseEntity,
554 /*VerifyOnly*/ false, TreatUnavailableAsInvalid);
555 if (BaseInit.isInvalid()) {
556 hadError = true;
557 return;
558 }
559
560 ILE->setInit(Init, BaseInit.getAs<Expr>());
561 } else if (InitListExpr *InnerILE =
562 dyn_cast<InitListExpr>(ILE->getInit(Init))) {
563 FillInEmptyInitializations(BaseEntity, InnerILE, RequiresSecondPass,
564 ILE, Init, FillWithNoInit);
565 } else if (DesignatedInitUpdateExpr *InnerDIUE =
566 dyn_cast<DesignatedInitUpdateExpr>(ILE->getInit(Init))) {
567 FillInEmptyInitializations(BaseEntity, InnerDIUE->getUpdater(),
568 RequiresSecondPass, ILE, Init,
569 /*FillWithNoInit =*/true);
570 }
571}
572
573void InitListChecker::FillInEmptyInitForField(unsigned Init, FieldDecl *Field,
574 const InitializedEntity &ParentEntity,
575 InitListExpr *ILE,
576 bool &RequiresSecondPass,
577 bool FillWithNoInit) {
578 SourceLocation Loc = ILE->getEndLoc();
579 unsigned NumInits = ILE->getNumInits();
580 InitializedEntity MemberEntity
581 = InitializedEntity::InitializeMember(Field, &ParentEntity);
582
583 if (const RecordType *RType = ILE->getType()->getAs<RecordType>())
584 if (!RType->getDecl()->isUnion())
585 assert(Init < NumInits && "This ILE should have been expanded");
586
587 if (Init >= NumInits || !ILE->getInit(Init)) {
588 if (FillWithNoInit) {
589 Expr *Filler = new (SemaRef.Context) NoInitExpr(Field->getType());
590 if (Init < NumInits)
591 ILE->setInit(Init, Filler);
592 else
593 ILE->updateInit(SemaRef.Context, Init, Filler);
594 return;
595 }
596 // C++1y [dcl.init.aggr]p7:
597 // If there are fewer initializer-clauses in the list than there are
598 // members in the aggregate, then each member not explicitly initialized
599 // shall be initialized from its brace-or-equal-initializer [...]
600 if (Field->hasInClassInitializer()) {
601 ExprResult DIE = SemaRef.BuildCXXDefaultInitExpr(Loc, Field);
602 if (DIE.isInvalid()) {
603 hadError = true;
604 return;
605 }
606 SemaRef.checkInitializerLifetime(MemberEntity, DIE.get());
607 if (Init < NumInits)
608 ILE->setInit(Init, DIE.get());
609 else {
610 ILE->updateInit(SemaRef.Context, Init, DIE.get());
611 RequiresSecondPass = true;
612 }
613 return;
614 }
615
616 if (Field->getType()->isReferenceType()) {
617 // C++ [dcl.init.aggr]p9:
618 // If an incomplete or empty initializer-list leaves a
619 // member of reference type uninitialized, the program is
620 // ill-formed.
621 SemaRef.Diag(Loc, diag::err_init_reference_member_uninitialized)
622 << Field->getType()
623 << ILE->getSyntacticForm()->getSourceRange();
624 SemaRef.Diag(Field->getLocation(),
625 diag::note_uninit_reference_member);
626 hadError = true;
627 return;
628 }
629
630 ExprResult MemberInit = PerformEmptyInit(SemaRef, Loc, MemberEntity,
631 /*VerifyOnly*/false,
632 TreatUnavailableAsInvalid);
633 if (MemberInit.isInvalid()) {
634 hadError = true;
635 return;
636 }
637
638 if (hadError) {
639 // Do nothing
640 } else if (Init < NumInits) {
641 ILE->setInit(Init, MemberInit.getAs<Expr>());
642 } else if (!isa<ImplicitValueInitExpr>(MemberInit.get())) {
643 // Empty initialization requires a constructor call, so
644 // extend the initializer list to include the constructor
645 // call and make a note that we'll need to take another pass
646 // through the initializer list.
647 ILE->updateInit(SemaRef.Context, Init, MemberInit.getAs<Expr>());
648 RequiresSecondPass = true;
649 }
650 } else if (InitListExpr *InnerILE
651 = dyn_cast<InitListExpr>(ILE->getInit(Init)))
652 FillInEmptyInitializations(MemberEntity, InnerILE,
653 RequiresSecondPass, ILE, Init, FillWithNoInit);
654 else if (DesignatedInitUpdateExpr *InnerDIUE
655 = dyn_cast<DesignatedInitUpdateExpr>(ILE->getInit(Init)))
656 FillInEmptyInitializations(MemberEntity, InnerDIUE->getUpdater(),
657 RequiresSecondPass, ILE, Init,
658 /*FillWithNoInit =*/true);
659}
660
661/// Recursively replaces NULL values within the given initializer list
662/// with expressions that perform value-initialization of the
663/// appropriate type, and finish off the InitListExpr formation.
664void
665InitListChecker::FillInEmptyInitializations(const InitializedEntity &Entity,
666 InitListExpr *ILE,
667 bool &RequiresSecondPass,
668 InitListExpr *OuterILE,
669 unsigned OuterIndex,
670 bool FillWithNoInit) {
671 assert((ILE->getType() != SemaRef.Context.VoidTy) &&
672 "Should not have void type");
673
674 // If this is a nested initializer list, we might have changed its contents
675 // (and therefore some of its properties, such as instantiation-dependence)
676 // while filling it in. Inform the outer initializer list so that its state
677 // can be updated to match.
678 // FIXME: We should fully build the inner initializers before constructing
679 // the outer InitListExpr instead of mutating AST nodes after they have
680 // been used as subexpressions of other nodes.
681 struct UpdateOuterILEWithUpdatedInit {
682 InitListExpr *Outer;
683 unsigned OuterIndex;
684 ~UpdateOuterILEWithUpdatedInit() {
685 if (Outer)
686 Outer->setInit(OuterIndex, Outer->getInit(OuterIndex));
687 }
688 } UpdateOuterRAII = {OuterILE, OuterIndex};
689
690 // A transparent ILE is not performing aggregate initialization and should
691 // not be filled in.
692 if (ILE->isTransparent())
693 return;
694
695 if (const RecordType *RType = ILE->getType()->getAs<RecordType>()) {
696 const RecordDecl *RDecl = RType->getDecl();
697 if (RDecl->isUnion() && ILE->getInitializedFieldInUnion())
698 FillInEmptyInitForField(0, ILE->getInitializedFieldInUnion(),
699 Entity, ILE, RequiresSecondPass, FillWithNoInit);
700 else if (RDecl->isUnion() && isa<CXXRecordDecl>(RDecl) &&
701 cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RDecl)->hasInClassInitializer()) {
702 for (auto *Field : RDecl->fields()) {
703 if (Field->hasInClassInitializer()) {
704 FillInEmptyInitForField(0, Field, Entity, ILE, RequiresSecondPass,
705 FillWithNoInit);
706 break;
707 }
708 }
709 } else {
710 // The fields beyond ILE->getNumInits() are default initialized, so in
711 // order to leave them uninitialized, the ILE is expanded and the extra
712 // fields are then filled with NoInitExpr.
713 unsigned NumElems = numStructUnionElements(ILE->getType());
714 if (RDecl->hasFlexibleArrayMember())
715 ++NumElems;
716 if (ILE->getNumInits() < NumElems)
717 ILE->resizeInits(SemaRef.Context, NumElems);
718
719 unsigned Init = 0;
720
721 if (auto *CXXRD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RDecl)) {
722 for (auto &Base : CXXRD->bases()) {
723 if (hadError)
724 return;
725
726 FillInEmptyInitForBase(Init, Base, Entity, ILE, RequiresSecondPass,
727 FillWithNoInit);
728 ++Init;
729 }
730 }
731
732 for (auto *Field : RDecl->fields()) {
733 if (Field->isUnnamedBitfield())
734 continue;
735
736 if (hadError)
737 return;
738
739 FillInEmptyInitForField(Init, Field, Entity, ILE, RequiresSecondPass,
740 FillWithNoInit);
741 if (hadError)
742 return;
743
744 ++Init;
745
746 // Only look at the first initialization of a union.
747 if (RDecl->isUnion())
748 break;
749 }
750 }
751
752 return;
753 }
754
755 QualType ElementType;
756
757 InitializedEntity ElementEntity = Entity;
758 unsigned NumInits = ILE->getNumInits();
759 unsigned NumElements = NumInits;
760 if (const ArrayType *AType = SemaRef.Context.getAsArrayType(ILE->getType())) {
761 ElementType = AType->getElementType();
762 if (const auto *CAType = dyn_cast<ConstantArrayType>(AType))
763 NumElements = CAType->getSize().getZExtValue();
764 // For an array new with an unknown bound, ask for one additional element
765 // in order to populate the array filler.
766 if (Entity.isVariableLengthArrayNew())
767 ++NumElements;
768 ElementEntity = InitializedEntity::InitializeElement(SemaRef.Context,
769 0, Entity);
770 } else if (const VectorType *VType = ILE->getType()->getAs<VectorType>()) {
771 ElementType = VType->getElementType();
772 NumElements = VType->getNumElements();
773 ElementEntity = InitializedEntity::InitializeElement(SemaRef.Context,
774 0, Entity);
775 } else
776 ElementType = ILE->getType();
777
778 for (unsigned Init = 0; Init != NumElements; ++Init) {
779 if (hadError)
780 return;
781
782 if (ElementEntity.getKind() == InitializedEntity::EK_ArrayElement ||
783 ElementEntity.getKind() == InitializedEntity::EK_VectorElement)
784 ElementEntity.setElementIndex(Init);
785
786 if (Init >= NumInits && ILE->hasArrayFiller())
787 return;
788
789 Expr *InitExpr = (Init < NumInits ? ILE->getInit(Init) : nullptr);
790 if (!InitExpr && Init < NumInits && ILE->hasArrayFiller())
791 ILE->setInit(Init, ILE->getArrayFiller());
792 else if (!InitExpr && !ILE->hasArrayFiller()) {
793 Expr *Filler = nullptr;
794
795 if (FillWithNoInit)
796 Filler = new (SemaRef.Context) NoInitExpr(ElementType);
797 else {
798 ExprResult ElementInit =
799 PerformEmptyInit(SemaRef, ILE->getEndLoc(), ElementEntity,
800 /*VerifyOnly*/ false, TreatUnavailableAsInvalid);
801 if (ElementInit.isInvalid()) {
802 hadError = true;
803 return;
804 }
805
806 Filler = ElementInit.getAs<Expr>();
807 }
808
809 if (hadError) {
810 // Do nothing
811 } else if (Init < NumInits) {
812 // For arrays, just set the expression used for value-initialization
813 // of the "holes" in the array.
814 if (ElementEntity.getKind() == InitializedEntity::EK_ArrayElement)
815 ILE->setArrayFiller(Filler);
816 else
817 ILE->setInit(Init, Filler);
818 } else {
819 // For arrays, just set the expression used for value-initialization
820 // of the rest of elements and exit.
821 if (ElementEntity.getKind() == InitializedEntity::EK_ArrayElement) {
822 ILE->setArrayFiller(Filler);
823 return;
824 }
825
826 if (!isa<ImplicitValueInitExpr>(Filler) && !isa<NoInitExpr>(Filler)) {
827 // Empty initialization requires a constructor call, so
828 // extend the initializer list to include the constructor
829 // call and make a note that we'll need to take another pass
830 // through the initializer list.
831 ILE->updateInit(SemaRef.Context, Init, Filler);
832 RequiresSecondPass = true;
833 }
834 }
835 } else if (InitListExpr *InnerILE
836 = dyn_cast_or_null<InitListExpr>(InitExpr))
837 FillInEmptyInitializations(ElementEntity, InnerILE, RequiresSecondPass,
838 ILE, Init, FillWithNoInit);
839 else if (DesignatedInitUpdateExpr *InnerDIUE
840 = dyn_cast_or_null<DesignatedInitUpdateExpr>(InitExpr))
841 FillInEmptyInitializations(ElementEntity, InnerDIUE->getUpdater(),
842 RequiresSecondPass, ILE, Init,
843 /*FillWithNoInit =*/true);
844 }
845}
846
847InitListChecker::InitListChecker(Sema &S, const InitializedEntity &Entity,
848 InitListExpr *IL, QualType &T,
849 bool VerifyOnly,
850 bool TreatUnavailableAsInvalid)
851 : SemaRef(S), VerifyOnly(VerifyOnly),
852 TreatUnavailableAsInvalid(TreatUnavailableAsInvalid) {
853 // FIXME: Check that IL isn't already the semantic form of some other
854 // InitListExpr. If it is, we'd create a broken AST.
855
856 hadError = false;
857
858 FullyStructuredList =
859 getStructuredSubobjectInit(IL, 0, T, nullptr, 0, IL->getSourceRange());
860 CheckExplicitInitList(Entity, IL, T, FullyStructuredList,
861 /*TopLevelObject=*/true);
862
863 if (!hadError && !VerifyOnly) {
864 bool RequiresSecondPass = false;
865 FillInEmptyInitializations(Entity, FullyStructuredList, RequiresSecondPass,
866 /*OuterILE=*/nullptr, /*OuterIndex=*/0);
867 if (RequiresSecondPass && !hadError)
868 FillInEmptyInitializations(Entity, FullyStructuredList,
869 RequiresSecondPass, nullptr, 0);
870 }
871}
872
873int InitListChecker::numArrayElements(QualType DeclType) {
874 // FIXME: use a proper constant
875 int maxElements = 0x7FFFFFFF;
876 if (const ConstantArrayType *CAT =
877 SemaRef.Context.getAsConstantArrayType(DeclType)) {
878 maxElements = static_cast<int>(CAT->getSize().getZExtValue());
879 }
880 return maxElements;
881}
882
883int InitListChecker::numStructUnionElements(QualType DeclType) {
884 RecordDecl *structDecl = DeclType->getAs<RecordType>()->getDecl();
885 int InitializableMembers = 0;
886 if (auto *CXXRD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(structDecl))
887 InitializableMembers += CXXRD->getNumBases();
888 for (const auto *Field : structDecl->fields())
889 if (!Field->isUnnamedBitfield())
890 ++InitializableMembers;
891
892 if (structDecl->isUnion())
893 return std::min(InitializableMembers, 1);
894 return InitializableMembers - structDecl->hasFlexibleArrayMember();
895}
896
897/// Determine whether Entity is an entity for which it is idiomatic to elide
898/// the braces in aggregate initialization.
899static bool isIdiomaticBraceElisionEntity(const InitializedEntity &Entity) {
900 // Recursive initialization of the one and only field within an aggregate
901 // class is considered idiomatic. This case arises in particular for
902 // initialization of std::array, where the C++ standard suggests the idiom of
903 //
904 // std::array<T, N> arr = {1, 2, 3};
905 //
906 // (where std::array is an aggregate struct containing a single array field.
907
908 // FIXME: Should aggregate initialization of a struct with a single
909 // base class and no members also suppress the warning?
910 if (Entity.getKind() != InitializedEntity::EK_Member || !Entity.getParent())
911 return false;
912
913 auto *ParentRD =
914 Entity.getParent()->getType()->castAs<RecordType>()->getDecl();
915 if (CXXRecordDecl *CXXRD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(ParentRD))
916 if (CXXRD->getNumBases())
917 return false;
918
919 auto FieldIt = ParentRD->field_begin();
920 assert(FieldIt != ParentRD->field_end() &&
921 "no fields but have initializer for member?");
922 return ++FieldIt == ParentRD->field_end();
923}
924
925/// Check whether the range of the initializer \p ParentIList from element
926/// \p Index onwards can be used to initialize an object of type \p T. Update
927/// \p Index to indicate how many elements of the list were consumed.
928///
929/// This also fills in \p StructuredList, from element \p StructuredIndex
930/// onwards, with the fully-braced, desugared form of the initialization.
931void InitListChecker::CheckImplicitInitList(const InitializedEntity &Entity,
932 InitListExpr *ParentIList,
933 QualType T, unsigned &Index,
934 InitListExpr *StructuredList,
935 unsigned &StructuredIndex) {
936 int maxElements = 0;
937
938 if (T->isArrayType())
939 maxElements = numArrayElements(T);
940 else if (T->isRecordType())
941 maxElements = numStructUnionElements(T);
942 else if (T->isVectorType())
943 maxElements = T->getAs<VectorType>()->getNumElements();
944 else
945 llvm_unreachable("CheckImplicitInitList(): Illegal type");
946
947 if (maxElements == 0) {
948 if (!VerifyOnly)
949 SemaRef.Diag(ParentIList->getInit(Index)->getBeginLoc(),
950 diag::err_implicit_empty_initializer);
951 ++Index;
952 hadError = true;
953 return;
954 }
955
956 // Build a structured initializer list corresponding to this subobject.
957 InitListExpr *StructuredSubobjectInitList = getStructuredSubobjectInit(
958 ParentIList, Index, T, StructuredList, StructuredIndex,
959 SourceRange(ParentIList->getInit(Index)->getBeginLoc(),
960 ParentIList->getSourceRange().getEnd()));
961 unsigned StructuredSubobjectInitIndex = 0;
962
963 // Check the element types and build the structural subobject.
964 unsigned StartIndex = Index;
965 CheckListElementTypes(Entity, ParentIList, T,
966 /*SubobjectIsDesignatorContext=*/false, Index,
967 StructuredSubobjectInitList,
968 StructuredSubobjectInitIndex);
969
970 if (!VerifyOnly) {
971 StructuredSubobjectInitList->setType(T);
972
973 unsigned EndIndex = (Index == StartIndex? StartIndex : Index - 1);
974 // Update the structured sub-object initializer so that it's ending
975 // range corresponds with the end of the last initializer it used.
976 if (EndIndex < ParentIList->getNumInits() &&
977 ParentIList->getInit(EndIndex)) {
978 SourceLocation EndLoc
979 = ParentIList->getInit(EndIndex)->getSourceRange().getEnd();
980 StructuredSubobjectInitList->setRBraceLoc(EndLoc);
981 }
982
983 // Complain about missing braces.
984 if ((T->isArrayType() || T->isRecordType()) &&
985 !ParentIList->isIdiomaticZeroInitializer(SemaRef.getLangOpts()) &&
986 !isIdiomaticBraceElisionEntity(Entity)) {
987 SemaRef.Diag(StructuredSubobjectInitList->getBeginLoc(),
988 diag::warn_missing_braces)
989 << StructuredSubobjectInitList->getSourceRange()
990 << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(
991 StructuredSubobjectInitList->getBeginLoc(), "{")
992 << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(
993 SemaRef.getLocForEndOfToken(
994 StructuredSubobjectInitList->getEndLoc()),
995 "}");
996 }
997
998 // Warn if this type won't be an aggregate in future versions of C++.
999 auto *CXXRD = T->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
1000 if (CXXRD && CXXRD->hasUserDeclaredConstructor()) {
1001 SemaRef.Diag(StructuredSubobjectInitList->getBeginLoc(),
1002 diag::warn_cxx2a_compat_aggregate_init_with_ctors)
1003 << StructuredSubobjectInitList->getSourceRange() << T;
1004 }
1005 }
1006}
1007
1008/// Warn that \p Entity was of scalar type and was initialized by a
1009/// single-element braced initializer list.
1010static void warnBracedScalarInit(Sema &S, const InitializedEntity &Entity,
1011 SourceRange Braces) {
1012 // Don't warn during template instantiation. If the initialization was
1013 // non-dependent, we warned during the initial parse; otherwise, the
1014 // type might not be scalar in some uses of the template.
1015 if (S.inTemplateInstantiation())
1016 return;
1017
1018 unsigned DiagID = 0;
1019
1020 switch (Entity.getKind()) {
1021 case InitializedEntity::EK_VectorElement:
1022 case InitializedEntity::EK_ComplexElement:
1023 case InitializedEntity::EK_ArrayElement:
1024 case InitializedEntity::EK_Parameter:
1025 case InitializedEntity::EK_Parameter_CF_Audited:
1026 case InitializedEntity::EK_Result:
1027 // Extra braces here are suspicious.
1028 DiagID = diag::warn_braces_around_scalar_init;
1029 break;
1030
1031 case InitializedEntity::EK_Member:
1032 // Warn on aggregate initialization but not on ctor init list or
1033 // default member initializer.
1034 if (Entity.getParent())
1035 DiagID = diag::warn_braces_around_scalar_init;
1036 break;
1037
1038 case InitializedEntity::EK_Variable:
1039 case InitializedEntity::EK_LambdaCapture:
1040 // No warning, might be direct-list-initialization.
1041 // FIXME: Should we warn for copy-list-initialization in these cases?
1042 break;
1043
1044 case InitializedEntity::EK_New:
1045 case InitializedEntity::EK_Temporary:
1046 case InitializedEntity::EK_CompoundLiteralInit:
1047 // No warning, braces are part of the syntax of the underlying construct.
1048 break;
1049
1050 case InitializedEntity::EK_RelatedResult:
1051 // No warning, we already warned when initializing the result.
1052 break;
1053
1054 case InitializedEntity::EK_Exception:
1055 case InitializedEntity::EK_Base:
1056 case InitializedEntity::EK_Delegating:
1057 case InitializedEntity::EK_BlockElement:
1058 case InitializedEntity::EK_LambdaToBlockConversionBlockElement:
1059 case InitializedEntity::EK_Binding:
1060 case InitializedEntity::EK_StmtExprResult:
1061 llvm_unreachable("unexpected braced scalar init");
1062 }
1063
1064 if (DiagID) {
1065 S.Diag(Braces.getBegin(), DiagID)
1066 << Braces
1067 << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(Braces.getBegin())
1068 << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(Braces.getEnd());
1069 }
1070}
1071
1072/// Check whether the initializer \p IList (that was written with explicit
1073/// braces) can be used to initialize an object of type \p T.
1074///
1075/// This also fills in \p StructuredList with the fully-braced, desugared
1076/// form of the initialization.
1077void InitListChecker::CheckExplicitInitList(const InitializedEntity &Entity,
1078 InitListExpr *IList, QualType &T,
1079 InitListExpr *StructuredList,
1080 bool TopLevelObject) {
1081 if (!VerifyOnly) {
1082 SyntacticToSemantic[IList] = StructuredList;
1083 StructuredList->setSyntacticForm(IList);
1084 }
1085
1086 unsigned Index = 0, StructuredIndex = 0;
1087 CheckListElementTypes(Entity, IList, T, /*SubobjectIsDesignatorContext=*/true,
1088 Index, StructuredList, StructuredIndex, TopLevelObject);
1089 if (!VerifyOnly) {
1090 QualType ExprTy = T;
1091 if (!ExprTy->isArrayType())
1092 ExprTy = ExprTy.getNonLValueExprType(SemaRef.Context);
1093 IList->setType(ExprTy);
1094 StructuredList->setType(ExprTy);
1095 }
1096 if (hadError)
1097 return;
1098
1099 if (Index < IList->getNumInits()) {
1100 // We have leftover initializers
1101 if (VerifyOnly) {
1102 if (SemaRef.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus ||
1103 (SemaRef.getLangOpts().OpenCL &&
1104 IList->getType()->isVectorType())) {
1105 hadError = true;
1106 }
1107 return;
1108 }
1109
1110 if (StructuredIndex == 1 &&
1111 IsStringInit(StructuredList->getInit(0), T, SemaRef.Context) ==
1112 SIF_None) {
1113 unsigned DK = diag::ext_excess_initializers_in_char_array_initializer;
1114 if (SemaRef.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
1115 DK = diag::err_excess_initializers_in_char_array_initializer;
1116 hadError = true;
1117 }
1118 // Special-case
1119 SemaRef.Diag(IList->getInit(Index)->getBeginLoc(), DK)
1120 << IList->getInit(Index)->getSourceRange();
1121 } else if (!T->isIncompleteType()) {
1122 // Don't complain for incomplete types, since we'll get an error
1123 // elsewhere
1124 QualType CurrentObjectType = StructuredList->getType();
1125 int initKind =
1126 CurrentObjectType->isArrayType()? 0 :
1127 CurrentObjectType->isVectorType()? 1 :
1128 CurrentObjectType->isScalarType()? 2 :
1129 CurrentObjectType->isUnionType()? 3 :
1130 4;
1131
1132 unsigned DK = diag::ext_excess_initializers;
1133 if (SemaRef.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
1134 DK = diag::err_excess_initializers;
1135 hadError = true;
1136 }
1137 if (SemaRef.getLangOpts().OpenCL && initKind == 1) {
1138 DK = diag::err_excess_initializers;
1139 hadError = true;
1140 }
1141
1142 SemaRef.Diag(IList->getInit(Index)->getBeginLoc(), DK)
1143 << initKind << IList->getInit(Index)->getSourceRange();
1144 }
1145 }
1146
1147 if (!VerifyOnly) {
1148 if (T->isScalarType() && IList->getNumInits() == 1 &&
1149 !isa<InitListExpr>(IList->getInit(0)))
1150 warnBracedScalarInit(SemaRef, Entity, IList->getSourceRange());
1151
1152 // Warn if this is a class type that won't be an aggregate in future
1153 // versions of C++.
1154 auto *CXXRD = T->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
1155 if (CXXRD && CXXRD->hasUserDeclaredConstructor()) {
1156 // Don't warn if there's an equivalent default constructor that would be
1157 // used instead.
1158 bool HasEquivCtor = false;
1159 if (IList->getNumInits() == 0) {
1160 auto *CD = SemaRef.LookupDefaultConstructor(CXXRD);
1161 HasEquivCtor = CD && !CD->isDeleted();
1162 }
1163
1164 if (!HasEquivCtor) {
1165 SemaRef.Diag(IList->getBeginLoc(),
1166 diag::warn_cxx2a_compat_aggregate_init_with_ctors)
1167 << IList->getSourceRange() << T;
1168 }
1169 }
1170 }
1171}
1172
1173void InitListChecker::CheckListElementTypes(const InitializedEntity &Entity,
1174 InitListExpr *IList,
1175 QualType &DeclType,
1176 bool SubobjectIsDesignatorContext,
1177 unsigned &Index,
1178 InitListExpr *StructuredList,
1179 unsigned &StructuredIndex,
1180 bool TopLevelObject) {
1181 if (DeclType->isAnyComplexType() && SubobjectIsDesignatorContext) {
1182 // Explicitly braced initializer for complex type can be real+imaginary
1183 // parts.
1184 CheckComplexType(Entity, IList, DeclType, Index,
1185 StructuredList, StructuredIndex);
1186 } else if (DeclType->isScalarType()) {
1187 CheckScalarType(Entity, IList, DeclType, Index,
1188 StructuredList, StructuredIndex);
1189 } else if (DeclType->isVectorType()) {
1190 CheckVectorType(Entity, IList, DeclType, Index,
1191 StructuredList, StructuredIndex);
1192 } else if (DeclType->isRecordType()) {
1193 assert(DeclType->isAggregateType() &&
1194 "non-aggregate records should be handed in CheckSubElementType");
1195 RecordDecl *RD = DeclType->getAs<RecordType>()->getDecl();
1196 auto Bases =
1197 CXXRecordDecl::base_class_range(CXXRecordDecl::base_class_iterator(),
1198 CXXRecordDecl::base_class_iterator());
1199 if (auto *CXXRD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RD))
1200 Bases = CXXRD->bases();
1201 CheckStructUnionTypes(Entity, IList, DeclType, Bases, RD->field_begin(),
1202 SubobjectIsDesignatorContext, Index, StructuredList,
1203 StructuredIndex, TopLevelObject);
1204 } else if (DeclType->isArrayType()) {
1205 llvm::APSInt Zero(
1206 SemaRef.Context.getTypeSize(SemaRef.Context.getSizeType()),
1207 false);
1208 CheckArrayType(Entity, IList, DeclType, Zero,
1209 SubobjectIsDesignatorContext, Index,
1210 StructuredList, StructuredIndex);
1211 } else if (DeclType->isVoidType() || DeclType->isFunctionType()) {
1212 // This type is invalid, issue a diagnostic.
1213 ++Index;
1214 if (!VerifyOnly)
1215 SemaRef.Diag(IList->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_illegal_initializer_type)
1216 << DeclType;
1217 hadError = true;
1218 } else if (DeclType->isReferenceType()) {
1219 CheckReferenceType(Entity, IList, DeclType, Index,
1220 StructuredList, StructuredIndex);
1221 } else if (DeclType->isObjCObjectType()) {
1222 if (!VerifyOnly)
1223 SemaRef.Diag(IList->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_init_objc_class) << DeclType;
1224 hadError = true;
1225 } else if (DeclType->isOCLIntelSubgroupAVCType()) {
1226 // Checks for scalar type are sufficient for these types too.
1227 CheckScalarType(Entity, IList, DeclType, Index, StructuredList,
1228 StructuredIndex);
1229 } else {
1230 if (!VerifyOnly)
1231 SemaRef.Diag(IList->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_illegal_initializer_type)
1232 << DeclType;
1233 hadError = true;
1234 }
1235}
1236
1237void InitListChecker::CheckSubElementType(const InitializedEntity &Entity,
1238 InitListExpr *IList,
1239 QualType ElemType,
1240 unsigned &Index,
1241 InitListExpr *StructuredList,
1242 unsigned &StructuredIndex) {
1243 Expr *expr = IList->getInit(Index);
1244
1245 if (ElemType->isReferenceType())
1246 return CheckReferenceType(Entity, IList, ElemType, Index,
1247 StructuredList, StructuredIndex);
1248
1249 if (InitListExpr *SubInitList = dyn_cast<InitListExpr>(expr)) {
1250 if (SubInitList->getNumInits() == 1 &&
1251 IsStringInit(SubInitList->getInit(0), ElemType, SemaRef.Context) ==
1252 SIF_None) {
1253 expr = SubInitList->getInit(0);
1254 } else if (!SemaRef.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
1255 InitListExpr *InnerStructuredList
1256 = getStructuredSubobjectInit(IList, Index, ElemType,
1257 StructuredList, StructuredIndex,
1258 SubInitList->getSourceRange(), true);
1259 CheckExplicitInitList(Entity, SubInitList, ElemType,
1260 InnerStructuredList);
1261
1262 if (!hadError && !VerifyOnly) {
1263 bool RequiresSecondPass = false;
1264 FillInEmptyInitializations(Entity, InnerStructuredList,
1265 RequiresSecondPass, StructuredList,
1266 StructuredIndex);
1267 if (RequiresSecondPass && !hadError)
1268 FillInEmptyInitializations(Entity, InnerStructuredList,
1269 RequiresSecondPass, StructuredList,
1270 StructuredIndex);
1271 }
1272 ++StructuredIndex;
1273 ++Index;
1274 return;
1275 }
1276 // C++ initialization is handled later.
1277 } else if (isa<ImplicitValueInitExpr>(expr)) {
1278 // This happens during template instantiation when we see an InitListExpr
1279 // that we've already checked once.
1280 assert(SemaRef.Context.hasSameType(expr->getType(), ElemType) &&
1281 "found implicit initialization for the wrong type");
1282 if (!VerifyOnly)
1283 UpdateStructuredListElement(StructuredList, StructuredIndex, expr);
1284 ++Index;
1285 return;
1286 }
1287
1288 if (SemaRef.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
1289 // C++ [dcl.init.aggr]p2:
1290 // Each member is copy-initialized from the corresponding
1291 // initializer-clause.
1292
1293 // FIXME: Better EqualLoc?
1294 InitializationKind Kind =
1295 InitializationKind::CreateCopy(expr->getBeginLoc(), SourceLocation());
1296 InitializationSequence Seq(SemaRef, Entity, Kind, expr,
1297 /*TopLevelOfInitList*/ true);
1298
1299 // C++14 [dcl.init.aggr]p13:
1300 // If the assignment-expression can initialize a member, the member is
1301 // initialized. Otherwise [...] brace elision is assumed
1302 //
1303 // Brace elision is never performed if the element is not an
1304 // assignment-expression.
1305 if (Seq || isa<InitListExpr>(expr)) {
1306 if (!VerifyOnly) {
1307 ExprResult Result =
1308 Seq.Perform(SemaRef, Entity, Kind, expr);
1309 if (Result.isInvalid())
1310 hadError = true;
1311
1312 UpdateStructuredListElement(StructuredList, StructuredIndex,
1313 Result.getAs<Expr>());
1314 } else if (!Seq)
1315 hadError = true;
1316 ++Index;
1317 return;
1318 }
1319
1320 // Fall through for subaggregate initialization
1321 } else if (ElemType->isScalarType() || ElemType->isAtomicType()) {
1322 // FIXME: Need to handle atomic aggregate types with implicit init lists.
1323 return CheckScalarType(Entity, IList, ElemType, Index,
1324 StructuredList, StructuredIndex);
1325 } else if (const ArrayType *arrayType =
1326 SemaRef.Context.getAsArrayType(ElemType)) {
1327 // arrayType can be incomplete if we're initializing a flexible
1328 // array member. There's nothing we can do with the completed
1329 // type here, though.
1330
1331 if (IsStringInit(expr, arrayType, SemaRef.Context) == SIF_None) {
1332 if (!VerifyOnly) {
1333 CheckStringInit(expr, ElemType, arrayType, SemaRef);
1334 UpdateStructuredListElement(StructuredList, StructuredIndex, expr);
1335 }
1336 ++Index;
1337 return;
1338 }
1339
1340 // Fall through for subaggregate initialization.
1341
1342 } else {
1343 assert((ElemType->isRecordType() || ElemType->isVectorType() ||
1344 ElemType->isOpenCLSpecificType()) && "Unexpected type");
1345
1346 // C99 6.7.8p13:
1347 //
1348 // The initializer for a structure or union object that has
1349 // automatic storage duration shall be either an initializer
1350 // list as described below, or a single expression that has
1351 // compatible structure or union type. In the latter case, the
1352 // initial value of the object, including unnamed members, is
1353 // that of the expression.
1354 ExprResult ExprRes = expr;
1355 if (SemaRef.CheckSingleAssignmentConstraints(
1356 ElemType, ExprRes, !VerifyOnly) != Sema::Incompatible) {
1357 if (ExprRes.isInvalid())
1358 hadError = true;
1359 else {
1360 ExprRes = SemaRef.DefaultFunctionArrayLvalueConversion(ExprRes.get());
1361 if (ExprRes.isInvalid())
1362 hadError = true;
1363 }
1364 UpdateStructuredListElement(StructuredList, StructuredIndex,
1365 ExprRes.getAs<Expr>());
1366 ++Index;
1367 return;
1368 }
1369 ExprRes.get();
1370 // Fall through for subaggregate initialization
1371 }
1372
1373 // C++ [dcl.init.aggr]p12:
1374 //
1375 // [...] Otherwise, if the member is itself a non-empty
1376 // subaggregate, brace elision is assumed and the initializer is
1377 // considered for the initialization of the first member of
1378 // the subaggregate.
1379 // OpenCL vector initializer is handled elsewhere.
1380 if ((!SemaRef.getLangOpts().OpenCL && ElemType->isVectorType()) ||
1381 ElemType->isAggregateType()) {
1382 CheckImplicitInitList(Entity, IList, ElemType, Index, StructuredList,
1383 StructuredIndex);
1384 ++StructuredIndex;
1385 } else {
1386 if (!VerifyOnly) {
1387 // We cannot initialize this element, so let
1388 // PerformCopyInitialization produce the appropriate diagnostic.
1389 SemaRef.PerformCopyInitialization(Entity, SourceLocation(), expr,
1390 /*TopLevelOfInitList=*/true);
1391 }
1392 hadError = true;
1393 ++Index;
1394 ++StructuredIndex;
1395 }
1396}
1397
1398void InitListChecker::CheckComplexType(const InitializedEntity &Entity,
1399 InitListExpr *IList, QualType DeclType,
1400 unsigned &Index,
1401 InitListExpr *StructuredList,
1402 unsigned &StructuredIndex) {
1403 assert(Index == 0 && "Index in explicit init list must be zero");
1404
1405 // As an extension, clang supports complex initializers, which initialize
1406 // a complex number component-wise. When an explicit initializer list for
1407 // a complex number contains two two initializers, this extension kicks in:
1408 // it exepcts the initializer list to contain two elements convertible to
1409 // the element type of the complex type. The first element initializes
1410 // the real part, and the second element intitializes the imaginary part.
1411
1412 if (IList->getNumInits() != 2)
1413 return CheckScalarType(Entity, IList, DeclType, Index, StructuredList,
1414 StructuredIndex);
1415
1416 // This is an extension in C. (The builtin _Complex type does not exist
1417 // in the C++ standard.)
1418 if (!SemaRef.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus && !VerifyOnly)
1419 SemaRef.Diag(IList->getBeginLoc(), diag::ext_complex_component_init)
1420 << IList->getSourceRange();
1421
1422 // Initialize the complex number.
1423 QualType elementType = DeclType->getAs<ComplexType>()->getElementType();
1424 InitializedEntity ElementEntity =
1425 InitializedEntity::InitializeElement(SemaRef.Context, 0, Entity);
1426
1427 for (unsigned i = 0; i < 2; ++i) {
1428 ElementEntity.setElementIndex(Index);
1429 CheckSubElementType(ElementEntity, IList, elementType, Index,
1430 StructuredList, StructuredIndex);
1431 }
1432}
1433
1434bool InitListChecker::isCapNarrowing(Expr* expr, QualType DeclType,
1435 unsigned *Index, unsigned *StructuredIndex) {
1436 if (SemaRef.Context.getLangOpts().getCheriCapConversion() ==
1437 LangOptions::CapConv_Ignore)
1438 return false;
1439
1440 // XXXAR: expr->getType() will return int for int&!
1441 QualType ExprType = expr->getRealReferenceType(SemaRef.Context);
1442 if (ExprType->isCHERICapabilityType(SemaRef.Context) &&
1443 !DeclType->isCHERICapabilityType(SemaRef.Context)) {
1444 // Initializing a T with a T& should be fine.
1445 if (ExprType->isReferenceType() && !DeclType->isReferenceType())
1446 return false;
1447 // For uintcap_t -> integer conversion fall back to the default diagnostics
1448 if (ExprType->isIntCapType() && DeclType->isIntegerType())
1449 return false;
1450 // TODO: allow for nullptr, etc.
1451 if (!VerifyOnly) {
1452 SemaRef.Diag(expr->getBeginLoc(), diag::ext_init_list_type_narrowing)
1453 << ExprType << DeclType << expr->getSourceRange();
1454 }
1455 ++(*Index);
1456 ++(*StructuredIndex);
1457 return true;
1458 }
1459 return false;
1460}
1461
1462void InitListChecker::CheckScalarType(const InitializedEntity &Entity,
1463 InitListExpr *IList, QualType DeclType,
1464 unsigned &Index,
1465 InitListExpr *StructuredList,
1466 unsigned &StructuredIndex) {
1467 if (Index >= IList->getNumInits()) {
1468 if (!VerifyOnly)
1469 SemaRef.Diag(IList->getBeginLoc(),
1470 SemaRef.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11
1471 ? diag::warn_cxx98_compat_empty_scalar_initializer
1472 : diag::err_empty_scalar_initializer)
1473 << IList->getSourceRange();
1474 hadError = !SemaRef.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11;
1475 ++Index;
1476 ++StructuredIndex;
1477 return;
1478 }
1479
1480 Expr *expr = IList->getInit(Index);
1481 if (isCapNarrowing(expr, DeclType, &Index, &StructuredIndex)) {
1482 hadError = true;
1483 return;
1484 }
1485 if (InitListExpr *SubIList = dyn_cast<InitListExpr>(expr)) {
1486 // FIXME: This is invalid, and accepting it causes overload resolution
1487 // to pick the wrong overload in some corner cases.
1488 if (!VerifyOnly)
1489 SemaRef.Diag(SubIList->getBeginLoc(),
1490 diag::ext_many_braces_around_scalar_init)
1491 << SubIList->getSourceRange();
1492
1493 CheckScalarType(Entity, SubIList, DeclType, Index, StructuredList,
1494 StructuredIndex);
1495 return;
1496 } else if (isa<DesignatedInitExpr>(expr)) {
1497 if (!VerifyOnly)
1498 SemaRef.Diag(expr->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_designator_for_scalar_init)
1499 << DeclType << expr->getSourceRange();
1500 hadError = true;
1501 ++Index;
1502 ++StructuredIndex;
1503 return;
1504 }
1505
1506 if (VerifyOnly) {
1507 if (!SemaRef.CanPerformCopyInitialization(Entity,expr))
1508 hadError = true;
1509 ++Index;
1510 return;
1511 }
1512
1513 ExprResult Result =
1514 SemaRef.PerformCopyInitialization(Entity, expr->getBeginLoc(), expr,
1515 /*TopLevelOfInitList=*/true);
1516
1517 Expr *ResultExpr = nullptr;
1518
1519 if (Result.isInvalid())
1520 hadError = true; // types weren't compatible.
1521 else {
1522 ResultExpr = Result.getAs<Expr>();
1523
1524 if (ResultExpr != expr) {
1525 // The type was promoted, update initializer list.
1526 IList->setInit(Index, ResultExpr);
1527 }
1528 }
1529 if (hadError)
1530 ++StructuredIndex;
1531 else
1532 UpdateStructuredListElement(StructuredList, StructuredIndex, ResultExpr);
1533 ++Index;
1534}
1535
1536void InitListChecker::CheckReferenceType(const InitializedEntity &Entity,
1537 InitListExpr *IList, QualType DeclType,
1538 unsigned &Index,
1539 InitListExpr *StructuredList,
1540 unsigned &StructuredIndex) {
1541 if (Index >= IList->getNumInits()) {
1542 // FIXME: It would be wonderful if we could point at the actual member. In
1543 // general, it would be useful to pass location information down the stack,
1544 // so that we know the location (or decl) of the "current object" being
1545 // initialized.
1546 if (!VerifyOnly)
1547 SemaRef.Diag(IList->getBeginLoc(),
1548 diag::err_init_reference_member_uninitialized)
1549 << DeclType << IList->getSourceRange();
1550 hadError = true;
1551 ++Index;
1552 ++StructuredIndex;
1553 return;
1554 }
1555
1556 Expr *expr = IList->getInit(Index);
1557 if (isa<InitListExpr>(expr) && !SemaRef.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11) {
1558 if (!VerifyOnly)
1559 SemaRef.Diag(IList->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_init_non_aggr_init_list)
1560 << DeclType << IList->getSourceRange();
1561 hadError = true;
1562 ++Index;
1563 ++StructuredIndex;
1564 return;
1565 }
1566
1567 if (VerifyOnly) {
1568 if (!SemaRef.CanPerformCopyInitialization(Entity,expr))
1569 hadError = true;
1570 ++Index;
1571 return;
1572 }
1573
1574 ExprResult Result =
1575 SemaRef.PerformCopyInitialization(Entity, expr->getBeginLoc(), expr,
1576 /*TopLevelOfInitList=*/true);
1577
1578 if (Result.isInvalid())
1579 hadError = true;
1580
1581 expr = Result.getAs<Expr>();
1582 if (expr) {
1583 if (isCapNarrowing(expr, DeclType, &Index, &StructuredIndex)) {
1584 hadError = true;
1585 return;
1586 }
1587 }
1588 IList->setInit(Index, expr);
1589
1590 if (hadError)
1591 ++StructuredIndex;
1592 else
1593 UpdateStructuredListElement(StructuredList, StructuredIndex, expr);
1594 ++Index;
1595}
1596
1597void InitListChecker::CheckVectorType(const InitializedEntity &Entity,
1598 InitListExpr *IList, QualType DeclType,
1599 unsigned &Index,
1600 InitListExpr *StructuredList,
1601 unsigned &StructuredIndex) {
1602 const VectorType *VT = DeclType->getAs<VectorType>();
1603 unsigned maxElements = VT->getNumElements();
1604 unsigned numEltsInit = 0;
1605 QualType elementType = VT->getElementType();
1606
1607 if (Index >= IList->getNumInits()) {
1608 // Make sure the element type can be value-initialized.
1609 if (VerifyOnly)
1610 CheckEmptyInitializable(
1611 InitializedEntity::InitializeElement(SemaRef.Context, 0, Entity),
1612 IList->getEndLoc());
1613 return;
1614 }
1615
1616 if (!SemaRef.getLangOpts().OpenCL) {
1617 // If the initializing element is a vector, try to copy-initialize
1618 // instead of breaking it apart (which is doomed to failure anyway).
1619 Expr *Init = IList->getInit(Index);
1620 if (!isa<InitListExpr>(Init) && Init->getType()->isVectorType()) {
1621 if (VerifyOnly) {
1622 if (!SemaRef.CanPerformCopyInitialization(Entity, Init))
1623 hadError = true;
1624 ++Index;
1625 return;
1626 }
1627
1628 ExprResult Result =
1629 SemaRef.PerformCopyInitialization(Entity, Init->getBeginLoc(), Init,
1630 /*TopLevelOfInitList=*/true);
1631
1632 Expr *ResultExpr = nullptr;
1633 if (Result.isInvalid())
1634 hadError = true; // types weren't compatible.
1635 else {
1636 ResultExpr = Result.getAs<Expr>();
1637
1638 if (ResultExpr != Init) {
1639 // The type was promoted, update initializer list.
1640 IList->setInit(Index, ResultExpr);
1641 }
1642 }
1643 if (hadError)
1644 ++StructuredIndex;
1645 else
1646 UpdateStructuredListElement(StructuredList, StructuredIndex,
1647 ResultExpr);
1648 ++Index;
1649 return;
1650 }
1651
1652 InitializedEntity ElementEntity =
1653 InitializedEntity::InitializeElement(SemaRef.Context, 0, Entity);
1654
1655 for (unsigned i = 0; i < maxElements; ++i, ++numEltsInit) {
1656 // Don't attempt to go past the end of the init list
1657 if (Index >= IList->getNumInits()) {
1658 if (VerifyOnly)
1659 CheckEmptyInitializable(ElementEntity, IList->getEndLoc());
1660 break;
1661 }
1662
1663 ElementEntity.setElementIndex(Index);
1664 CheckSubElementType(ElementEntity, IList, elementType, Index,
1665 StructuredList, StructuredIndex);
1666 }
1667
1668 if (VerifyOnly)
1669 return;
1670
1671 bool isBigEndian = SemaRef.Context.getTargetInfo().isBigEndian();
1672 const VectorType *T = Entity.getType()->getAs<VectorType>();
1673 if (isBigEndian && (T->getVectorKind() == VectorType::NeonVector ||
1674 T->getVectorKind() == VectorType::NeonPolyVector)) {
1675 // The ability to use vector initializer lists is a GNU vector extension
1676 // and is unrelated to the NEON intrinsics in arm_neon.h. On little
1677 // endian machines it works fine, however on big endian machines it
1678 // exhibits surprising behaviour:
1679 //
1680 // uint32x2_t x = {42, 64};
1681 // return vget_lane_u32(x, 0); // Will return 64.
1682 //
1683 // Because of this, explicitly call out that it is non-portable.
1684 //
1685 SemaRef.Diag(IList->getBeginLoc(),
1686 diag::warn_neon_vector_initializer_non_portable);
1687
1688 const char *typeCode;
1689 unsigned typeSize = SemaRef.Context.getTypeSize(elementType);
1690
1691 if (elementType->isFloatingType())
1692 typeCode = "f";
1693 else if (elementType->isSignedIntegerType())
1694 typeCode = "s";
1695 else if (elementType->isUnsignedIntegerType())
1696 typeCode = "u";
1697 else
1698 llvm_unreachable("Invalid element type!");
1699
1700 SemaRef.Diag(IList->getBeginLoc(),
1701 SemaRef.Context.getTypeSize(VT) > 64
1702 ? diag::note_neon_vector_initializer_non_portable_q
1703 : diag::note_neon_vector_initializer_non_portable)
1704 << typeCode << typeSize;
1705 }
1706
1707 return;
1708 }
1709
1710 InitializedEntity ElementEntity =
1711 InitializedEntity::InitializeElement(SemaRef.Context, 0, Entity);
1712
1713 // OpenCL initializers allows vectors to be constructed from vectors.
1714 for (unsigned i = 0; i < maxElements; ++i) {
1715 // Don't attempt to go past the end of the init list
1716 if (Index >= IList->getNumInits())
1717 break;
1718
1719 ElementEntity.setElementIndex(Index);
1720
1721 QualType IType = IList->getInit(Index)->getType();
1722 if (!IType->isVectorType()) {
1723 CheckSubElementType(ElementEntity, IList, elementType, Index,
1724 StructuredList, StructuredIndex);
1725 ++numEltsInit;
1726 } else {
1727 QualType VecType;
1728 const VectorType *IVT = IType->getAs<VectorType>();
1729 unsigned numIElts = IVT->getNumElements();
1730
1731 if (IType->isExtVectorType())
1732 VecType = SemaRef.Context.getExtVectorType(elementType, numIElts);
1733 else
1734 VecType = SemaRef.Context.getVectorType(elementType, numIElts,
1735 IVT->getVectorKind());
1736 CheckSubElementType(ElementEntity, IList, VecType, Index,
1737 StructuredList, StructuredIndex);
1738 numEltsInit += numIElts;
1739 }
1740 }
1741
1742 // OpenCL requires all elements to be initialized.
1743 if (numEltsInit != maxElements) {
1744 if (!VerifyOnly)
1745 SemaRef.Diag(IList->getBeginLoc(),
1746 diag::err_vector_incorrect_num_initializers)
1747 << (numEltsInit < maxElements) << maxElements << numEltsInit;
1748 hadError = true;
1749 }
1750}
1751
1752/// Check if the type of a class element has an accessible destructor, and marks
1753/// it referenced. Returns true if we shouldn't form a reference to the
1754/// destructor.
1755///
1756/// Aggregate initialization requires a class element's destructor be
1757/// accessible per 11.6.1 [dcl.init.aggr]:
1758///
1759/// The destructor for each element of class type is potentially invoked
1760/// (15.4 [class.dtor]) from the context where the aggregate initialization
1761/// occurs.
1762static bool checkDestructorReference(QualType ElementType, SourceLocation Loc,
1763 Sema &SemaRef) {
1764 auto *CXXRD = ElementType->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
1765 if (!CXXRD)
1766 return false;
1767
1768 CXXDestructorDecl *Destructor = SemaRef.LookupDestructor(CXXRD);
1769 SemaRef.CheckDestructorAccess(Loc, Destructor,
1770 SemaRef.PDiag(diag::err_access_dtor_temp)
1771 << ElementType);
1772 SemaRef.MarkFunctionReferenced(Loc, Destructor);
1773 return SemaRef.DiagnoseUseOfDecl(Destructor, Loc);
1774}
1775
1776void InitListChecker::CheckArrayType(const InitializedEntity &Entity,
1777 InitListExpr *IList, QualType &DeclType,
1778 llvm::APSInt elementIndex,
1779 bool SubobjectIsDesignatorContext,
1780 unsigned &Index,
1781 InitListExpr *StructuredList,
1782 unsigned &StructuredIndex) {
1783 const ArrayType *arrayType = SemaRef.Context.getAsArrayType(DeclType);
1784
1785 if (!VerifyOnly) {
1786 if (checkDestructorReference(arrayType->getElementType(),
1787 IList->getEndLoc(), SemaRef)) {
1788 hadError = true;
1789 return;
1790 }
1791 }
1792
1793 // Check for the special-case of initializing an array with a string.
1794 if (Index < IList->getNumInits()) {
1795 if (IsStringInit(IList->getInit(Index), arrayType, SemaRef.Context) ==
1796 SIF_None) {
1797 // We place the string literal directly into the resulting
1798 // initializer list. This is the only place where the structure
1799 // of the structured initializer list doesn't match exactly,
1800 // because doing so would involve allocating one character
1801 // constant for each string.
1802 if (!VerifyOnly) {
1803 CheckStringInit(IList->getInit(Index), DeclType, arrayType, SemaRef);
1804 UpdateStructuredListElement(StructuredList, StructuredIndex,
1805 IList->getInit(Index));
1806 StructuredList->resizeInits(SemaRef.Context, StructuredIndex);
1807 }
1808 ++Index;
1809 return;
1810 }
1811 }
1812 if (const VariableArrayType *VAT = dyn_cast<VariableArrayType>(arrayType)) {
1813 // Check for VLAs; in standard C it would be possible to check this
1814 // earlier, but I don't know where clang accepts VLAs (gcc accepts
1815 // them in all sorts of strange places).
1816 if (!VerifyOnly)
1817 SemaRef.Diag(VAT->getSizeExpr()->getBeginLoc(),
1818 diag::err_variable_object_no_init)
1819 << VAT->getSizeExpr()->getSourceRange();
1820 hadError = true;
1821 ++Index;
1822 ++StructuredIndex;
1823 return;
1824 }
1825
1826 // We might know the maximum number of elements in advance.
1827 llvm::APSInt maxElements(elementIndex.getBitWidth(),
1828 elementIndex.isUnsigned());
1829 bool maxElementsKnown = false;
1830 if (const ConstantArrayType *CAT = dyn_cast<ConstantArrayType>(arrayType)) {
1831 maxElements = CAT->getSize();
1832 elementIndex = elementIndex.extOrTrunc(maxElements.getBitWidth());
1833 elementIndex.setIsUnsigned(maxElements.isUnsigned());
1834 maxElementsKnown = true;
1835 }
1836
1837 QualType elementType = arrayType->getElementType();
1838 while (Index < IList->getNumInits()) {
1839 Expr *Init = IList->getInit(Index);
1840 if (DesignatedInitExpr *DIE = dyn_cast<DesignatedInitExpr>(Init)) {
1841 // If we're not the subobject that matches up with the '{' for
1842 // the designator, we shouldn't be handling the
1843 // designator. Return immediately.
1844 if (!SubobjectIsDesignatorContext)
1845 return;
1846
1847 // Handle this designated initializer. elementIndex will be
1848 // updated to be the next array element we'll initialize.
1849 if (CheckDesignatedInitializer(Entity, IList, DIE, 0,
1850 DeclType, nullptr, &elementIndex, Index,
1851 StructuredList, StructuredIndex, true,
1852 false)) {
1853 hadError = true;
1854 continue;
1855 }
1856
1857 if (elementIndex.getBitWidth() > maxElements.getBitWidth())
1858 maxElements = maxElements.extend(elementIndex.getBitWidth());
1859 else if (elementIndex.getBitWidth() < maxElements.getBitWidth())
1860 elementIndex = elementIndex.extend(maxElements.getBitWidth());
1861 elementIndex.setIsUnsigned(maxElements.isUnsigned());
1862
1863 // If the array is of incomplete type, keep track of the number of
1864 // elements in the initializer.
1865 if (!maxElementsKnown && elementIndex > maxElements)
1866 maxElements = elementIndex;
1867
1868 continue;
1869 }
1870
1871 // If we know the maximum number of elements, and we've already
1872 // hit it, stop consuming elements in the initializer list.
1873 if (maxElementsKnown && elementIndex == maxElements)
1874 break;
1875
1876 InitializedEntity ElementEntity =
1877 InitializedEntity::InitializeElement(SemaRef.Context, StructuredIndex,
1878 Entity);
1879 // Check this element.
1880 CheckSubElementType(ElementEntity, IList, elementType, Index,
1881 StructuredList, StructuredIndex);
1882 ++elementIndex;
1883
1884 // If the array is of incomplete type, keep track of the number of
1885 // elements in the initializer.
1886 if (!maxElementsKnown && elementIndex > maxElements)
1887 maxElements = elementIndex;
1888 }
1889 if (!hadError && DeclType->isIncompleteArrayType() && !VerifyOnly) {
1890 // If this is an incomplete array type, the actual type needs to
1891 // be calculated here.
1892 llvm::APSInt Zero(maxElements.getBitWidth(), maxElements.isUnsigned());
1893 if (maxElements == Zero && !Entity.isVariableLengthArrayNew()) {
1894 // Sizing an array implicitly to zero is not allowed by ISO C,
1895 // but is supported by GNU.
1896 SemaRef.Diag(IList->getBeginLoc(), diag::ext_typecheck_zero_array_size);
1897 }
1898
1899 DeclType = SemaRef.Context.getConstantArrayType(elementType, maxElements,
1900 ArrayType::Normal, 0);
1901 }
1902 if (!hadError && VerifyOnly) {
1903 // If there are any members of the array that get value-initialized, check
1904 // that is possible. That happens if we know the bound and don't have
1905 // enough elements, or if we're performing an array new with an unknown
1906 // bound.
1907 // FIXME: This needs to detect holes left by designated initializers too.
1908 if ((maxElementsKnown && elementIndex < maxElements) ||
1909 Entity.isVariableLengthArrayNew())
1910 CheckEmptyInitializable(
1911 InitializedEntity::InitializeElement(SemaRef.Context, 0, Entity),
1912 IList->getEndLoc());
1913 }
1914}
1915
1916bool InitListChecker::CheckFlexibleArrayInit(const InitializedEntity &Entity,
1917 Expr *InitExpr,
1918 FieldDecl *Field,
1919 bool TopLevelObject) {
1920 // Handle GNU flexible array initializers.
1921 unsigned FlexArrayDiag;
1922 if (isa<InitListExpr>(InitExpr) &&
1923 cast<InitListExpr>(InitExpr)->getNumInits() == 0) {
1924 // Empty flexible array init always allowed as an extension
1925 FlexArrayDiag = diag::ext_flexible_array_init;
1926 } else if (SemaRef.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
1927 // Disallow flexible array init in C++; it is not required for gcc
1928 // compatibility, and it needs work to IRGen correctly in general.
1929 FlexArrayDiag = diag::err_flexible_array_init;
1930 } else if (!TopLevelObject) {
1931 // Disallow flexible array init on non-top-level object
1932 FlexArrayDiag = diag::err_flexible_array_init;
1933 } else if (Entity.getKind() != InitializedEntity::EK_Variable) {
1934 // Disallow flexible array init on anything which is not a variable.
1935 FlexArrayDiag = diag::err_flexible_array_init;
1936 } else if (cast<VarDecl>(Entity.getDecl())->hasLocalStorage()) {
1937 // Disallow flexible array init on local variables.
1938 FlexArrayDiag = diag::err_flexible_array_init;
1939 } else {
1940 // Allow other cases.
1941 FlexArrayDiag = diag::ext_flexible_array_init;
1942 }
1943
1944 if (!VerifyOnly) {
1945 SemaRef.Diag(InitExpr->getBeginLoc(), FlexArrayDiag)
1946 << InitExpr->getBeginLoc();
1947 SemaRef.Diag(Field->getLocation(), diag::note_flexible_array_member)
1948 << Field;
1949 }
1950
1951 return FlexArrayDiag != diag::ext_flexible_array_init;
1952}
1953
1954void InitListChecker::CheckStructUnionTypes(
1955 const InitializedEntity &Entity, InitListExpr *IList, QualType DeclType,
1956 CXXRecordDecl::base_class_range Bases, RecordDecl::field_iterator Field,
1957 bool SubobjectIsDesignatorContext, unsigned &Index,
1958 InitListExpr *StructuredList, unsigned &StructuredIndex,
1959 bool TopLevelObject) {
1960 RecordDecl *structDecl = DeclType->getAs<RecordType>()->getDecl();
1961
1962 // If the record is invalid, some of it's members are invalid. To avoid
1963 // confusion, we forgo checking the intializer for the entire record.
1964 if (structDecl->isInvalidDecl()) {
1965 // Assume it was supposed to consume a single initializer.
1966 ++Index;
1967 hadError = true;
1968 return;
1969 }
1970
1971 if (DeclType->isUnionType() && IList->getNumInits() == 0) {
1972 RecordDecl *RD = DeclType->getAs<RecordType>()->getDecl();
1973
1974 if (!VerifyOnly)
1975 for (FieldDecl *FD : RD->fields()) {
1976 QualType ET = SemaRef.Context.getBaseElementType(FD->getType());
1977 if (checkDestructorReference(ET, IList->getEndLoc(), SemaRef)) {
1978 hadError = true;
1979 return;
1980 }
1981 }
1982
1983 // If there's a default initializer, use it.
1984 if (isa<CXXRecordDecl>(RD) && cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RD)->hasInClassInitializer()) {
1985 if (VerifyOnly)
1986 return;
1987 for (RecordDecl::field_iterator FieldEnd = RD->field_end();
1988 Field != FieldEnd; ++Field) {
1989 if (Field->hasInClassInitializer()) {
1990 StructuredList->setInitializedFieldInUnion(*Field);
1991 // FIXME: Actually build a CXXDefaultInitExpr?
1992 return;
1993 }
1994 }
1995 }
1996
1997 // Value-initialize the first member of the union that isn't an unnamed
1998 // bitfield.
1999 for (RecordDecl::field_iterator FieldEnd = RD->field_end();
2000 Field != FieldEnd; ++Field) {
2001 if (!Field->isUnnamedBitfield()) {
2002 if (VerifyOnly)
2003 CheckEmptyInitializable(
2004 InitializedEntity::InitializeMember(*Field, &Entity),
2005 IList->getEndLoc());
2006 else
2007 StructuredList->setInitializedFieldInUnion(*Field);
2008 break;
2009 }
2010 }
2011 return;
2012 }
2013
2014 bool InitializedSomething = false;
2015
2016 // If we have any base classes, they are initialized prior to the fields.
2017 for (auto &Base : Bases) {
2018 Expr *Init = Index < IList->getNumInits() ? IList->getInit(Index) : nullptr;
2019
2020 // Designated inits always initialize fields, so if we see one, all
2021 // remaining base classes have no explicit initializer.
2022 if (Init && isa<DesignatedInitExpr>(Init))
2023 Init = nullptr;
2024
2025 SourceLocation InitLoc = Init ? Init->getBeginLoc() : IList->getEndLoc();
2026 InitializedEntity BaseEntity = InitializedEntity::InitializeBase(
2027 SemaRef.Context, &Base, false, &Entity);
2028 if (Init) {
2029 CheckSubElementType(BaseEntity, IList, Base.getType(), Index,
2030 StructuredList, StructuredIndex);
2031 InitializedSomething = true;
2032 } else if (VerifyOnly) {
2033 CheckEmptyInitializable(BaseEntity, InitLoc);
2034 }
2035
2036 if (!VerifyOnly)
2037 if (checkDestructorReference(Base.getType(), InitLoc, SemaRef)) {
2038 hadError = true;
2039 return;
2040 }
2041 }
2042
2043 // If structDecl is a forward declaration, this loop won't do
2044 // anything except look at designated initializers; That's okay,
2045 // because an error should get printed out elsewhere. It might be
2046 // worthwhile to skip over the rest of the initializer, though.
2047 RecordDecl *RD = DeclType->getAs<RecordType>()->getDecl();
2048 RecordDecl::field_iterator FieldEnd = RD->field_end();
2049 bool CheckForMissingFields =
2050 !IList->isIdiomaticZeroInitializer(SemaRef.getLangOpts());
2051 bool HasDesignatedInit = false;
2052
2053 while (Index < IList->getNumInits()) {
2054 Expr *Init = IList->getInit(Index);
2055 SourceLocation InitLoc = Init->getBeginLoc();
2056
2057 if (DesignatedInitExpr *DIE = dyn_cast<DesignatedInitExpr>(Init)) {
2058 // If we're not the subobject that matches up with the '{' for
2059 // the designator, we shouldn't be handling the
2060 // designator. Return immediately.
2061 if (!SubobjectIsDesignatorContext)
2062 return;
2063
2064 HasDesignatedInit = true;
2065
2066 // Handle this designated initializer. Field will be updated to
2067 // the next field that we'll be initializing.
2068 if (CheckDesignatedInitializer(Entity, IList, DIE, 0,
2069 DeclType, &Field, nullptr, Index,
2070 StructuredList, StructuredIndex,
2071 true, TopLevelObject))
2072 hadError = true;
2073 else if (!VerifyOnly) {
2074 // Find the field named by the designated initializer.
2075 RecordDecl::field_iterator F = RD->field_begin();
2076 while (std::next(F) != Field)
2077 ++F;
2078 QualType ET = SemaRef.Context.getBaseElementType(F->getType());
2079 if (checkDestructorReference(ET, InitLoc, SemaRef)) {
2080 hadError = true;
2081 return;
2082 }
2083 }
2084
2085 InitializedSomething = true;
2086
2087 // Disable check for missing fields when designators are used.
2088 // This matches gcc behaviour.
2089 CheckForMissingFields = false;
2090 continue;
2091 }
2092
2093 if (Field == FieldEnd) {
2094 // We've run out of fields. We're done.
2095 break;
2096 }
2097
2098 // We've already initialized a member of a union. We're done.
2099 if (InitializedSomething && DeclType->isUnionType())
2100 break;
2101
2102 // If we've hit the flexible array member at the end, we're done.
2103 if (Field->getType()->isIncompleteArrayType())
2104 break;
2105
2106 if (Field->isUnnamedBitfield()) {
2107 // Don't initialize unnamed bitfields, e.g. "int : 20;"
2108 ++Field;
2109 continue;
2110 }
2111
2112 // Make sure we can use this declaration.
2113 bool InvalidUse;
2114 if (VerifyOnly)
2115 InvalidUse = !SemaRef.CanUseDecl(*Field, TreatUnavailableAsInvalid);
2116 else
2117 InvalidUse = SemaRef.DiagnoseUseOfDecl(
2118 *Field, IList->getInit(Index)->getBeginLoc());
2119 if (InvalidUse) {
2120 ++Index;
2121 ++Field;
2122 hadError = true;
2123 continue;
2124 }
2125
2126 if (!VerifyOnly) {
2127 QualType ET = SemaRef.Context.getBaseElementType(Field->getType());
2128 if (checkDestructorReference(ET, InitLoc, SemaRef)) {
2129 hadError = true;
2130 return;
2131 }
2132 }
2133
2134 InitializedEntity MemberEntity =
2135 InitializedEntity::InitializeMember(*Field, &Entity);
2136 CheckSubElementType(MemberEntity, IList, Field->getType(), Index,
2137 StructuredList, StructuredIndex);
2138 InitializedSomething = true;
2139
2140 if (DeclType->isUnionType() && !VerifyOnly) {
2141 // Initialize the first field within the union.
2142 StructuredList->setInitializedFieldInUnion(*Field);
2143 }
2144
2145 ++Field;
2146 }
2147
2148 // Emit warnings for missing struct field initializers.
2149 if (!VerifyOnly && InitializedSomething && CheckForMissingFields &&
2150 Field != FieldEnd && !Field->getType()->isIncompleteArrayType() &&
2151 !DeclType->isUnionType()) {
2152 // It is possible we have one or more unnamed bitfields remaining.
2153 // Find first (if any) named field and emit warning.
2154 for (RecordDecl::field_iterator it = Field, end = RD->field_end();
2155 it != end; ++it) {
2156 if (!it->isUnnamedBitfield() && !it->hasInClassInitializer()) {
2157 SemaRef.Diag(IList->getSourceRange().getEnd(),
2158 diag::warn_missing_field_initializers) << *it;
2159 break;
2160 }
2161 }
2162 }
2163
2164 // Check that any remaining fields can be value-initialized.
2165 if (VerifyOnly && Field != FieldEnd && !DeclType->isUnionType() &&
2166 !Field->getType()->isIncompleteArrayType()) {
2167 // FIXME: Should check for holes left by designated initializers too.
2168 for (; Field != FieldEnd && !hadError; ++Field) {
2169 if (!Field->isUnnamedBitfield() && !Field->hasInClassInitializer())
2170 CheckEmptyInitializable(
2171 InitializedEntity::InitializeMember(*Field, &Entity),
2172 IList->getEndLoc());
2173 }
2174 }
2175
