2176 // Check that the types of the remaining fields have accessible destructors.
2177 if (!VerifyOnly) {
2178 // If the initializer expression has a designated initializer, check the
2179 // elements for which a designated initializer is not provided too.
2180 RecordDecl::field_iterator I = HasDesignatedInit ? RD->field_begin()
2181 : Field;
2182 for (RecordDecl::field_iterator E = RD->field_end(); I != E; ++I) {
2183 QualType ET = SemaRef.Context.getBaseElementType(I->getType());
2184 if (checkDestructorReference(ET, IList->getEndLoc(), SemaRef)) {
2185 hadError = true;
2186 return;
2187 }
2188 }
2189 }
2190
2191 if (Field == FieldEnd || !Field->getType()->isIncompleteArrayType() ||
2192 Index >= IList->getNumInits())
2193 return;
2194
2195 if (CheckFlexibleArrayInit(Entity, IList->getInit(Index), *Field,
2196 TopLevelObject)) {
2197 hadError = true;
2198 ++Index;
2199 return;
2200 }
2201
2202 InitializedEntity MemberEntity =
2203 InitializedEntity::InitializeMember(*Field, &Entity);
2204
2205 if (isa<InitListExpr>(IList->getInit(Index)))
2206 CheckSubElementType(MemberEntity, IList, Field->getType(), Index,
2207 StructuredList, StructuredIndex);
2208 else
2209 CheckImplicitInitList(MemberEntity, IList, Field->getType(), Index,
2210 StructuredList, StructuredIndex);
2211}
2212
2213/// Expand a field designator that refers to a member of an
2214/// anonymous struct or union into a series of field designators that
2215/// refers to the field within the appropriate subobject.
2216///
2217static void ExpandAnonymousFieldDesignator(Sema &SemaRef,
2218 DesignatedInitExpr *DIE,
2219 unsigned DesigIdx,
2220 IndirectFieldDecl *IndirectField) {
2221 typedef DesignatedInitExpr::Designator Designator;
2222
2223 // Build the replacement designators.
2224 SmallVector<Designator, 4> Replacements;
2225 for (IndirectFieldDecl::chain_iterator PI = IndirectField->chain_begin(),
2226 PE = IndirectField->chain_end(); PI != PE; ++PI) {
2227 if (PI + 1 == PE)
2228 Replacements.push_back(Designator((IdentifierInfo *)nullptr,
2229 DIE->getDesignator(DesigIdx)->getDotLoc(),
2230 DIE->getDesignator(DesigIdx)->getFieldLoc()));
2231 else
2232 Replacements.push_back(Designator((IdentifierInfo *)nullptr,
2233 SourceLocation(), SourceLocation()));
2234 assert(isa<FieldDecl>(*PI));
2235 Replacements.back().setField(cast<FieldDecl>(*PI));
2236 }
2237
2238 // Expand the current designator into the set of replacement
2239 // designators, so we have a full subobject path down to where the
2240 // member of the anonymous struct/union is actually stored.
2241 DIE->ExpandDesignator(SemaRef.Context, DesigIdx, &Replacements[0],
2242 &Replacements[0] + Replacements.size());
2243}
2244
2245static DesignatedInitExpr *CloneDesignatedInitExpr(Sema &SemaRef,
2246 DesignatedInitExpr *DIE) {
2247 unsigned NumIndexExprs = DIE->getNumSubExprs() - 1;
2248 SmallVector<Expr*, 4> IndexExprs(NumIndexExprs);
2249 for (unsigned I = 0; I < NumIndexExprs; ++I)
2250 IndexExprs[I] = DIE->getSubExpr(I + 1);
2251 return DesignatedInitExpr::Create(SemaRef.Context, DIE->designators(),
2252 IndexExprs,
2253 DIE->getEqualOrColonLoc(),
2254 DIE->usesGNUSyntax(), DIE->getInit());
2255}
2256
2257namespace {
2258
2259// Callback to only accept typo corrections that are for field members of
2260// the given struct or union.
2261class FieldInitializerValidatorCCC final : public CorrectionCandidateCallback {
2262 public:
2263 explicit FieldInitializerValidatorCCC(RecordDecl *RD)
2264 : Record(RD) {}
2265
2266 bool ValidateCandidate(const TypoCorrection &candidate) override {
2267 FieldDecl *FD = candidate.getCorrectionDeclAs<FieldDecl>();
2268 return FD && FD->getDeclContext()->getRedeclContext()->Equals(Record);
2269 }
2270
2271 std::unique_ptr<CorrectionCandidateCallback> clone() override {
2272 return llvm::make_unique<FieldInitializerValidatorCCC>(*this);
2273 }
2274
2275 private:
2276 RecordDecl *Record;
2277};
2278
2279} // end anonymous namespace
2280
2281/// Check the well-formedness of a C99 designated initializer.
2282///
2283/// Determines whether the designated initializer @p DIE, which
2284/// resides at the given @p Index within the initializer list @p
2285/// IList, is well-formed for a current object of type @p DeclType
2286/// (C99 6.7.8). The actual subobject that this designator refers to
2287/// within the current subobject is returned in either
2288/// @p NextField or @p NextElementIndex (whichever is appropriate).
2289///
2290/// @param IList The initializer list in which this designated
2291/// initializer occurs.
2292///
2293/// @param DIE The designated initializer expression.
2294///
2295/// @param DesigIdx The index of the current designator.
2296///
2297/// @param CurrentObjectType The type of the "current object" (C99 6.7.8p17),
2298/// into which the designation in @p DIE should refer.
2299///
2300/// @param NextField If non-NULL and the first designator in @p DIE is
2301/// a field, this will be set to the field declaration corresponding
2302/// to the field named by the designator.
2303///
2304/// @param NextElementIndex If non-NULL and the first designator in @p
2305/// DIE is an array designator or GNU array-range designator, this
2306/// will be set to the last index initialized by this designator.
2307///
2308/// @param Index Index into @p IList where the designated initializer
2309/// @p DIE occurs.
2310///
2311/// @param StructuredList The initializer list expression that
2312/// describes all of the subobject initializers in the order they'll
2313/// actually be initialized.
2314///
2315/// @returns true if there was an error, false otherwise.
2316bool
2317InitListChecker::CheckDesignatedInitializer(const InitializedEntity &Entity,
2318 InitListExpr *IList,
2319 DesignatedInitExpr *DIE,
2320 unsigned DesigIdx,
2321 QualType &CurrentObjectType,
2322 RecordDecl::field_iterator *NextField,
2323 llvm::APSInt *NextElementIndex,
2324 unsigned &Index,
2325 InitListExpr *StructuredList,
2326 unsigned &StructuredIndex,
2327 bool FinishSubobjectInit,
2328 bool TopLevelObject) {
2329 if (DesigIdx == DIE->size()) {
2330 // Check the actual initialization for the designated object type.
2331 bool prevHadError = hadError;
2332
2333 // Temporarily remove the designator expression from the
2334 // initializer list that the child calls see, so that we don't try
2335 // to re-process the designator.
2336 unsigned OldIndex = Index;
2337 IList->setInit(OldIndex, DIE->getInit());
2338
2339 CheckSubElementType(Entity, IList, CurrentObjectType, Index,
2340 StructuredList, StructuredIndex);
2341
2342 // Restore the designated initializer expression in the syntactic
2343 // form of the initializer list.
2344 if (IList->getInit(OldIndex) != DIE->getInit())
2345 DIE->setInit(IList->getInit(OldIndex));
2346 IList->setInit(OldIndex, DIE);
2347
2348 return hadError && !prevHadError;
2349 }
2350
2351 DesignatedInitExpr::Designator *D = DIE->getDesignator(DesigIdx);
2352 bool IsFirstDesignator = (DesigIdx == 0);
2353 if (!VerifyOnly) {
2354 assert((IsFirstDesignator || StructuredList) &&
2355 "Need a non-designated initializer list to start from");
2356
2357 // Determine the structural initializer list that corresponds to the
2358 // current subobject.
2359 if (IsFirstDesignator)
2360 StructuredList = SyntacticToSemantic.lookup(IList);
2361 else {
2362 Expr *ExistingInit = StructuredIndex < StructuredList->getNumInits() ?
2363 StructuredList->getInit(StructuredIndex) : nullptr;
2364 if (!ExistingInit && StructuredList->hasArrayFiller())
2365 ExistingInit = StructuredList->getArrayFiller();
2366
2367 if (!ExistingInit)
2368 StructuredList = getStructuredSubobjectInit(
2369 IList, Index, CurrentObjectType, StructuredList, StructuredIndex,
2370 SourceRange(D->getBeginLoc(), DIE->getEndLoc()));
2371 else if (InitListExpr *Result = dyn_cast<InitListExpr>(ExistingInit))
2372 StructuredList = Result;
2373 else {
2374 if (DesignatedInitUpdateExpr *E =
2375 dyn_cast<DesignatedInitUpdateExpr>(ExistingInit))
2376 StructuredList = E->getUpdater();
2377 else {
2378 DesignatedInitUpdateExpr *DIUE = new (SemaRef.Context)
2379 DesignatedInitUpdateExpr(SemaRef.Context, D->getBeginLoc(),
2380 ExistingInit, DIE->getEndLoc());
2381 StructuredList->updateInit(SemaRef.Context, StructuredIndex, DIUE);
2382 StructuredList = DIUE->getUpdater();
2383 }
2384
2385 // We need to check on source range validity because the previous
2386 // initializer does not have to be an explicit initializer. e.g.,
2387 //
2388 // struct P { int a, b; };
2389 // struct PP { struct P p } l = { { .a = 2 }, .p.b = 3 };
2390 //
2391 // There is an overwrite taking place because the first braced initializer
2392 // list "{ .a = 2 }" already provides value for .p.b (which is zero).
2393 if (ExistingInit->getSourceRange().isValid()) {
2394 // We are creating an initializer list that initializes the
2395 // subobjects of the current object, but there was already an
2396 // initialization that completely initialized the current
2397 // subobject, e.g., by a compound literal:
2398 //
2399 // struct X { int a, b; };
2400 // struct X xs[] = { [0] = (struct X) { 1, 2 }, [0].b = 3 };
2401 //
2402 // Here, xs[0].a == 0 and xs[0].b == 3, since the second,
2403 // designated initializer re-initializes the whole
2404 // subobject [0], overwriting previous initializers.
2405 SemaRef.Diag(D->getBeginLoc(),
2406 diag::warn_subobject_initializer_overrides)
2407 << SourceRange(D->getBeginLoc(), DIE->getEndLoc());
2408
2409 SemaRef.Diag(ExistingInit->getBeginLoc(),
2410 diag::note_previous_initializer)
2411 << /*FIXME:has side effects=*/0 << ExistingInit->getSourceRange();
2412 }
2413 }
2414 }
2415 assert(StructuredList && "Expected a structured initializer list");
2416 }
2417
2418 if (D->isFieldDesignator()) {
2419 // C99 6.7.8p7:
2420 //
2421 // If a designator has the form
2422 //
2423 // . identifier
2424 //
2425 // then the current object (defined below) shall have
2426 // structure or union type and the identifier shall be the
2427 // name of a member of that type.
2428 const RecordType *RT = CurrentObjectType->getAs<RecordType>();
2429 if (!RT) {
2430 SourceLocation Loc = D->getDotLoc();
2431 if (Loc.isInvalid())
2432 Loc = D->getFieldLoc();
2433 if (!VerifyOnly)
2434 SemaRef.Diag(Loc, diag::err_field_designator_non_aggr)
2435 << SemaRef.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus << CurrentObjectType;
2436 ++Index;
2437 return true;
2438 }
2439
2440 FieldDecl *KnownField = D->getField();
2441 if (!KnownField) {
2442 IdentifierInfo *FieldName = D->getFieldName();
2443 DeclContext::lookup_result Lookup = RT->getDecl()->lookup(FieldName);
2444 for (NamedDecl *ND : Lookup) {
2445 if (auto *FD = dyn_cast<FieldDecl>(ND)) {
2446 KnownField = FD;
2447 break;
2448 }
2449 if (auto *IFD = dyn_cast<IndirectFieldDecl>(ND)) {
2450 // In verify mode, don't modify the original.
2451 if (VerifyOnly)
2452 DIE = CloneDesignatedInitExpr(SemaRef, DIE);
2453 ExpandAnonymousFieldDesignator(SemaRef, DIE, DesigIdx, IFD);
2454 D = DIE->getDesignator(DesigIdx);
2455 KnownField = cast<FieldDecl>(*IFD->chain_begin());
2456 break;
2457 }
2458 }
2459 if (!KnownField) {
2460 if (VerifyOnly) {
2461 ++Index;
2462 return true; // No typo correction when just trying this out.
2463 }
2464
2465 // Name lookup found something, but it wasn't a field.
2466 if (!Lookup.empty()) {
2467 SemaRef.Diag(D->getFieldLoc(), diag::err_field_designator_nonfield)
2468 << FieldName;
2469 SemaRef.Diag(Lookup.front()->getLocation(),
2470 diag::note_field_designator_found);
2471 ++Index;
2472 return true;
2473 }
2474
2475 // Name lookup didn't find anything.
2476 // Determine whether this was a typo for another field name.
2477 FieldInitializerValidatorCCC CCC(RT->getDecl());
2478 if (TypoCorrection Corrected = SemaRef.CorrectTypo(
2479 DeclarationNameInfo(FieldName, D->getFieldLoc()),
2480 Sema::LookupMemberName, /*Scope=*/nullptr, /*SS=*/nullptr, CCC,
2481 Sema::CTK_ErrorRecovery, RT->getDecl())) {
2482 SemaRef.diagnoseTypo(
2483 Corrected,
2484 SemaRef.PDiag(diag::err_field_designator_unknown_suggest)
2485 << FieldName << CurrentObjectType);
2486 KnownField = Corrected.getCorrectionDeclAs<FieldDecl>();
2487 hadError = true;
2488 } else {
2489 // Typo correction didn't find anything.
2490 SemaRef.Diag(D->getFieldLoc(), diag::err_field_designator_unknown)
2491 << FieldName << CurrentObjectType;
2492 ++Index;
2493 return true;
2494 }
2495 }
2496 }
2497
2498 unsigned FieldIndex = 0;
2499
2500 if (auto *CXXRD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RT->getDecl()))
2501 FieldIndex = CXXRD->getNumBases();
2502
2503 for (auto *FI : RT->getDecl()->fields()) {
2504 if (FI->isUnnamedBitfield())
2505 continue;
2506 if (declaresSameEntity(KnownField, FI)) {
2507 KnownField = FI;
2508 break;
2509 }
2510 ++FieldIndex;
2511 }
2512
2513 RecordDecl::field_iterator Field =
2514 RecordDecl::field_iterator(DeclContext::decl_iterator(KnownField));
2515
2516 // All of the fields of a union are located at the same place in
2517 // the initializer list.
2518 if (RT->getDecl()->isUnion()) {
2519 FieldIndex = 0;
2520 if (!VerifyOnly) {
2521 FieldDecl *CurrentField = StructuredList->getInitializedFieldInUnion();
2522 if (CurrentField && !declaresSameEntity(CurrentField, *Field)) {
2523 assert(StructuredList->getNumInits() == 1
2524 && "A union should never have more than one initializer!");
2525
2526 Expr *ExistingInit = StructuredList->getInit(0);
2527 if (ExistingInit) {
2528 // We're about to throw away an initializer, emit warning.
2529 SemaRef.Diag(D->getFieldLoc(),
2530 diag::warn_initializer_overrides)
2531 << D->getSourceRange();
2532 SemaRef.Diag(ExistingInit->getBeginLoc(),
2533 diag::note_previous_initializer)
2534 << /*FIXME:has side effects=*/0
2535 << ExistingInit->getSourceRange();
2536 }
2537
2538 // remove existing initializer
2539 StructuredList->resizeInits(SemaRef.Context, 0);
2540 StructuredList->setInitializedFieldInUnion(nullptr);
2541 }
2542
2543 StructuredList->setInitializedFieldInUnion(*Field);
2544 }
2545 }
2546
2547 // Make sure we can use this declaration.
2548 bool InvalidUse;
2549 if (VerifyOnly)
2550 InvalidUse = !SemaRef.CanUseDecl(*Field, TreatUnavailableAsInvalid);
2551 else
2552 InvalidUse = SemaRef.DiagnoseUseOfDecl(*Field, D->getFieldLoc());
2553 if (InvalidUse) {
2554 ++Index;
2555 return true;
2556 }
2557
2558 if (!VerifyOnly) {
2559 // Update the designator with the field declaration.
2560 D->setField(*Field);
2561
2562 // Make sure that our non-designated initializer list has space
2563 // for a subobject corresponding to this field.
2564 if (FieldIndex >= StructuredList->getNumInits())
2565 StructuredList->resizeInits(SemaRef.Context, FieldIndex + 1);
2566 }
2567
2568 // This designator names a flexible array member.
2569 if (Field->getType()->isIncompleteArrayType()) {
2570 bool Invalid = false;
2571 if ((DesigIdx + 1) != DIE->size()) {
2572 // We can't designate an object within the flexible array
2573 // member (because GCC doesn't allow it).
2574 if (!VerifyOnly) {
2575 DesignatedInitExpr::Designator *NextD
2576 = DIE->getDesignator(DesigIdx + 1);
2577 SemaRef.Diag(NextD->getBeginLoc(),
2578 diag::err_designator_into_flexible_array_member)
2579 << SourceRange(NextD->getBeginLoc(), DIE->getEndLoc());
2580 SemaRef.Diag(Field->getLocation(), diag::note_flexible_array_member)
2581 << *Field;
2582 }
2583 Invalid = true;
2584 }
2585
2586 if (!hadError && !isa<InitListExpr>(DIE->getInit()) &&
2587 !isa<StringLiteral>(DIE->getInit())) {
2588 // The initializer is not an initializer list.
2589 if (!VerifyOnly) {
2590 SemaRef.Diag(DIE->getInit()->getBeginLoc(),
2591 diag::err_flexible_array_init_needs_braces)
2592 << DIE->getInit()->getSourceRange();
2593 SemaRef.Diag(Field->getLocation(), diag::note_flexible_array_member)
2594 << *Field;
2595 }
2596 Invalid = true;
2597 }
2598
2599 // Check GNU flexible array initializer.
2600 if (!Invalid && CheckFlexibleArrayInit(Entity, DIE->getInit(), *Field,
2601 TopLevelObject))
2602 Invalid = true;
2603
2604 if (Invalid) {
2605 ++Index;
2606 return true;
2607 }
2608
2609 // Initialize the array.
2610 bool prevHadError = hadError;
2611 unsigned newStructuredIndex = FieldIndex;
2612 unsigned OldIndex = Index;
2613 IList->setInit(Index, DIE->getInit());
2614
2615 InitializedEntity MemberEntity =
2616 InitializedEntity::InitializeMember(*Field, &Entity);
2617 CheckSubElementType(MemberEntity, IList, Field->getType(), Index,
2618 StructuredList, newStructuredIndex);
2619
2620 IList->setInit(OldIndex, DIE);
2621 if (hadError && !prevHadError) {
2622 ++Field;
2623 ++FieldIndex;
2624 if (NextField)
2625 *NextField = Field;
2626 StructuredIndex = FieldIndex;
2627 return true;
2628 }
2629 } else {
2630 // Recurse to check later designated subobjects.
2631 QualType FieldType = Field->getType();
2632 unsigned newStructuredIndex = FieldIndex;
2633
2634 InitializedEntity MemberEntity =
2635 InitializedEntity::InitializeMember(*Field, &Entity);
2636 if (CheckDesignatedInitializer(MemberEntity, IList, DIE, DesigIdx + 1,
2637 FieldType, nullptr, nullptr, Index,
2638 StructuredList, newStructuredIndex,
2639 FinishSubobjectInit, false))
2640 return true;
2641 }
2642
2643 // Find the position of the next field to be initialized in this
2644 // subobject.
2645 ++Field;
2646 ++FieldIndex;
2647
2648 // If this the first designator, our caller will continue checking
2649 // the rest of this struct/class/union subobject.
2650 if (IsFirstDesignator) {
2651 if (NextField)
2652 *NextField = Field;
2653 StructuredIndex = FieldIndex;
2654 return false;
2655 }
2656
2657 if (!FinishSubobjectInit)
2658 return false;
2659
2660 // We've already initialized something in the union; we're done.
2661 if (RT->getDecl()->isUnion())
2662 return hadError;
2663
2664 // Check the remaining fields within this class/struct/union subobject.
2665 bool prevHadError = hadError;
2666
2667 auto NoBases =
2668 CXXRecordDecl::base_class_range(CXXRecordDecl::base_class_iterator(),
2669 CXXRecordDecl::base_class_iterator());
2670 CheckStructUnionTypes(Entity, IList, CurrentObjectType, NoBases, Field,
2671 false, Index, StructuredList, FieldIndex);
2672 return hadError && !prevHadError;
2673 }
2674
2675 // C99 6.7.8p6:
2676 //
2677 // If a designator has the form
2678 //
2679 // [ constant-expression ]
2680 //
2681 // then the current object (defined below) shall have array
2682 // type and the expression shall be an integer constant
2683 // expression. If the array is of unknown size, any
2684 // nonnegative value is valid.
2685 //
2686 // Additionally, cope with the GNU extension that permits
2687 // designators of the form
2688 //
2689 // [ constant-expression ... constant-expression ]
2690 const ArrayType *AT = SemaRef.Context.getAsArrayType(CurrentObjectType);
2691 if (!AT) {
2692 if (!VerifyOnly)
2693 SemaRef.Diag(D->getLBracketLoc(), diag::err_array_designator_non_array)
2694 << CurrentObjectType;
2695 ++Index;
2696 return true;
2697 }
2698
2699 Expr *IndexExpr = nullptr;
2700 llvm::APSInt DesignatedStartIndex, DesignatedEndIndex;
2701 if (D->isArrayDesignator()) {
2702 IndexExpr = DIE->getArrayIndex(*D);
2703 DesignatedStartIndex = IndexExpr->EvaluateKnownConstInt(SemaRef.Context);
2704 DesignatedEndIndex = DesignatedStartIndex;
2705 } else {
2706 assert(D->isArrayRangeDesignator() && "Need array-range designator");
2707
2708 DesignatedStartIndex =
2709 DIE->getArrayRangeStart(*D)->EvaluateKnownConstInt(SemaRef.Context);
2710 DesignatedEndIndex =
2711 DIE->getArrayRangeEnd(*D)->EvaluateKnownConstInt(SemaRef.Context);
2712 IndexExpr = DIE->getArrayRangeEnd(*D);
2713
2714 // Codegen can't handle evaluating array range designators that have side
2715 // effects, because we replicate the AST value for each initialized element.
2716 // As such, set the sawArrayRangeDesignator() bit if we initialize multiple
2717 // elements with something that has a side effect, so codegen can emit an
2718 // "error unsupported" error instead of miscompiling the app.
2719 if (DesignatedStartIndex.getZExtValue()!=DesignatedEndIndex.getZExtValue()&&
2720 DIE->getInit()->HasSideEffects(SemaRef.Context) && !VerifyOnly)
2721 FullyStructuredList->sawArrayRangeDesignator();
2722 }
2723
2724 if (isa<ConstantArrayType>(AT)) {
2725 llvm::APSInt MaxElements(cast<ConstantArrayType>(AT)->getSize(), false);
2726 DesignatedStartIndex
2727 = DesignatedStartIndex.extOrTrunc(MaxElements.getBitWidth());
2728 DesignatedStartIndex.setIsUnsigned(MaxElements.isUnsigned());
2729 DesignatedEndIndex
2730 = DesignatedEndIndex.extOrTrunc(MaxElements.getBitWidth());
2731 DesignatedEndIndex.setIsUnsigned(MaxElements.isUnsigned());
2732 if (DesignatedEndIndex >= MaxElements) {
2733 if (!VerifyOnly)
2734 SemaRef.Diag(IndexExpr->getBeginLoc(),
2735 diag::err_array_designator_too_large)
2736 << DesignatedEndIndex.toString(10) << MaxElements.toString(10)
2737 << IndexExpr->getSourceRange();
2738 ++Index;
2739 return true;
2740 }
2741 } else {
2742 unsigned DesignatedIndexBitWidth =
2743 ConstantArrayType::getMaxSizeBits(SemaRef.Context);
2744 DesignatedStartIndex =
2745 DesignatedStartIndex.extOrTrunc(DesignatedIndexBitWidth);
2746 DesignatedEndIndex =
2747 DesignatedEndIndex.extOrTrunc(DesignatedIndexBitWidth);
2748 DesignatedStartIndex.setIsUnsigned(true);
2749 DesignatedEndIndex.setIsUnsigned(true);
2750 }
2751
2752 if (!VerifyOnly && StructuredList->isStringLiteralInit()) {
2753 // We're modifying a string literal init; we have to decompose the string
2754 // so we can modify the individual characters.
2755 ASTContext &Context = SemaRef.Context;
2756 Expr *SubExpr = StructuredList->getInit(0)->IgnoreParens();
2757
2758 // Compute the character type
2759 QualType CharTy = AT->getElementType();
2760
2761 // Compute the type of the integer literals.
2762 QualType PromotedCharTy = CharTy;
2763 if (CharTy->isPromotableIntegerType())
2764 PromotedCharTy = Context.getPromotedIntegerType(CharTy);
2765 unsigned PromotedCharTyWidth = Context.getTypeSize(PromotedCharTy);
2766
2767 if (StringLiteral *SL = dyn_cast<StringLiteral>(SubExpr)) {
2768 // Get the length of the string.
2769 uint64_t StrLen = SL->getLength();
2770 if (cast<ConstantArrayType>(AT)->getSize().ult(StrLen))
2771 StrLen = cast<ConstantArrayType>(AT)->getSize().getZExtValue();
2772 StructuredList->resizeInits(Context, StrLen);
2773
2774 // Build a literal for each character in the string, and put them into
2775 // the init list.
2776 for (unsigned i = 0, e = StrLen; i != e; ++i) {
2777 llvm::APInt CodeUnit(PromotedCharTyWidth, SL->getCodeUnit(i));
2778 Expr *Init = new (Context) IntegerLiteral(
2779 Context, CodeUnit, PromotedCharTy, SubExpr->getExprLoc());
2780 if (CharTy != PromotedCharTy)
2781 Init = ImplicitCastExpr::Create(Context, CharTy, CK_IntegralCast,
2782 Init, nullptr, VK_RValue);
2783 StructuredList->updateInit(Context, i, Init);
2784 }
2785 } else {
2786 ObjCEncodeExpr *E = cast<ObjCEncodeExpr>(SubExpr);
2787 std::string Str;
2788 Context.getObjCEncodingForType(E->getEncodedType(), Str);
2789
2790 // Get the length of the string.
2791 uint64_t StrLen = Str.size();
2792 if (cast<ConstantArrayType>(AT)->getSize().ult(StrLen))
2793 StrLen = cast<ConstantArrayType>(AT)->getSize().getZExtValue();
2794 StructuredList->resizeInits(Context, StrLen);
2795
2796 // Build a literal for each character in the string, and put them into
2797 // the init list.
2798 for (unsigned i = 0, e = StrLen; i != e; ++i) {
2799 llvm::APInt CodeUnit(PromotedCharTyWidth, Str[i]);
2800 Expr *Init = new (Context) IntegerLiteral(
2801 Context, CodeUnit, PromotedCharTy, SubExpr->getExprLoc());
2802 if (CharTy != PromotedCharTy)
2803 Init = ImplicitCastExpr::Create(Context, CharTy, CK_IntegralCast,
2804 Init, nullptr, VK_RValue);
2805 StructuredList->updateInit(Context, i, Init);
2806 }
2807 }
2808 }
2809
2810 // Make sure that our non-designated initializer list has space
2811 // for a subobject corresponding to this array element.
2812 if (!VerifyOnly &&
2813 DesignatedEndIndex.getZExtValue() >= StructuredList->getNumInits())
2814 StructuredList->resizeInits(SemaRef.Context,
2815 DesignatedEndIndex.getZExtValue() + 1);
2816
2817 // Repeatedly perform subobject initializations in the range
2818 // [DesignatedStartIndex, DesignatedEndIndex].
2819
2820 // Move to the next designator
2821 unsigned ElementIndex = DesignatedStartIndex.getZExtValue();
2822 unsigned OldIndex = Index;
2823
2824 InitializedEntity ElementEntity =
2825 InitializedEntity::InitializeElement(SemaRef.Context, 0, Entity);
2826
2827 while (DesignatedStartIndex <= DesignatedEndIndex) {
2828 // Recurse to check later designated subobjects.
2829 QualType ElementType = AT->getElementType();
2830 Index = OldIndex;
2831
2832 ElementEntity.setElementIndex(ElementIndex);
2833 if (CheckDesignatedInitializer(
2834 ElementEntity, IList, DIE, DesigIdx + 1, ElementType, nullptr,
2835 nullptr, Index, StructuredList, ElementIndex,
2836 FinishSubobjectInit && (DesignatedStartIndex == DesignatedEndIndex),
2837 false))
2838 return true;
2839
2840 // Move to the next index in the array that we'll be initializing.
2841 ++DesignatedStartIndex;
2842 ElementIndex = DesignatedStartIndex.getZExtValue();
2843 }
2844
2845 // If this the first designator, our caller will continue checking
2846 // the rest of this array subobject.
2847 if (IsFirstDesignator) {
2848 if (NextElementIndex)
2849 *NextElementIndex = DesignatedStartIndex;
2850 StructuredIndex = ElementIndex;
2851 return false;
2852 }
2853
2854 if (!FinishSubobjectInit)
2855 return false;
2856
2857 // Check the remaining elements within this array subobject.
2858 bool prevHadError = hadError;
2859 CheckArrayType(Entity, IList, CurrentObjectType, DesignatedStartIndex,
2860 /*SubobjectIsDesignatorContext=*/false, Index,
2861 StructuredList, ElementIndex);
2862 return hadError && !prevHadError;
2863}
2864
2865// Get the structured initializer list for a subobject of type
2866// @p CurrentObjectType.
2867InitListExpr *
2868InitListChecker::getStructuredSubobjectInit(InitListExpr *IList, unsigned Index,
2869 QualType CurrentObjectType,
2870 InitListExpr *StructuredList,
2871 unsigned StructuredIndex,
2872 SourceRange InitRange,
2873 bool IsFullyOverwritten) {
2874 if (VerifyOnly)
2875 return nullptr; // No structured list in verification-only mode.
2876 Expr *ExistingInit = nullptr;
2877 if (!StructuredList)
2878 ExistingInit = SyntacticToSemantic.lookup(IList);
2879 else if (StructuredIndex < StructuredList->getNumInits())
2880 ExistingInit = StructuredList->getInit(StructuredIndex);
2881
2882 if (InitListExpr *Result = dyn_cast_or_null<InitListExpr>(ExistingInit))
2883 // There might have already been initializers for subobjects of the current
2884 // object, but a subsequent initializer list will overwrite the entirety
2885 // of the current object. (See DR 253 and C99 6.7.8p21). e.g.,
2886 //
2887 // struct P { char x[6]; };
2888 // struct P l = { .x[2] = 'x', .x = { [0] = 'f' } };
2889 //
2890 // The first designated initializer is ignored, and l.x is just "f".
2891 if (!IsFullyOverwritten)
2892 return Result;
2893
2894 if (ExistingInit) {
2895 // We are creating an initializer list that initializes the
2896 // subobjects of the current object, but there was already an
2897 // initialization that completely initialized the current
2898 // subobject, e.g., by a compound literal:
2899 //
2900 // struct X { int a, b; };
2901 // struct X xs[] = { [0] = (struct X) { 1, 2 }, [0].b = 3 };
2902 //
2903 // Here, xs[0].a == 0 and xs[0].b == 3, since the second,
2904 // designated initializer re-initializes the whole
2905 // subobject [0], overwriting previous initializers.
2906 SemaRef.Diag(InitRange.getBegin(),
2907 diag::warn_subobject_initializer_overrides)
2908 << InitRange;
2909 SemaRef.Diag(ExistingInit->getBeginLoc(), diag::note_previous_initializer)
2910 << /*FIXME:has side effects=*/0 << ExistingInit->getSourceRange();
2911 }
2912
2913 InitListExpr *Result
2914 = new (SemaRef.Context) InitListExpr(SemaRef.Context,
2915 InitRange.getBegin(), None,
2916 InitRange.getEnd());
2917
2918 QualType ResultType = CurrentObjectType;
2919 if (!ResultType->isArrayType())
2920 ResultType = ResultType.getNonLValueExprType(SemaRef.Context);
2921 Result->setType(ResultType);
2922
2923 // Pre-allocate storage for the structured initializer list.
2924 unsigned NumElements = 0;
2925 unsigned NumInits = 0;
2926 bool GotNumInits = false;
2927 if (!StructuredList) {
2928 NumInits = IList->getNumInits();
2929 GotNumInits = true;
2930 } else if (Index < IList->getNumInits()) {
2931 if (InitListExpr *SubList = dyn_cast<InitListExpr>(IList->getInit(Index))) {
2932 NumInits = SubList->getNumInits();
2933 GotNumInits = true;
2934 }
2935 }
2936
2937 if (const ArrayType *AType
2938 = SemaRef.Context.getAsArrayType(CurrentObjectType)) {
2939 if (const ConstantArrayType *CAType = dyn_cast<ConstantArrayType>(AType)) {
2940 NumElements = CAType->getSize().getZExtValue();
2941 // Simple heuristic so that we don't allocate a very large
2942 // initializer with many empty entries at the end.
2943 if (GotNumInits && NumElements > NumInits)
2944 NumElements = 0;
2945 }
2946 } else if (const VectorType *VType = CurrentObjectType->getAs<VectorType>())
2947 NumElements = VType->getNumElements();
2948 else if (const RecordType *RType = CurrentObjectType->getAs<RecordType>()) {
2949 RecordDecl *RDecl = RType->getDecl();
2950 if (RDecl->isUnion())
2951 NumElements = 1;
2952 else
2953 NumElements = std::distance(RDecl->field_begin(), RDecl->field_end());
2954 }
2955
2956 Result->reserveInits(SemaRef.Context, NumElements);
2957
2958 // Link this new initializer list into the structured initializer
2959 // lists.
2960 if (StructuredList)
2961 StructuredList->updateInit(SemaRef.Context, StructuredIndex, Result);
2962 else {
2963 Result->setSyntacticForm(IList);
2964 SyntacticToSemantic[IList] = Result;
2965 }
2966
2967 return Result;
2968}
2969
2970/// Update the initializer at index @p StructuredIndex within the
2971/// structured initializer list to the value @p expr.
2972void InitListChecker::UpdateStructuredListElement(InitListExpr *StructuredList,
2973 unsigned &StructuredIndex,
2974 Expr *expr) {
2975 // No structured initializer list to update
2976 if (!StructuredList)
2977 return;
2978
2979 if (Expr *PrevInit = StructuredList->updateInit(SemaRef.Context,
2980 StructuredIndex, expr)) {
2981 // This initializer overwrites a previous initializer. Warn.
2982 // We need to check on source range validity because the previous
2983 // initializer does not have to be an explicit initializer.
2984 // struct P { int a, b; };
2985 // struct PP { struct P p } l = { { .a = 2 }, .p.b = 3 };
2986 // There is an overwrite taking place because the first braced initializer
2987 // list "{ .a = 2 }' already provides value for .p.b (which is zero).
2988 if (PrevInit->getSourceRange().isValid()) {
2989 SemaRef.Diag(expr->getBeginLoc(), diag::warn_initializer_overrides)
2990 << expr->getSourceRange();
2991
2992 SemaRef.Diag(PrevInit->getBeginLoc(), diag::note_previous_initializer)
2993 << /*FIXME:has side effects=*/0 << PrevInit->getSourceRange();
2994 }
2995 }
2996
2997 ++StructuredIndex;
2998}
2999
3000/// Check that the given Index expression is a valid array designator
3001/// value. This is essentially just a wrapper around
3002/// VerifyIntegerConstantExpression that also checks for negative values
3003/// and produces a reasonable diagnostic if there is a
3004/// failure. Returns the index expression, possibly with an implicit cast
3005/// added, on success. If everything went okay, Value will receive the
3006/// value of the constant expression.
3007static ExprResult
3008CheckArrayDesignatorExpr(Sema &S, Expr *Index, llvm::APSInt &Value) {
3009 SourceLocation Loc = Index->getBeginLoc();
3010
3011 // Make sure this is an integer constant expression.
3012 ExprResult Result = S.VerifyIntegerConstantExpression(Index, &Value);
3013 if (Result.isInvalid())
3014 return Result;
3015
3016 if (Value.isSigned() && Value.isNegative())
3017 return S.Diag(Loc, diag::err_array_designator_negative)
3018 << Value.toString(10) << Index->getSourceRange();
3019
3020 Value.setIsUnsigned(true);
3021 return Result;
3022}
3023
3024ExprResult Sema::ActOnDesignatedInitializer(Designation &Desig,
3025 SourceLocation Loc,
3026 bool GNUSyntax,
3027 ExprResult Init) {
3028 typedef DesignatedInitExpr::Designator ASTDesignator;
3029
3030 bool Invalid = false;
3031 SmallVector<ASTDesignator, 32> Designators;
3032 SmallVector<Expr *, 32> InitExpressions;
3033
3034 // Build designators and check array designator expressions.
3035 for (unsigned Idx = 0; Idx < Desig.getNumDesignators(); ++Idx) {
3036 const Designator &D = Desig.getDesignator(Idx);
3037 switch (D.getKind()) {
3038 case Designator::FieldDesignator:
3039 Designators.push_back(ASTDesignator(D.getField(), D.getDotLoc(),
3040 D.getFieldLoc()));
3041 break;
3042
3043 case Designator::ArrayDesignator: {
3044 Expr *Index = static_cast<Expr *>(D.getArrayIndex());
3045 llvm::APSInt IndexValue;
3046 if (!Index->isTypeDependent() && !Index->isValueDependent())
3047 Index = CheckArrayDesignatorExpr(*this, Index, IndexValue).get();
3048 if (!Index)
3049 Invalid = true;
3050 else {
3051 Designators.push_back(ASTDesignator(InitExpressions.size(),
3052 D.getLBracketLoc(),
3053 D.getRBracketLoc()));
3054 InitExpressions.push_back(Index);
3055 }
3056 break;
3057 }
3058
3059 case Designator::ArrayRangeDesignator: {
3060 Expr *StartIndex = static_cast<Expr *>(D.getArrayRangeStart());
3061 Expr *EndIndex = static_cast<Expr *>(D.getArrayRangeEnd());
3062 llvm::APSInt StartValue;
3063 llvm::APSInt EndValue;
3064 bool StartDependent = StartIndex->isTypeDependent() ||
3065 StartIndex->isValueDependent();
3066 bool EndDependent = EndIndex->isTypeDependent() ||
3067 EndIndex->isValueDependent();
3068 if (!StartDependent)
3069 StartIndex =
3070 CheckArrayDesignatorExpr(*this, StartIndex, StartValue).get();
3071 if (!EndDependent)
3072 EndIndex = CheckArrayDesignatorExpr(*this, EndIndex, EndValue).get();
3073
3074 if (!StartIndex || !EndIndex)
3075 Invalid = true;
3076 else {
3077 // Make sure we're comparing values with the same bit width.
3078 if (StartDependent || EndDependent) {
3079 // Nothing to compute.
3080 } else if (StartValue.getBitWidth() > EndValue.getBitWidth())
3081 EndValue = EndValue.extend(StartValue.getBitWidth());
3082 else if (StartValue.getBitWidth() < EndValue.getBitWidth())
3083 StartValue = StartValue.extend(EndValue.getBitWidth());
3084
3085 if (!StartDependent && !EndDependent && EndValue < StartValue) {
3086 Diag(D.getEllipsisLoc(), diag::err_array_designator_empty_range)
3087 << StartValue.toString(10) << EndValue.toString(10)
3088 << StartIndex->getSourceRange() << EndIndex->getSourceRange();
3089 Invalid = true;
3090 } else {
3091 Designators.push_back(ASTDesignator(InitExpressions.size(),
3092 D.getLBracketLoc(),
3093 D.getEllipsisLoc(),
3094 D.getRBracketLoc()));
3095 InitExpressions.push_back(StartIndex);
3096 InitExpressions.push_back(EndIndex);
3097 }
3098 }
3099 break;
3100 }
3101 }
3102 }
3103
3104 if (Invalid || Init.isInvalid())
3105 return ExprError();
3106
3107 // Clear out the expressions within the designation.
3108 Desig.ClearExprs(*this);
3109
3110 DesignatedInitExpr *DIE
3111 = DesignatedInitExpr::Create(Context,
3112 Designators,
3113 InitExpressions, Loc, GNUSyntax,
3114 Init.getAs<Expr>());
3115
3116 if (!getLangOpts().C99)
3117 Diag(DIE->getBeginLoc(), diag::ext_designated_init)
3118 << DIE->getSourceRange();
3119
3120 return DIE;
3121}
3122
3123//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
3124// Initialization entity
3125//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
3126
3127InitializedEntity::InitializedEntity(ASTContext &Context, unsigned Index,
3128 const InitializedEntity &Parent)
3129 : Parent(&Parent), Index(Index)
3130{
3131 if (const ArrayType *AT = Context.getAsArrayType(Parent.getType())) {
3132 Kind = EK_ArrayElement;
3133 Type = AT->getElementType();
3134 } else if (const VectorType *VT = Parent.getType()->getAs<VectorType>()) {
3135 Kind = EK_VectorElement;
3136 Type = VT->getElementType();
3137 } else {
3138 const ComplexType *CT = Parent.getType()->getAs<ComplexType>();
3139 assert(CT && "Unexpected type");
3140 Kind = EK_ComplexElement;
3141 Type = CT->getElementType();
3142 }
3143}
3144
3145InitializedEntity
3146InitializedEntity::InitializeBase(ASTContext &Context,
3147 const CXXBaseSpecifier *Base,
3148 bool IsInheritedVirtualBase,
3149 const InitializedEntity *Parent) {
3150 InitializedEntity Result;
3151 Result.Kind = EK_Base;
3152 Result.Parent = Parent;
3153 Result.Base = reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(Base);
3154 if (IsInheritedVirtualBase)
3155 Result.Base |= 0x01;
3156
3157 Result.Type = Base->getType();
3158 return Result;
3159}
3160
3161DeclarationName InitializedEntity::getName() const {
3162 switch (getKind()) {
3163 case EK_Parameter:
3164 case EK_Parameter_CF_Audited: {
3165 ParmVarDecl *D = reinterpret_cast<ParmVarDecl*>(Parameter & ~0x1);
3166 return (D ? D->getDeclName() : DeclarationName());
3167 }
3168
3169 case EK_Variable:
3170 case EK_Member:
3171 case EK_Binding:
3172 return Variable.VariableOrMember->getDeclName();
3173
3174 case EK_LambdaCapture:
3175 return DeclarationName(Capture.VarID);
3176
3177 case EK_Result:
3178 case EK_StmtExprResult:
3179 case EK_Exception:
3180 case EK_New:
3181 case EK_Temporary:
3182 case EK_Base:
3183 case EK_Delegating:
3184 case EK_ArrayElement:
3185 case EK_VectorElement:
3186 case EK_ComplexElement:
3187 case EK_BlockElement:
3188 case EK_LambdaToBlockConversionBlockElement:
3189 case EK_CompoundLiteralInit:
3190 case EK_RelatedResult:
3191 return DeclarationName();
3192 }
3193
3194 llvm_unreachable("Invalid EntityKind!");
3195}
3196
3197ValueDecl *InitializedEntity::getDecl() const {
3198 switch (getKind()) {
3199 case EK_Variable:
3200 case EK_Member:
3201 case EK_Binding:
3202 return Variable.VariableOrMember;
3203
3204 case EK_Parameter:
3205 case EK_Parameter_CF_Audited:
3206 return reinterpret_cast<ParmVarDecl*>(Parameter & ~0x1);
3207
3208 case EK_Result:
3209 case EK_StmtExprResult:
3210 case EK_Exception:
3211 case EK_New:
3212 case EK_Temporary:
3213 case EK_Base:
3214 case EK_Delegating:
3215 case EK_ArrayElement:
3216 case EK_VectorElement:
3217 case EK_ComplexElement:
3218 case EK_BlockElement:
3219 case EK_LambdaToBlockConversionBlockElement:
3220 case EK_LambdaCapture:
3221 case EK_CompoundLiteralInit:
3222 case EK_RelatedResult:
3223 return nullptr;
3224 }
3225
3226 llvm_unreachable("Invalid EntityKind!");
3227}
3228
3229bool InitializedEntity::allowsNRVO() const {
3230 switch (getKind()) {
3231 case EK_Result:
3232 case EK_Exception:
3233 return LocAndNRVO.NRVO;
3234
3235 case EK_StmtExprResult:
3236 case EK_Variable:
3237 case EK_Parameter:
3238 case EK_Parameter_CF_Audited:
3239 case EK_Member:
3240 case EK_Binding:
3241 case EK_New:
3242 case EK_Temporary:
3243 case EK_CompoundLiteralInit:
3244 case EK_Base:
3245 case EK_Delegating:
3246 case EK_ArrayElement:
3247 case EK_VectorElement:
3248 case EK_ComplexElement:
3249 case EK_BlockElement:
3250 case EK_LambdaToBlockConversionBlockElement:
3251 case EK_LambdaCapture:
3252 case EK_RelatedResult:
3253 break;
3254 }
3255
3256 return false;
3257}
3258
3259unsigned InitializedEntity::dumpImpl(raw_ostream &OS) const {
3260 assert(getParent() != this);
3261 unsigned Depth = getParent() ? getParent()->dumpImpl(OS) : 0;
3262 for (unsigned I = 0; I != Depth; ++I)
3263 OS << "`-";
3264
3265 switch (getKind()) {
3266 case EK_Variable: OS << "Variable"; break;
3267 case EK_Parameter: OS << "Parameter"; break;
3268 case EK_Parameter_CF_Audited: OS << "CF audited function Parameter";
3269 break;
3270 case EK_Result: OS << "Result"; break;
3271 case EK_StmtExprResult: OS << "StmtExprResult"; break;
3272 case EK_Exception: OS << "Exception"; break;
3273 case EK_Member: OS << "Member"; break;
3274 case EK_Binding: OS << "Binding"; break;
3275 case EK_New: OS << "New"; break;
3276 case EK_Temporary: OS << "Temporary"; break;
3277 case EK_CompoundLiteralInit: OS << "CompoundLiteral";break;
3278 case EK_RelatedResult: OS << "RelatedResult"; break;
3279 case EK_Base: OS << "Base"; break;
3280 case EK_Delegating: OS << "Delegating"; break;
3281 case EK_ArrayElement: OS << "ArrayElement " << Index; break;
3282 case EK_VectorElement: OS << "VectorElement " << Index; break;
3283 case EK_ComplexElement: OS << "ComplexElement " << Index; break;
3284 case EK_BlockElement: OS << "Block"; break;
3285 case EK_LambdaToBlockConversionBlockElement:
3286 OS << "Block (lambda)";
3287 break;
3288 case EK_LambdaCapture:
3289 OS << "LambdaCapture ";
3290 OS << DeclarationName(Capture.VarID);
3291 break;
3292 }
3293
3294 if (auto *D = getDecl()) {
3295 OS << " ";
3296 D->printQualifiedName(OS);
3297 }
3298
3299 OS << " '" << getType().getAsString() << "'\n";
3300
3301 return Depth + 1;
3302}
3303
3304LLVM_DUMP_METHOD void InitializedEntity::dump() const {
3305 dumpImpl(llvm::errs());
3306}

3312void InitializationSequence::Step::Destroy() {
3313 switch (Kind) {
3314 case SK_ResolveAddressOfOverloadedFunction:
3315 case SK_CastDerivedToBaseRValue:
3316 case SK_CastDerivedToBaseXValue:
3317 case SK_CastDerivedToBaseLValue:
3318 case SK_BindReference:
3319 case SK_BindReferenceToTemporary:
3320 case SK_FinalCopy:
3321 case SK_ExtraneousCopyToTemporary:
3322 case SK_UserConversion:
3323 case SK_QualificationConversionRValue:
3324 case SK_QualificationConversionXValue:
3325 case SK_QualificationConversionLValue:
3326 case SK_AtomicConversion:
3327 case SK_LValueToRValue:
3328 case SK_ListInitialization:
3329 case SK_UnwrapInitList:
3330 case SK_RewrapInitList:
3331 case SK_ConstructorInitialization:
3332 case SK_ConstructorInitializationFromList:
3333 case SK_ZeroInitialization:
3334 case SK_CAssignment:
3335 case SK_StringInit:
3336 case SK_ObjCObjectConversion:
3337 case SK_ArrayLoopIndex:
3338 case SK_ArrayLoopInit:
3339 case SK_ArrayInit:
3340 case SK_GNUArrayInit:
3341 case SK_ParenthesizedArrayInit:
3342 case SK_PassByIndirectCopyRestore:
3343 case SK_PassByIndirectRestore:
3344 case SK_ProduceObjCObject:
3345 case SK_StdInitializerList:
3346 case SK_StdInitializerListConstructorCall:
3347 case SK_OCLSamplerInit:
3348 case SK_OCLZeroOpaqueType:
3349 break;
3350
3351 case SK_ConversionSequence:
3352 case SK_ConversionSequenceNoNarrowing:
3353 delete ICS;
3354 }
3355}
3356
3357bool InitializationSequence::isDirectReferenceBinding() const {
3358 // There can be some lvalue adjustments after the SK_BindReference step.
3359 for (auto I = Steps.rbegin(); I != Steps.rend(); ++I) {
3360 if (I->Kind == SK_BindReference)
3361 return true;
3362 if (I->Kind == SK_BindReferenceToTemporary)
3363 return false;
3364 }
3365 return false;
3366}
3367
3368bool InitializationSequence::isAmbiguous() const {
3369 if (!Failed())
3370 return false;
3371
3372 switch (getFailureKind()) {
3373 case FK_TooManyInitsForReference:
3374 case FK_ParenthesizedListInitForReference:
3375 case FK_ArrayNeedsInitList:
3376 case FK_ArrayNeedsInitListOrStringLiteral:
3377 case FK_ArrayNeedsInitListOrWideStringLiteral:
3378 case FK_NarrowStringIntoWideCharArray:
3379 case FK_WideStringIntoCharArray:
3380 case FK_IncompatWideStringIntoWideChar:
3381 case FK_PlainStringIntoUTF8Char:
3382 case FK_UTF8StringIntoPlainChar:
3383 case FK_AddressOfOverloadFailed: // FIXME: Could do better
3384 case FK_NonConstLValueReferenceBindingToTemporary:
3385 case FK_NonConstLValueReferenceBindingToBitfield:
3386 case FK_NonConstLValueReferenceBindingToVectorElement:
3387 case FK_NonConstLValueReferenceBindingToUnrelated:
3388 case FK_RValueReferenceBindingToLValue:
3389 case FK_ReferenceAddrspaceMismatchTemporary:
3390 case FK_ReferenceInitDropsQualifiers:
3391 case FK_ReferenceInitFailed:
3392 case FK_ConversionFailed:
3393 case FK_ConversionFromCapabilityFailed:
3394 case FK_ConversionToCapabilityFailed:
3395 case FK_ReferenceInitChangesCapabilityQualifier:
3396 case FK_ConversionFromPropertyFailed:
3397 case FK_TooManyInitsForScalar:
3398 case FK_ParenthesizedListInitForScalar:
3399 case FK_ReferenceBindingToInitList:
3400 case FK_InitListBadDestinationType:
3401 case FK_DefaultInitOfConst:
3402 case FK_Incomplete:
3403 case FK_ArrayTypeMismatch:
3404 case FK_NonConstantArrayInit:
3405 case FK_ListInitializationFailed:
3406 case FK_VariableLengthArrayHasInitializer:
3407 case FK_PlaceholderType:
3408 case FK_ExplicitConstructor:
3409 case FK_AddressOfUnaddressableFunction:
3410 return false;
3411
3412 case FK_ReferenceInitOverloadFailed:
3413 case FK_UserConversionOverloadFailed:
3414 case FK_ConstructorOverloadFailed:
3415 case FK_ListConstructorOverloadFailed:
3416 return FailedOverloadResult == OR_Ambiguous;
3417 }
3418
3419 llvm_unreachable("Invalid EntityKind!");
3420}

3667//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
3668// Attempt initialization
3669//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
3670
3671/// Tries to add a zero initializer. Returns true if that worked.
3672static bool
3673maybeRecoverWithZeroInitialization(Sema &S, InitializationSequence &Sequence,
3674 const InitializedEntity &Entity) {
3675 if (Entity.getKind() != InitializedEntity::EK_Variable)
3676 return false;
3677
3678 VarDecl *VD = cast<VarDecl>(Entity.getDecl());
3679 if (VD->getInit() || VD->getEndLoc().isMacroID())
3680 return false;
3681
3682 QualType VariableTy = VD->getType().getCanonicalType();
3683 SourceLocation Loc = S.getLocForEndOfToken(VD->getEndLoc());
3684 std::string Init = S.getFixItZeroInitializerForType(VariableTy, Loc);
3685 if (!Init.empty()) {
3686 Sequence.AddZeroInitializationStep(Entity.getType());
3687 Sequence.SetZeroInitializationFixit(Init, Loc);
3688 return true;
3689 }
3690 return false;
3691}
3692
3693static void MaybeProduceObjCObject(Sema &S,
3694 InitializationSequence &Sequence,
3695 const InitializedEntity &Entity) {
3696 if (!S.getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount) return;
3697
3698 /// When initializing a parameter, produce the value if it's marked
3699 /// __attribute__((ns_consumed)).
3700 if (Entity.isParameterKind()) {
3701 if (!Entity.isParameterConsumed())
3702 return;
3703
3704 assert(Entity.getType()->isObjCRetainableType() &&
3705 "consuming an object of unretainable type?");
3706 Sequence.AddProduceObjCObjectStep(Entity.getType());
3707
3708 /// When initializing a return value, if the return type is a
3709 /// retainable type, then returns need to immediately retain the
3710 /// object. If an autorelease is required, it will be done at the
3711 /// last instant.
3712 } else if (Entity.getKind() == InitializedEntity::EK_Result ||
3713 Entity.getKind() == InitializedEntity::EK_StmtExprResult) {
3714 if (!Entity.getType()->isObjCRetainableType())
3715 return;
3716
3717 Sequence.AddProduceObjCObjectStep(Entity.getType());
3718 }
3719}
3720
3721static void TryListInitialization(Sema &S,
3722 const InitializedEntity &Entity,
3723 const InitializationKind &Kind,
3724 InitListExpr *InitList,
3725 InitializationSequence &Sequence,
3726 bool TreatUnavailableAsInvalid);
3727
3728/// When initializing from init list via constructor, handle
3729/// initialization of an object of type std::initializer_list<T>.
3730///
3731/// \return true if we have handled initialization of an object of type
3732/// std::initializer_list<T>, false otherwise.
3733static bool TryInitializerListConstruction(Sema &S,
3734 InitListExpr *List,
3735 QualType DestType,
3736 InitializationSequence &Sequence,
3737 bool TreatUnavailableAsInvalid) {
3738 QualType E;
3739 if (!S.isStdInitializerList(DestType, &E))
3740 return false;
3741
3742 if (!S.isCompleteType(List->getExprLoc(), E)) {
3743 Sequence.setIncompleteTypeFailure(E);
3744 return true;
3745 }
3746
3747 // Try initializing a temporary array from the init list.
3748 QualType ArrayType = S.Context.getConstantArrayType(
3749 E.withConst(), llvm::APInt(S.Context.getTypeSize(S.Context.getSizeType()),
3750 List->getNumInits()),
3751 clang::ArrayType::Normal, 0);
3752 InitializedEntity HiddenArray =
3753 InitializedEntity::InitializeTemporary(ArrayType);
3754 InitializationKind Kind = InitializationKind::CreateDirectList(
3755 List->getExprLoc(), List->getBeginLoc(), List->getEndLoc());
3756 TryListInitialization(S, HiddenArray, Kind, List, Sequence,
3757 TreatUnavailableAsInvalid);
3758 if (Sequence)
3759 Sequence.AddStdInitializerListConstructionStep(DestType);
3760 return true;
3761}
3762
3763/// Determine if the constructor has the signature of a copy or move
3764/// constructor for the type T of the class in which it was found. That is,
3765/// determine if its first parameter is of type T or reference to (possibly
3766/// cv-qualified) T.
3767static bool hasCopyOrMoveCtorParam(ASTContext &Ctx,
3768 const ConstructorInfo &Info) {
3769 if (Info.Constructor->getNumParams() == 0)
3770 return false;
3771
3772 QualType ParmT =
3773 Info.Constructor->getParamDecl(0)->getType().getNonReferenceType();
3774 QualType ClassT =
3775 Ctx.getRecordType(cast<CXXRecordDecl>(Info.FoundDecl->getDeclContext()));
3776
3777 return Ctx.hasSameUnqualifiedType(ParmT, ClassT);
3778}
3779
3780static OverloadingResult
3781ResolveConstructorOverload(Sema &S, SourceLocation DeclLoc,
3782 MultiExprArg Args,
3783 OverloadCandidateSet &CandidateSet,
3784 QualType DestType,
3785 DeclContext::lookup_result Ctors,
3786 OverloadCandidateSet::iterator &Best,
3787 bool CopyInitializing, bool AllowExplicit,
3788 bool OnlyListConstructors, bool IsListInit,
3789 bool SecondStepOfCopyInit = false) {
3790 CandidateSet.clear(OverloadCandidateSet::CSK_InitByConstructor);
3791
3792 for (NamedDecl *D : Ctors) {
3793 auto Info = getConstructorInfo(D);
3794 if (!Info.Constructor || Info.Constructor->isInvalidDecl())
3795 continue;
3796
3797 if (!AllowExplicit && Info.Constructor->isExplicit())
3798 continue;
3799
3800 if (OnlyListConstructors && !S.isInitListConstructor(Info.Constructor))
3801 continue;
3802
3803 // C++11 [over.best.ics]p4:
3804 // ... and the constructor or user-defined conversion function is a
3805 // candidate by
3806 // - 13.3.1.3, when the argument is the temporary in the second step
3807 // of a class copy-initialization, or
3808 // - 13.3.1.4, 13.3.1.5, or 13.3.1.6 (in all cases), [not handled here]
3809 // - the second phase of 13.3.1.7 when the initializer list has exactly
3810 // one element that is itself an initializer list, and the target is
3811 // the first parameter of a constructor of class X, and the conversion
3812 // is to X or reference to (possibly cv-qualified X),
3813 // user-defined conversion sequences are not considered.
3814 bool SuppressUserConversions =
3815 SecondStepOfCopyInit ||
3816 (IsListInit && Args.size() == 1 && isa<InitListExpr>(Args[0]) &&
3817 hasCopyOrMoveCtorParam(S.Context, Info));
3818
3819 if (Info.ConstructorTmpl)
3820 S.AddTemplateOverloadCandidate(
3821 Info.ConstructorTmpl, Info.FoundDecl,
3822 /*ExplicitArgs*/ nullptr, Args, CandidateSet, SuppressUserConversions,
3823 /*PartialOverloading=*/false, AllowExplicit);
3824 else {
3825 // C++ [over.match.copy]p1:
3826 // - When initializing a temporary to be bound to the first parameter
3827 // of a constructor [for type T] that takes a reference to possibly
3828 // cv-qualified T as its first argument, called with a single
3829 // argument in the context of direct-initialization, explicit
3830 // conversion functions are also considered.
3831 // FIXME: What if a constructor template instantiates to such a signature?
3832 bool AllowExplicitConv = AllowExplicit && !CopyInitializing &&
3833 Args.size() == 1 &&
3834 hasCopyOrMoveCtorParam(S.Context, Info);
3835 S.AddOverloadCandidate(Info.Constructor, Info.FoundDecl, Args,
3836 CandidateSet, SuppressUserConversions,
3837 /*PartialOverloading=*/false, AllowExplicit,
3838 AllowExplicitConv);
3839 }
3840 }
3841
3842 // FIXME: Work around a bug in C++17 guaranteed copy elision.
3843 //
3844 // When initializing an object of class type T by constructor
3845 // ([over.match.ctor]) or by list-initialization ([over.match.list])
3846 // from a single expression of class type U, conversion functions of
3847 // U that convert to the non-reference type cv T are candidates.
3848 // Explicit conversion functions are only candidates during
3849 // direct-initialization.
3850 //
3851 // Note: SecondStepOfCopyInit is only ever true in this case when
3852 // evaluating whether to produce a C++98 compatibility warning.
3853 if (S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus17 && Args.size() == 1 &&
3854 !SecondStepOfCopyInit) {
3855 Expr *Initializer = Args[0];
3856 auto *SourceRD = Initializer->getType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
3857 if (SourceRD && S.isCompleteType(DeclLoc, Initializer->getType())) {
3858 const auto &Conversions = SourceRD->getVisibleConversionFunctions();
3859 for (auto I = Conversions.begin(), E = Conversions.end(); I != E; ++I) {
3860 NamedDecl *D = *I;
3861 CXXRecordDecl *ActingDC = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(D->getDeclContext());
3862 D = D->getUnderlyingDecl();
3863
3864 FunctionTemplateDecl *ConvTemplate = dyn_cast<FunctionTemplateDecl>(D);
3865 CXXConversionDecl *Conv;
3866 if (ConvTemplate)
3867 Conv = cast<CXXConversionDecl>(ConvTemplate->getTemplatedDecl());
3868 else
3869 Conv = cast<CXXConversionDecl>(D);
3870
3871 if (AllowExplicit || !Conv->isExplicit()) {
3872 if (ConvTemplate)
3873 S.AddTemplateConversionCandidate(
3874 ConvTemplate, I.getPair(), ActingDC, Initializer, DestType,
3875 CandidateSet, AllowExplicit, AllowExplicit,
3876 /*AllowResultConversion*/ false);
3877 else
3878 S.AddConversionCandidate(Conv, I.getPair(), ActingDC, Initializer,
3879 DestType, CandidateSet, AllowExplicit,
3880 AllowExplicit,
3881 /*AllowResultConversion*/ false);
3882 }
3883 }
3884 }
3885 }
3886
3887 // Perform overload resolution and return the result.
3888 return CandidateSet.BestViableFunction(S, DeclLoc, Best);
3889}
3890
3891/// Attempt initialization by constructor (C++ [dcl.init]), which
3892/// enumerates the constructors of the initialized entity and performs overload
3893/// resolution to select the best.
3894/// \param DestType The destination class type.
3895/// \param DestArrayType The destination type, which is either DestType or
3896/// a (possibly multidimensional) array of DestType.
3897/// \param IsListInit Is this list-initialization?
3898/// \param IsInitListCopy Is this non-list-initialization resulting from a
3899/// list-initialization from {x} where x is the same
3900/// type as the entity?
3901static void TryConstructorInitialization(Sema &S,
3902 const InitializedEntity &Entity,
3903 const InitializationKind &Kind,
3904 MultiExprArg Args, QualType DestType,
3905 QualType DestArrayType,
3906 InitializationSequence &Sequence,
3907 bool IsListInit = false,
3908 bool IsInitListCopy = false) {
3909 assert(((!IsListInit && !IsInitListCopy) ||
3910 (Args.size() == 1 && isa<InitListExpr>(Args[0]))) &&
3911 "IsListInit/IsInitListCopy must come with a single initializer list "
3912 "argument.");
3913 InitListExpr *ILE =
3914 (IsListInit || IsInitListCopy) ? cast<InitListExpr>(Args[0]) : nullptr;
3915 MultiExprArg UnwrappedArgs =
3916 ILE ? MultiExprArg(ILE->getInits(), ILE->getNumInits()) : Args;
3917
3918 // The type we're constructing needs to be complete.
3919 if (!S.isCompleteType(Kind.getLocation(), DestType)) {
3920 Sequence.setIncompleteTypeFailure(DestType);
3921 return;
3922 }
3923
3924 // C++17 [dcl.init]p17:
3925 // - If the initializer expression is a prvalue and the cv-unqualified
3926 // version of the source type is the same class as the class of the
3927 // destination, the initializer expression is used to initialize the
3928 // destination object.
3929 // Per DR (no number yet), this does not apply when initializing a base
3930 // class or delegating to another constructor from a mem-initializer.
3931 // ObjC++: Lambda captured by the block in the lambda to block conversion
3932 // should avoid copy elision.
3933 if (S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus17 &&
3934 Entity.getKind() != InitializedEntity::EK_Base &&
3935 Entity.getKind() != InitializedEntity::EK_Delegating &&
3936 Entity.getKind() !=
3937 InitializedEntity::EK_LambdaToBlockConversionBlockElement &&
3938 UnwrappedArgs.size() == 1 && UnwrappedArgs[0]->isRValue() &&
3939 S.Context.hasSameUnqualifiedType(UnwrappedArgs[0]->getType(), DestType)) {
3940 // Convert qualifications if necessary.
3941 Sequence.AddQualificationConversionStep(DestType, VK_RValue);
3942 if (ILE)
3943 Sequence.RewrapReferenceInitList(DestType, ILE);
3944 return;
3945 }
3946
3947 const RecordType *DestRecordType = DestType->getAs<RecordType>();
3948 assert(DestRecordType && "Constructor initialization requires record type");
3949 CXXRecordDecl *DestRecordDecl
3950 = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(DestRecordType->getDecl());
3951
3952 // Build the candidate set directly in the initialization sequence
3953 // structure, so that it will persist if we fail.
3954 OverloadCandidateSet &CandidateSet = Sequence.getFailedCandidateSet();
3955
3956 // Determine whether we are allowed to call explicit constructors or
3957 // explicit conversion operators.
3958 bool AllowExplicit = Kind.AllowExplicit() || IsListInit;
3959 bool CopyInitialization = Kind.getKind() == InitializationKind::IK_Copy;
3960
3961 // - Otherwise, if T is a class type, constructors are considered. The
3962 // applicable constructors are enumerated, and the best one is chosen
3963 // through overload resolution.
3964 DeclContext::lookup_result Ctors = S.LookupConstructors(DestRecordDecl);
3965
3966 OverloadingResult Result = OR_No_Viable_Function;
3967 OverloadCandidateSet::iterator Best;
3968 bool AsInitializerList = false;
3969
3970 // C++11 [over.match.list]p1, per DR1467:
3971 // When objects of non-aggregate type T are list-initialized, such that
3972 // 8.5.4 [dcl.init.list] specifies that overload resolution is performed
3973 // according to the rules in this section, overload resolution selects
3974 // the constructor in two phases:
3975 //
3976 // - Initially, the candidate functions are the initializer-list
3977 // constructors of the class T and the argument list consists of the
3978 // initializer list as a single argument.
3979 if (IsListInit) {
3980 AsInitializerList = true;
3981
3982 // If the initializer list has no elements and T has a default constructor,
3983 // the first phase is omitted.
3984 if (!(UnwrappedArgs.empty() && DestRecordDecl->hasDefaultConstructor()))
3985 Result = ResolveConstructorOverload(S, Kind.getLocation(), Args,
3986 CandidateSet, DestType, Ctors, Best,
3987 CopyInitialization, AllowExplicit,
3988 /*OnlyListConstructor=*/true,
3989 IsListInit);
3990 }
3991
3992 // C++11 [over.match.list]p1:
3993 // - If no viable initializer-list constructor is found, overload resolution
3994 // is performed again, where the candidate functions are all the
3995 // constructors of the class T and the argument list consists of the
3996 // elements of the initializer list.
3997 if (Result == OR_No_Viable_Function) {
3998 AsInitializerList = false;
3999 Result = ResolveConstructorOverload(S, Kind.getLocation(), UnwrappedArgs,
4000 CandidateSet, DestType, Ctors, Best,
4001 CopyInitialization, AllowExplicit,
4002 /*OnlyListConstructors=*/false,
4003 IsListInit);
4004 }
4005 if (Result) {
4006 Sequence.SetOverloadFailure(IsListInit ?
4007 InitializationSequence::FK_ListConstructorOverloadFailed :
4008 InitializationSequence::FK_ConstructorOverloadFailed,
4009 Result);
4010 return;
4011 }
4012
4013 bool HadMultipleCandidates = (CandidateSet.size() > 1);
4014
4015 // In C++17, ResolveConstructorOverload can select a conversion function
4016 // instead of a constructor.
4017 if (auto *CD = dyn_cast<CXXConversionDecl>(Best->Function)) {
4018 // Add the user-defined conversion step that calls the conversion function.
4019 QualType ConvType = CD->getConversionType();
4020 assert(S.Context.hasSameUnqualifiedType(ConvType, DestType) &&
4021 "should not have selected this conversion function");
4022 Sequence.AddUserConversionStep(CD, Best->FoundDecl, ConvType,
4023 HadMultipleCandidates);
4024 if (!S.Context.hasSameType(ConvType, DestType))
4025 Sequence.AddQualificationConversionStep(DestType, VK_RValue);
4026 if (IsListInit)
4027 Sequence.RewrapReferenceInitList(Entity.getType(), ILE);
4028 return;
4029 }
4030
4031 // C++11 [dcl.init]p6:
4032 // If a program calls for the default initialization of an object
4033 // of a const-qualified type T, T shall be a class type with a
4034 // user-provided default constructor.
4035 // C++ core issue 253 proposal:
4036 // If the implicit default constructor initializes all subobjects, no
4037 // initializer should be required.
4038 // The 253 proposal is for example needed to process libstdc++ headers in 5.x.
4039 CXXConstructorDecl *CtorDecl = cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(Best->Function);
4040 if (Kind.getKind() == InitializationKind::IK_Default &&
4041 Entity.getType().isConstQualified()) {
4042 if (!CtorDecl->getParent()->allowConstDefaultInit()) {
4043 if (!maybeRecoverWithZeroInitialization(S, Sequence, Entity))
4044 Sequence.SetFailed(InitializationSequence::FK_DefaultInitOfConst);
4045 return;
4046 }
4047 }
4048
4049 // C++11 [over.match.list]p1:
4050 // In copy-list-initialization, if an explicit constructor is chosen, the
4051 // initializer is ill-formed.
4052 if (IsListInit && !Kind.AllowExplicit() && CtorDecl->isExplicit()) {
4053 Sequence.SetFailed(InitializationSequence::FK_ExplicitConstructor);
4054 return;
4055 }
4056
4057 // Add the constructor initialization step. Any cv-qualification conversion is
4058 // subsumed by the initialization.
4059 Sequence.AddConstructorInitializationStep(
4060 Best->FoundDecl, CtorDecl, DestArrayType, HadMultipleCandidates,
4061 IsListInit | IsInitListCopy, AsInitializerList);
4062}
4063
4064static bool
4065ResolveOverloadedFunctionForReferenceBinding(Sema &S,
4066 Expr *Initializer,
4067 QualType &SourceType,
4068 QualType &UnqualifiedSourceType,
4069 QualType UnqualifiedTargetType,
4070 InitializationSequence &Sequence) {
4071 if (S.Context.getCanonicalType(UnqualifiedSourceType) ==
4072 S.Context.OverloadTy) {
4073 DeclAccessPair Found;
4074 bool HadMultipleCandidates = false;
4075 if (FunctionDecl *Fn
4076 = S.ResolveAddressOfOverloadedFunction(Initializer,
4077 UnqualifiedTargetType,
4078 false, Found,
4079 &HadMultipleCandidates)) {
4080 Sequence.AddAddressOverloadResolutionStep(Fn, Found,
4081 HadMultipleCandidates);
4082 SourceType = Fn->getType();
4083 UnqualifiedSourceType = SourceType.getUnqualifiedType();
4084 } else if (!UnqualifiedTargetType->isRecordType()) {
4085 Sequence.SetFailed(InitializationSequence::FK_AddressOfOverloadFailed);
4086 return true;
4087 }
4088 }
4089 return false;
4090}
4091
4092static void TryReferenceInitializationCore(Sema &S,
4093 const InitializedEntity &Entity,
4094 const InitializationKind &Kind,
4095 Expr *Initializer,
4096 QualType cv1T1, QualType T1,
4097 Qualifiers T1Quals,
4098 QualType cv2T2, QualType T2,
4099 Qualifiers T2Quals,
4100 InitializationSequence &Sequence);
4101
4102static void TryValueInitialization(Sema &S,
4103 const InitializedEntity &Entity,
4104 const InitializationKind &Kind,
4105 InitializationSequence &Sequence,
4106 InitListExpr *InitList = nullptr);
4107
4108/// Attempt list initialization of a reference.
4109static void TryReferenceListInitialization(Sema &S,
4110 const InitializedEntity &Entity,
4111 const InitializationKind &Kind,
4112 InitListExpr *InitList,
4113 InitializationSequence &Sequence,
4114 bool TreatUnavailableAsInvalid) {
4115 // First, catch C++03 where this isn't possible.
4116 if (!S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11) {
4117 Sequence.SetFailed(InitializationSequence::FK_ReferenceBindingToInitList);
4118 return;
4119 }
4120 // Can't reference initialize a compound literal.
4121 if (Entity.getKind() == InitializedEntity::EK_CompoundLiteralInit) {
4122 Sequence.SetFailed(InitializationSequence::FK_ReferenceBindingToInitList);
4123 return;
4124 }
4125
4126 QualType DestType = Entity.getType();
4127 QualType cv1T1 = DestType->getAs<ReferenceType>()->getPointeeType();
4128 Qualifiers T1Quals;
4129 QualType T1 = S.Context.getUnqualifiedArrayType(cv1T1, T1Quals);
4130
4131 // Reference initialization via an initializer list works thus:
4132 // If the initializer list consists of a single element that is
4133 // reference-related to the referenced type, bind directly to that element
4134 // (possibly creating temporaries).
4135 // Otherwise, initialize a temporary with the initializer list and
4136 // bind to that.
4137 if (InitList->getNumInits() == 1) {
4138 Expr *Initializer = InitList->getInit(0);
4139 QualType cv2T2 = Initializer->getType();
4140 Qualifiers T2Quals;
4141 QualType T2 = S.Context.getUnqualifiedArrayType(cv2T2, T2Quals);
4142
4143 // If this fails, creating a temporary wouldn't work either.
4144 if (ResolveOverloadedFunctionForReferenceBinding(S, Initializer, cv2T2, T2,
4145 T1, Sequence))
4146 return;
4147
4148 SourceLocation DeclLoc = Initializer->getBeginLoc();
4149 bool dummy1, dummy2, dummy3;
4150 Sema::ReferenceCompareResult RefRelationship
4151 = S.CompareReferenceRelationship(DeclLoc, cv1T1, cv2T2, dummy1,
4152 dummy2, dummy3);
4153 if (RefRelationship >= Sema::Ref_Related) {
4154 // Try to bind the reference here.
4155 TryReferenceInitializationCore(S, Entity, Kind, Initializer, cv1T1, T1,
4156 T1Quals, cv2T2, T2, T2Quals, Sequence);
4157 if (Sequence)
4158 Sequence.RewrapReferenceInitList(cv1T1, InitList);
4159 return;
4160 }
4161
4162 // Update the initializer if we've resolved an overloaded function.
4163 if (Sequence.step_begin() != Sequence.step_end())
4164 Sequence.RewrapReferenceInitList(cv1T1, InitList);
4165 }
4166
4167 // Not reference-related. Create a temporary and bind to that.
4168 InitializedEntity TempEntity = InitializedEntity::InitializeTemporary(cv1T1);
4169
4170 TryListInitialization(S, TempEntity, Kind, InitList, Sequence,
4171 TreatUnavailableAsInvalid);
4172 if (Sequence) {
4173 if (DestType->isRValueReferenceType() ||
4174 (T1Quals.hasConst() && !T1Quals.hasVolatile()))
4175 Sequence.AddReferenceBindingStep(cv1T1, /*bindingTemporary=*/true);
4176 else
4177 Sequence.SetFailed(
4178 InitializationSequence::FK_NonConstLValueReferenceBindingToTemporary);
4179 }
4180}
4181
4182/// Attempt list initialization (C++0x [dcl.init.list])
4183static void TryListInitialization(Sema &S,
4184 const InitializedEntity &Entity,
4185 const InitializationKind &Kind,
4186 InitListExpr *InitList,
4187 InitializationSequence &Sequence,
4188 bool TreatUnavailableAsInvalid) {
4189 QualType DestType = Entity.getType();
4190
4191 // C++ doesn't allow scalar initialization with more than one argument.
4192 // But C99 complex numbers are scalars and it makes sense there.
4193 if (S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus && DestType->isScalarType() &&
4194 !DestType->isAnyComplexType() && InitList->getNumInits() > 1) {
4195 Sequence.SetFailed(InitializationSequence::FK_TooManyInitsForScalar);
4196 return;
4197 }
4198 if (DestType->isReferenceType()) {
4199 TryReferenceListInitialization(S, Entity, Kind, InitList, Sequence,
4200 TreatUnavailableAsInvalid);
4201 return;
4202 }
4203
4204 if (DestType->isRecordType() &&
4205 !S.isCompleteType(InitList->getBeginLoc(), DestType)) {
4206 Sequence.setIncompleteTypeFailure(DestType);
4207 return;
4208 }
4209
4210 // C++11 [dcl.init.list]p3, per DR1467:
4211 // - If T is a class type and the initializer list has a single element of
4212 // type cv U, where U is T or a class derived from T, the object is
4213 // initialized from that element (by copy-initialization for
4214 // copy-list-initialization, or by direct-initialization for
4215 // direct-list-initialization).
4216 // - Otherwise, if T is a character array and the initializer list has a
4217 // single element that is an appropriately-typed string literal
4218 // (8.5.2 [dcl.init.string]), initialization is performed as described
4219 // in that section.
4220 // - Otherwise, if T is an aggregate, [...] (continue below).
4221 if (S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11 && InitList->getNumInits() == 1) {
4222 if (DestType->isRecordType()) {
4223 QualType InitType = InitList->getInit(0)->getType();
4224 if (S.Context.hasSameUnqualifiedType(InitType, DestType) ||
4225 S.IsDerivedFrom(InitList->getBeginLoc(), InitType, DestType)) {
4226 Expr *InitListAsExpr = InitList;
4227 TryConstructorInitialization(S, Entity, Kind, InitListAsExpr, DestType,
4228 DestType, Sequence,
4229 /*InitListSyntax*/false,
4230 /*IsInitListCopy*/true);
4231 return;
4232 }
4233 }
4234 if (const ArrayType *DestAT = S.Context.getAsArrayType(DestType)) {
4235 Expr *SubInit[1] = {InitList->getInit(0)};
4236 if (!isa<VariableArrayType>(DestAT) &&
4237 IsStringInit(SubInit[0], DestAT, S.Context) == SIF_None) {
4238 InitializationKind SubKind =
4239 Kind.getKind() == InitializationKind::IK_DirectList
4240 ? InitializationKind::CreateDirect(Kind.getLocation(),
4241 InitList->getLBraceLoc(),
4242 InitList->getRBraceLoc())
4243 : Kind;
4244 Sequence.InitializeFrom(S, Entity, SubKind, SubInit,
4245 /*TopLevelOfInitList*/ true,
4246 TreatUnavailableAsInvalid);
4247
4248 // TryStringLiteralInitialization() (in InitializeFrom()) will fail if
4249 // the element is not an appropriately-typed string literal, in which
4250 // case we should proceed as in C++11 (below).
4251 if (Sequence) {
4252 Sequence.RewrapReferenceInitList(Entity.getType(), InitList);
4253 return;
4254 }
4255 }
4256 }
4257 }
4258
4259 // C++11 [dcl.init.list]p3:
4260 // - If T is an aggregate, aggregate initialization is performed.
4261 if ((DestType->isRecordType() && !DestType->isAggregateType()) ||
4262 (S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11 &&
4263 S.isStdInitializerList(DestType, nullptr))) {
4264 if (S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11) {
4265 // - Otherwise, if the initializer list has no elements and T is a
4266 // class type with a default constructor, the object is
4267 // value-initialized.
4268 if (InitList->getNumInits() == 0) {
4269 CXXRecordDecl *RD = DestType->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
4270 if (RD->hasDefaultConstructor()) {
4271 TryValueInitialization(S, Entity, Kind, Sequence, InitList);
4272 return;
4273 }
4274 }
4275
4276 // - Otherwise, if T is a specialization of std::initializer_list<E>,
4277 // an initializer_list object constructed [...]
4278 if (TryInitializerListConstruction(S, InitList, DestType, Sequence,
4279 TreatUnavailableAsInvalid))
4280 return;
4281
4282 // - Otherwise, if T is a class type, constructors are considered.
4283 Expr *InitListAsExpr = InitList;
4284 TryConstructorInitialization(S, Entity, Kind, InitListAsExpr, DestType,
4285 DestType, Sequence, /*InitListSyntax*/true);
4286 } else
4287 Sequence.SetFailed(InitializationSequence::FK_InitListBadDestinationType);
4288 return;
4289 }
4290
4291 if (S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus && !DestType->isAggregateType() &&
4292 InitList->getNumInits() == 1) {
4293 Expr *E = InitList->getInit(0);
4294
4295 // - Otherwise, if T is an enumeration with a fixed underlying type,
4296 // the initializer-list has a single element v, and the initialization
4297 // is direct-list-initialization, the object is initialized with the
4298 // value T(v); if a narrowing conversion is required to convert v to
4299 // the underlying type of T, the program is ill-formed.
4300 auto *ET = DestType->getAs<EnumType>();
4301 if (S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus17 &&
4302 Kind.getKind() == InitializationKind::IK_DirectList &&
4303 ET && ET->getDecl()->isFixed() &&
4304 !S.Context.hasSameUnqualifiedType(E->getType(), DestType) &&
4305 (E->getType()->isIntegralOrEnumerationType() ||
4306 E->getType()->isFloatingType())) {
4307 // There are two ways that T(v) can work when T is an enumeration type.
4308 // If there is either an implicit conversion sequence from v to T or
4309 // a conversion function that can convert from v to T, then we use that.
4310 // Otherwise, if v is of integral, enumeration, or floating-point type,
4311 // it is converted to the enumeration type via its underlying type.
4312 // There is no overlap possible between these two cases (except when the
4313 // source value is already of the destination type), and the first
4314 // case is handled by the general case for single-element lists below.
4315 ImplicitConversionSequence ICS;
4316 ICS.setStandard(ImplicitConversionSequence::MemsetToZero);
4317 ICS.Standard.setAsIdentityConversion();
4318 if (!E->isRValue())
4319 ICS.Standard.First = ICK_Lvalue_To_Rvalue;
4320 // If E is of a floating-point type, then the conversion is ill-formed
4321 // due to narrowing, but go through the motions in order to produce the
4322 // right diagnostic.
4323 ICS.Standard.Second = E->getType()->isFloatingType()
4324 ? ICK_Floating_Integral
4325 : ICK_Integral_Conversion;
4326 ICS.Standard.setFromType(E->getType());
4327 ICS.Standard.setToType(0, E->getType());
4328 ICS.Standard.setToType(1, DestType);
4329 ICS.Standard.setToType(2, DestType);
4330 Sequence.AddConversionSequenceStep(ICS, ICS.Standard.getToType(2),
4331 /*TopLevelOfInitList*/true);
4332 Sequence.RewrapReferenceInitList(Entity.getType(), InitList);
4333 return;
4334 }
4335
4336 // - Otherwise, if the initializer list has a single element of type E
4337 // [...references are handled above...], the object or reference is
4338 // initialized from that element (by copy-initialization for
4339 // copy-list-initialization, or by direct-initialization for
4340 // direct-list-initialization); if a narrowing conversion is required
4341 // to convert the element to T, the program is ill-formed.
4342 //
4343 // Per core-24034, this is direct-initialization if we were performing
4344 // direct-list-initialization and copy-initialization otherwise.
4345 // We can't use InitListChecker for this, because it always performs
4346 // copy-initialization. This only matters if we might use an 'explicit'
4347 // conversion operator, so we only need to handle the cases where the source
4348 // is of record type.
4349 if (InitList->getInit(0)->getType()->isRecordType()) {
4350 InitializationKind SubKind =
4351 Kind.getKind() == InitializationKind::IK_DirectList
4352 ? InitializationKind::CreateDirect(Kind.getLocation(),
4353 InitList->getLBraceLoc(),
4354 InitList->getRBraceLoc())
4355 : Kind;
4356 Expr *SubInit[1] = { InitList->getInit(0) };
4357 Sequence.InitializeFrom(S, Entity, SubKind, SubInit,
4358 /*TopLevelOfInitList*/true,
4359 TreatUnavailableAsInvalid);
4360 if (Sequence)
4361 Sequence.RewrapReferenceInitList(Entity.getType(), InitList);
4362 return;
4363 }
4364 }
4365
4366 InitListChecker CheckInitList(S, Entity, InitList,
4367 DestType, /*VerifyOnly=*/true, TreatUnavailableAsInvalid);
4368 if (CheckInitList.HadError()) {
4369 Sequence.SetFailed(InitializationSequence::FK_ListInitializationFailed);
4370 return;
4371 }
4372
4373 // Add the list initialization step with the built init list.
4374 Sequence.AddListInitializationStep(DestType);
4375}
4376
4377/// Try a reference initialization that involves calling a conversion
4378/// function.
4379static OverloadingResult TryRefInitWithConversionFunction(
4380 Sema &S, const InitializedEntity &Entity, const InitializationKind &Kind,
4381 Expr *Initializer, bool AllowRValues, bool IsLValueRef,
4382 InitializationSequence &Sequence) {
4383 QualType DestType = Entity.getType();
4384 QualType cv1T1 = DestType->getAs<ReferenceType>()->getPointeeType();
4385 QualType T1 = cv1T1.getUnqualifiedType();
4386 QualType cv2T2 = Initializer->getType();
4387 QualType T2 = cv2T2.getUnqualifiedType();
4388
4389 bool DerivedToBase;
4390 bool ObjCConversion;
4391 bool ObjCLifetimeConversion;
4392 assert(!S.CompareReferenceRelationship(Initializer->getBeginLoc(), T1, T2,
4393 DerivedToBase, ObjCConversion,
4394 ObjCLifetimeConversion) &&
4395 "Must have incompatible references when binding via conversion");
4396 (void)DerivedToBase;
4397 (void)ObjCConversion;
4398 (void)ObjCLifetimeConversion;
4399
4400 // Build the candidate set directly in the initialization sequence
4401 // structure, so that it will persist if we fail.
4402 OverloadCandidateSet &CandidateSet = Sequence.getFailedCandidateSet();
4403 CandidateSet.clear(OverloadCandidateSet::CSK_InitByUserDefinedConversion);
4404
4405 // Determine whether we are allowed to call explicit conversion operators.
4406 // Note that none of [over.match.copy], [over.match.conv], nor
4407 // [over.match.ref] permit an explicit constructor to be chosen when
4408 // initializing a reference, not even for direct-initialization.
4409 bool AllowExplicitCtors = false;
4410 bool AllowExplicitConvs = Kind.allowExplicitConversionFunctionsInRefBinding();
4411
4412 const RecordType *T1RecordType = nullptr;
4413 if (AllowRValues && (T1RecordType = T1->getAs<RecordType>()) &&
4414 S.isCompleteType(Kind.getLocation(), T1)) {
4415 // The type we're converting to is a class type. Enumerate its constructors
4416 // to see if there is a suitable conversion.
4417 CXXRecordDecl *T1RecordDecl = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(T1RecordType->getDecl());
4418
4419 for (NamedDecl *D : S.LookupConstructors(T1RecordDecl)) {
4420 auto Info = getConstructorInfo(D);
4421 if (!Info.Constructor)
4422 continue;
4423
4424 if (!Info.Constructor->isInvalidDecl() &&
4425 Info.Constructor->isConvertingConstructor(AllowExplicitCtors)) {
4426 if (Info.ConstructorTmpl)
4427 S.AddTemplateOverloadCandidate(
4428 Info.ConstructorTmpl, Info.FoundDecl,
4429 /*ExplicitArgs*/ nullptr, Initializer, CandidateSet,
4430 /*SuppressUserConversions=*/true,
4431 /*PartialOverloading*/ false, AllowExplicitCtors);
4432 else
4433 S.AddOverloadCandidate(
4434 Info.Constructor, Info.FoundDecl, Initializer, CandidateSet,
4435 /*SuppressUserConversions=*/true,
4436 /*PartialOverloading*/ false, AllowExplicitCtors);
4437 }
4438 }
4439 }
4440 if (T1RecordType && T1RecordType->getDecl()->isInvalidDecl())
4441 return OR_No_Viable_Function;
4442
4443 const RecordType *T2RecordType = nullptr;
4444 if ((T2RecordType = T2->getAs<RecordType>()) &&
4445 S.isCompleteType(Kind.getLocation(), T2)) {
4446 // The type we're converting from is a class type, enumerate its conversion
4447 // functions.
4448 CXXRecordDecl *T2RecordDecl = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(T2RecordType->getDecl());
4449
4450 const auto &Conversions = T2RecordDecl->getVisibleConversionFunctions();
4451 for (auto I = Conversions.begin(), E = Conversions.end(); I != E; ++I) {
4452 NamedDecl *D = *I;
4453 CXXRecordDecl *ActingDC = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(D->getDeclContext());
4454 if (isa<UsingShadowDecl>(D))
4455 D = cast<UsingShadowDecl>(D)->getTargetDecl();
4456
4457 FunctionTemplateDecl *ConvTemplate = dyn_cast<FunctionTemplateDecl>(D);
4458 CXXConversionDecl *Conv;
4459 if (ConvTemplate)
4460 Conv = cast<CXXConversionDecl>(ConvTemplate->getTemplatedDecl());
4461 else
4462 Conv = cast<CXXConversionDecl>(D);
4463
4464 // If the conversion function doesn't return a reference type,
4465 // it can't be considered for this conversion unless we're allowed to
4466 // consider rvalues.
4467 // FIXME: Do we need to make sure that we only consider conversion
4468 // candidates with reference-compatible results? That might be needed to
4469 // break recursion.
4470 if ((AllowExplicitConvs || !Conv->isExplicit()) &&
4471 (AllowRValues ||
4472 Conv->getConversionType()->isLValueReferenceType())) {
4473 if (ConvTemplate)
4474 S.AddTemplateConversionCandidate(
4475 ConvTemplate, I.getPair(), ActingDC, Initializer, DestType,
4476 CandidateSet,
4477 /*AllowObjCConversionOnExplicit=*/false, AllowExplicitConvs);
4478 else
4479 S.AddConversionCandidate(
4480 Conv, I.getPair(), ActingDC, Initializer, DestType, CandidateSet,
4481 /*AllowObjCConversionOnExplicit=*/false, AllowExplicitConvs);
4482 }
4483 }
4484 }
4485 if (T2RecordType && T2RecordType->getDecl()->isInvalidDecl())
4486 return OR_No_Viable_Function;
4487
4488 SourceLocation DeclLoc = Initializer->getBeginLoc();
4489
