4490 // Perform overload resolution. If it fails, return the failed result.
4491 OverloadCandidateSet::iterator Best;
4492 if (OverloadingResult Result
4493 = CandidateSet.BestViableFunction(S, DeclLoc, Best))
4494 return Result;
4495
4496 FunctionDecl *Function = Best->Function;
4497 // This is the overload that will be used for this initialization step if we
4498 // use this initialization. Mark it as referenced.
4499 Function->setReferenced();
4500
4501 // Compute the returned type and value kind of the conversion.
4502 QualType cv3T3;
4503 if (isa<CXXConversionDecl>(Function))
4504 cv3T3 = Function->getReturnType();
4505 else
4506 cv3T3 = T1;
4507
4508 ExprValueKind VK = VK_RValue;
4509 if (cv3T3->isLValueReferenceType())
4510 VK = VK_LValue;
4511 else if (const auto *RRef = cv3T3->getAs<RValueReferenceType>())
4512 VK = RRef->getPointeeType()->isFunctionType() ? VK_LValue : VK_XValue;
4513 cv3T3 = cv3T3.getNonLValueExprType(S.Context);
4514
4515 // Add the user-defined conversion step.
4516 bool HadMultipleCandidates = (CandidateSet.size() > 1);
4517 Sequence.AddUserConversionStep(Function, Best->FoundDecl, cv3T3,
4518 HadMultipleCandidates);
4519
4520 // Determine whether we'll need to perform derived-to-base adjustments or
4521 // other conversions.
4522 bool NewDerivedToBase = false;
4523 bool NewObjCConversion = false;
4524 bool NewObjCLifetimeConversion = false;
4525 Sema::ReferenceCompareResult NewRefRelationship
4526 = S.CompareReferenceRelationship(DeclLoc, T1, cv3T3,
4527 NewDerivedToBase, NewObjCConversion,
4528 NewObjCLifetimeConversion);
4529
4530 // Add the final conversion sequence, if necessary.
4531 if (NewRefRelationship == Sema::Ref_Incompatible) {
4532 assert(!isa<CXXConstructorDecl>(Function) &&
4533 "should not have conversion after constructor");
4534
4535 ImplicitConversionSequence ICS;
4536 ICS.setStandard(Best->FinalConversion);
4537 Sequence.AddConversionSequenceStep(ICS, ICS.Standard.getToType(2));
4538
4539 // Every implicit conversion results in a prvalue, except for a glvalue
4540 // derived-to-base conversion, which we handle below.
4541 cv3T3 = ICS.Standard.getToType(2);
4542 VK = VK_RValue;
4543 }
4544
4545 // If the converted initializer is a prvalue, its type T4 is adjusted to
4546 // type "cv1 T4" and the temporary materialization conversion is applied.
4547 //
4548 // We adjust the cv-qualifications to match the reference regardless of
4549 // whether we have a prvalue so that the AST records the change. In this
4550 // case, T4 is "cv3 T3".
4551 QualType cv1T4 = S.Context.getQualifiedType(cv3T3, cv1T1.getQualifiers());
4552 if (cv1T4.getQualifiers() != cv3T3.getQualifiers())
4553 Sequence.AddQualificationConversionStep(cv1T4, VK);
4554 Sequence.AddReferenceBindingStep(cv1T4, VK == VK_RValue);
4555 VK = IsLValueRef ? VK_LValue : VK_XValue;
4556
4557 if (NewDerivedToBase)
4558 Sequence.AddDerivedToBaseCastStep(cv1T1, VK);
4559 else if (NewObjCConversion)
4560 Sequence.AddObjCObjectConversionStep(cv1T1);
4561
4562 return OR_Success;
4563}
4564
4565static void CheckCXX98CompatAccessibleCopy(Sema &S,
4566 const InitializedEntity &Entity,
4567 Expr *CurInitExpr);
4568
4569/// Attempt reference initialization (C++0x [dcl.init.ref])
4570static void TryReferenceInitialization(Sema &S,
4571 const InitializedEntity &Entity,
4572 const InitializationKind &Kind,
4573 Expr *Initializer,
4574 InitializationSequence &Sequence) {
4575 QualType DestType = Entity.getType();
4576 QualType cv1T1 = DestType->getAs<ReferenceType>()->getPointeeType();
4577 Qualifiers T1Quals;
4578 QualType T1 = S.Context.getUnqualifiedArrayType(cv1T1, T1Quals);
4579 QualType cv2T2 = Initializer->getType();
4580 Qualifiers T2Quals;
4581 QualType T2 = S.Context.getUnqualifiedArrayType(cv2T2, T2Quals);
4582
4583 // If the initializer is the address of an overloaded function, try
4584 // to resolve the overloaded function. If all goes well, T2 is the
4585 // type of the resulting function.
4586 if (ResolveOverloadedFunctionForReferenceBinding(S, Initializer, cv2T2, T2,
4587 T1, Sequence))
4588 return;
4589
4590 // Delegate everything else to a subfunction.
4591 TryReferenceInitializationCore(S, Entity, Kind, Initializer, cv1T1, T1,
4592 T1Quals, cv2T2, T2, T2Quals, Sequence);
4593}
4594
4595/// Determine whether an expression is a non-referenceable glvalue (one to
4596/// which a reference can never bind). Attempting to bind a reference to
4597/// such a glvalue will always create a temporary.
4598static bool isNonReferenceableGLValue(Expr *E) {
4599 return E->refersToBitField() || E->refersToVectorElement();
4600}
4601
4602static void CheckReferenceInitCHERI(Sema& S, const InitializedEntity &Entity,
4603 Expr *Initializer,
4604 InitializationSequence &Sequence) {
4605 if (!Sequence)
4606 return; // already failed so no need to diagnose
4607
4608 auto& TI = S.getASTContext().getTargetInfo();
4609 // XXXAR: keep runnign this code for non-CHERI for now to catch bugs in getRealReferenceType()
4610 // if (!TI.SupportsCapabilities())
4611 // return; // no capability support -> don't attempt to diagnose
4612
4613 if (S.getASTContext().getLangOpts().getCheriCapConversion() ==
4614 LangOptions::CapConv_Ignore)
4615 return;
4616
4617 // FIXME: don't error on rvalue references.
4618
4619 // Check that we aren't converting between capability and non-capability references
4620 const bool PureCapABI = TI.areAllPointersCapabilities();
4621 // If we are in the purecap ABI we can't create non-capabality references so no need to check
4622 if (!PureCapABI) {
4623 bool DestIsCapRef = PureCapABI;
4624 // Allow rvalue references.
4625 if (Entity.getType()->isRValueReferenceType())
4626 return;
4627 if (auto DestRef = Entity.getType()->getAs<ReferenceType>())
4628 DestIsCapRef = DestRef->isCHERICapability();
4629 bool SrcIsCapRef = false;
4630 // Handle special case of when we assign a dereferenced capability. This
4631 // will be represented by a UnaryOperator AST node and we then need to
4632 // check the type of the variable being dereferenced.
4633 if (auto SrcUniOp = dyn_cast<UnaryOperator>(Initializer)) {
4634 if (SrcUniOp->getOpcode() == UO_Deref) {
4635 if (auto SrcDeclRef = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(SrcUniOp->getSubExpr()->IgnoreImpCasts())) {
4636 if (auto SrcCap = SrcDeclRef->getDecl()->getType()->getAs<PointerType>())
4637 SrcIsCapRef = SrcCap->isCHERICapability();
4638 }
4639 }
4640 }
4641 if (!SrcIsCapRef) {
4642 QualType RealSrcType =
4643 Initializer->getRealReferenceType(S.getASTContext());
4644 if (auto SrcRef = RealSrcType->getAs<ReferenceType>())
4645 SrcIsCapRef = SrcRef->isCHERICapability();
4646 }
4647 if (SrcIsCapRef != DestIsCapRef) {
4648 Sequence.SetFailed(InitializationSequence::FK_ReferenceInitChangesCapabilityQualifier);
4649 return;
4650 }
4651 }
4652}
4653
4654/// Reference initialization without resolving overloaded functions.
4655static void TryReferenceInitializationCore(Sema &S,
4656 const InitializedEntity &Entity,
4657 const InitializationKind &Kind,
4658 Expr *Initializer,
4659 QualType cv1T1, QualType T1,
4660 Qualifiers T1Quals,
4661 QualType cv2T2, QualType T2,
4662 Qualifiers T2Quals,
4663 InitializationSequence &Sequence) {
4664 QualType DestType = Entity.getType();
4665 SourceLocation DeclLoc = Initializer->getBeginLoc();
4666 // Compute some basic properties of the types and the initializer.
4667 bool isLValueRef = DestType->isLValueReferenceType();
4668 bool isRValueRef = !isLValueRef;
4669 bool DerivedToBase = false;
4670 bool ObjCConversion = false;
4671 bool ObjCLifetimeConversion = false;
4672 Expr::Classification InitCategory = Initializer->Classify(S.Context);
4673 Sema::ReferenceCompareResult RefRelationship
4674 = S.CompareReferenceRelationship(DeclLoc, cv1T1, cv2T2, DerivedToBase,
4675 ObjCConversion, ObjCLifetimeConversion);
4676
4677 // make sure to check that we aren't converting from capability to non-capability
4678 auto CheckCheriCompatibility = llvm::make_scope_exit([&]() {
4679 CheckReferenceInitCHERI(S, Entity, Initializer, Sequence);
4680 });
4681
4682 // C++0x [dcl.init.ref]p5:
4683 // A reference to type "cv1 T1" is initialized by an expression of type
4684 // "cv2 T2" as follows:
4685 //
4686 // - If the reference is an lvalue reference and the initializer
4687 // expression
4688 // Note the analogous bullet points for rvalue refs to functions. Because
4689 // there are no function rvalues in C++, rvalue refs to functions are treated
4690 // like lvalue refs.
4691 OverloadingResult ConvOvlResult = OR_Success;
4692 bool T1Function = T1->isFunctionType();
4693 if (isLValueRef || T1Function) {
4694 if (InitCategory.isLValue() && !isNonReferenceableGLValue(Initializer) &&
4695 (RefRelationship == Sema::Ref_Compatible ||
4696 (Kind.isCStyleOrFunctionalCast() &&
4697 RefRelationship == Sema::Ref_Related))) {
4698 // - is an lvalue (but is not a bit-field), and "cv1 T1" is
4699 // reference-compatible with "cv2 T2," or
4700 if (T1Quals != T2Quals)
4701 // Convert to cv1 T2. This should only add qualifiers unless this is a
4702 // c-style cast. The removal of qualifiers in that case notionally
4703 // happens after the reference binding, but that doesn't matter.
4704 Sequence.AddQualificationConversionStep(
4705 S.Context.getQualifiedType(T2, T1Quals),
4706 Initializer->getValueKind());
4707 if (DerivedToBase)
4708 Sequence.AddDerivedToBaseCastStep(cv1T1, VK_LValue);
4709 else if (ObjCConversion)
4710 Sequence.AddObjCObjectConversionStep(cv1T1);
4711
4712 // We only create a temporary here when binding a reference to a
4713 // bit-field or vector element. Those cases are't supposed to be
4714 // handled by this bullet, but the outcome is the same either way.
4715 Sequence.AddReferenceBindingStep(cv1T1, false);
4716 return;
4717 }
4718
4719 // - has a class type (i.e., T2 is a class type), where T1 is not
4720 // reference-related to T2, and can be implicitly converted to an
4721 // lvalue of type "cv3 T3," where "cv1 T1" is reference-compatible
4722 // with "cv3 T3" (this conversion is selected by enumerating the
4723 // applicable conversion functions (13.3.1.6) and choosing the best
4724 // one through overload resolution (13.3)),
4725 // If we have an rvalue ref to function type here, the rhs must be
4726 // an rvalue. DR1287 removed the "implicitly" here.
4727 if (RefRelationship == Sema::Ref_Incompatible && T2->isRecordType() &&
4728 (isLValueRef || InitCategory.isRValue())) {
4729 ConvOvlResult = TryRefInitWithConversionFunction(
4730 S, Entity, Kind, Initializer, /*AllowRValues*/ isRValueRef,
4731 /*IsLValueRef*/ isLValueRef, Sequence);
4732 if (ConvOvlResult == OR_Success)
4733 return;
4734 if (ConvOvlResult != OR_No_Viable_Function)
4735 Sequence.SetOverloadFailure(
4736 InitializationSequence::FK_ReferenceInitOverloadFailed,
4737 ConvOvlResult);
4738 }
4739 }
4740
4741 // - Otherwise, the reference shall be an lvalue reference to a
4742 // non-volatile const type (i.e., cv1 shall be const), or the reference
4743 // shall be an rvalue reference.
4744 if (isLValueRef && !(T1Quals.hasConst() && !T1Quals.hasVolatile())) {
4745 if (S.Context.getCanonicalType(T2) == S.Context.OverloadTy)
4746 Sequence.SetFailed(InitializationSequence::FK_AddressOfOverloadFailed);
4747 else if (ConvOvlResult && !Sequence.getFailedCandidateSet().empty())
4748 Sequence.SetOverloadFailure(
4749 InitializationSequence::FK_ReferenceInitOverloadFailed,
4750 ConvOvlResult);
4751 else if (!InitCategory.isLValue())
4752 Sequence.SetFailed(
4753 InitializationSequence::FK_NonConstLValueReferenceBindingToTemporary);
4754 else {
4755 InitializationSequence::FailureKind FK;
4756 switch (RefRelationship) {
4757 case Sema::Ref_Compatible:
4758 if (Initializer->refersToBitField())
4759 FK = InitializationSequence::
4760 FK_NonConstLValueReferenceBindingToBitfield;
4761 else if (Initializer->refersToVectorElement())
4762 FK = InitializationSequence::
4763 FK_NonConstLValueReferenceBindingToVectorElement;
4764 else
4765 llvm_unreachable("unexpected kind of compatible initializer");
4766 break;
4767 case Sema::Ref_Related:
4768 FK = InitializationSequence::FK_ReferenceInitDropsQualifiers;
4769 break;
4770 case Sema::Ref_Incompatible:
4771 FK = InitializationSequence::
4772 FK_NonConstLValueReferenceBindingToUnrelated;
4773 break;
4774 }
4775 Sequence.SetFailed(FK);
4776 }
4777 return;
4778 }
4779
4780 // - If the initializer expression
4781 // - is an
4782 // [<=14] xvalue (but not a bit-field), class prvalue, array prvalue, or
4783 // [1z] rvalue (but not a bit-field) or
4784 // function lvalue and "cv1 T1" is reference-compatible with "cv2 T2"
4785 //
4786 // Note: functions are handled above and below rather than here...
4787 if (!T1Function &&
4788 (RefRelationship == Sema::Ref_Compatible ||
4789 (Kind.isCStyleOrFunctionalCast() &&
4790 RefRelationship == Sema::Ref_Related)) &&
4791 ((InitCategory.isXValue() && !isNonReferenceableGLValue(Initializer)) ||
4792 (InitCategory.isPRValue() &&
4793 (S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus17 || T2->isRecordType() ||
4794 T2->isArrayType())))) {
4795 ExprValueKind ValueKind = InitCategory.isXValue() ? VK_XValue : VK_RValue;
4796 if (InitCategory.isPRValue() && T2->isRecordType()) {
4797 // The corresponding bullet in C++03 [dcl.init.ref]p5 gives the
4798 // compiler the freedom to perform a copy here or bind to the
4799 // object, while C++0x requires that we bind directly to the
4800 // object. Hence, we always bind to the object without making an
4801 // extra copy. However, in C++03 requires that we check for the
4802 // presence of a suitable copy constructor:
4803 //
4804 // The constructor that would be used to make the copy shall
4805 // be callable whether or not the copy is actually done.
4806 if (!S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11 && !S.getLangOpts().MicrosoftExt)
4807 Sequence.AddExtraneousCopyToTemporary(cv2T2);
4808 else if (S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11)
4809 CheckCXX98CompatAccessibleCopy(S, Entity, Initializer);
4810 }
4811
4812 // C++1z [dcl.init.ref]/5.2.1.2:
4813 // If the converted initializer is a prvalue, its type T4 is adjusted
4814 // to type "cv1 T4" and the temporary materialization conversion is
4815 // applied.
4816 // Postpone address space conversions to after the temporary materialization
4817 // conversion to allow creating temporaries in the alloca address space.
4818 auto T1QualsIgnoreAS = T1Quals;
4819 auto T2QualsIgnoreAS = T2Quals;
4820 if (T1Quals.getAddressSpace() != T2Quals.getAddressSpace()) {
4821 T1QualsIgnoreAS.removeAddressSpace();
4822 T2QualsIgnoreAS.removeAddressSpace();
4823 }
4824 QualType cv1T4 = S.Context.getQualifiedType(cv2T2, T1QualsIgnoreAS);
4825 if (T1QualsIgnoreAS != T2QualsIgnoreAS)
4826 Sequence.AddQualificationConversionStep(cv1T4, ValueKind);
4827 Sequence.AddReferenceBindingStep(cv1T4, ValueKind == VK_RValue);
4828 ValueKind = isLValueRef ? VK_LValue : VK_XValue;
4829 // Add addr space conversion if required.
4830 if (T1Quals.getAddressSpace() != T2Quals.getAddressSpace()) {
4831 auto T4Quals = cv1T4.getQualifiers();
4832 T4Quals.addAddressSpace(T1Quals.getAddressSpace());
4833 QualType cv1T4WithAS = S.Context.getQualifiedType(T2, T4Quals);
4834 Sequence.AddQualificationConversionStep(cv1T4WithAS, ValueKind);
4835 }
4836
4837 // In any case, the reference is bound to the resulting glvalue (or to
4838 // an appropriate base class subobject).
4839 if (DerivedToBase)
4840 Sequence.AddDerivedToBaseCastStep(cv1T1, ValueKind);
4841 else if (ObjCConversion)
4842 Sequence.AddObjCObjectConversionStep(cv1T1);
4843 return;
4844 }
4845
4846 // - has a class type (i.e., T2 is a class type), where T1 is not
4847 // reference-related to T2, and can be implicitly converted to an
4848 // xvalue, class prvalue, or function lvalue of type "cv3 T3",
4849 // where "cv1 T1" is reference-compatible with "cv3 T3",
4850 //
4851 // DR1287 removes the "implicitly" here.
4852 if (T2->isRecordType()) {
4853 if (RefRelationship == Sema::Ref_Incompatible) {
4854 ConvOvlResult = TryRefInitWithConversionFunction(
4855 S, Entity, Kind, Initializer, /*AllowRValues*/ true,
4856 /*IsLValueRef*/ isLValueRef, Sequence);
4857 if (ConvOvlResult)
4858 Sequence.SetOverloadFailure(
4859 InitializationSequence::FK_ReferenceInitOverloadFailed,
4860 ConvOvlResult);
4861
4862 return;
4863 }
4864
4865 if (RefRelationship == Sema::Ref_Compatible &&
4866 isRValueRef && InitCategory.isLValue()) {
4867 Sequence.SetFailed(
4868 InitializationSequence::FK_RValueReferenceBindingToLValue);
4869 return;
4870 }
4871
4872 Sequence.SetFailed(InitializationSequence::FK_ReferenceInitDropsQualifiers);
4873 return;
4874 }
4875
4876 // - Otherwise, a temporary of type "cv1 T1" is created and initialized
4877 // from the initializer expression using the rules for a non-reference
4878 // copy-initialization (8.5). The reference is then bound to the
4879 // temporary. [...]
4880
4881 // Ignore address space of reference type at this point and perform address
4882 // space conversion after the reference binding step.
4883 QualType cv1T1IgnoreAS =
4884 T1Quals.hasAddressSpace()
4885 ? S.Context.getQualifiedType(T1, T1Quals.withoutAddressSpace())
4886 : cv1T1;
4887
4888 InitializedEntity TempEntity =
4889 InitializedEntity::InitializeTemporary(cv1T1IgnoreAS);
4890
4891 // FIXME: Why do we use an implicit conversion here rather than trying
4892 // copy-initialization?
4893 ImplicitConversionSequence ICS
4894 = S.TryImplicitConversion(Initializer, TempEntity.getType(),
4895 /*SuppressUserConversions=*/false,
4896 /*AllowExplicit=*/false,
4897 /*FIXME:InOverloadResolution=*/false,
4898 /*CStyle=*/Kind.isCStyleOrFunctionalCast(),
4899 /*AllowObjCWritebackConversion=*/false);
4900
4901 if (ICS.isBad()) {
4902 // FIXME: Use the conversion function set stored in ICS to turn
4903 // this into an overloading ambiguity diagnostic. However, we need
4904 // to keep that set as an OverloadCandidateSet rather than as some
4905 // other kind of set.
4906 if (ConvOvlResult && !Sequence.getFailedCandidateSet().empty())
4907 Sequence.SetOverloadFailure(
4908 InitializationSequence::FK_ReferenceInitOverloadFailed,
4909 ConvOvlResult);
4910 else if (S.Context.getCanonicalType(T2) == S.Context.OverloadTy)
4911 Sequence.SetFailed(InitializationSequence::FK_AddressOfOverloadFailed);
4912 else
4913 Sequence.SetFailed(InitializationSequence::FK_ReferenceInitFailed);
4914 return;
4915 } else {
4916 Sequence.AddConversionSequenceStep(ICS, TempEntity.getType());
4917 }
4918
4919 // [...] If T1 is reference-related to T2, cv1 must be the
4920 // same cv-qualification as, or greater cv-qualification
4921 // than, cv2; otherwise, the program is ill-formed.
4922 unsigned T1CVRQuals = T1Quals.getCVRQualifiers();
4923 unsigned T2CVRQuals = T2Quals.getCVRQualifiers();
4924 if ((RefRelationship == Sema::Ref_Related &&
4925 (T1CVRQuals | T2CVRQuals) != T1CVRQuals) ||
4926 !T1Quals.isAddressSpaceSupersetOf(T2Quals)) {
4927 Sequence.SetFailed(InitializationSequence::FK_ReferenceInitDropsQualifiers);
4928 return;
4929 }
4930
4931 // [...] If T1 is reference-related to T2 and the reference is an rvalue
4932 // reference, the initializer expression shall not be an lvalue.
4933 if (RefRelationship >= Sema::Ref_Related && !isLValueRef &&
4934 InitCategory.isLValue()) {
4935 Sequence.SetFailed(
4936 InitializationSequence::FK_RValueReferenceBindingToLValue);
4937 return;
4938 }
4939
4940 Sequence.AddReferenceBindingStep(cv1T1IgnoreAS, /*bindingTemporary=*/true);
4941
4942 if (T1Quals.hasAddressSpace()) {
4943 if (!Qualifiers::isAddressSpaceSupersetOf(T1Quals.getAddressSpace(),
4944 LangAS::Default)) {
4945 Sequence.SetFailed(
4946 InitializationSequence::FK_ReferenceAddrspaceMismatchTemporary);
4947 return;
4948 }
4949 Sequence.AddQualificationConversionStep(cv1T1, isLValueRef ? VK_LValue
4950 : VK_XValue);
4951 }
4952}
4953
4954/// Attempt character array initialization from a string literal
4955/// (C++ [dcl.init.string], C99 6.7.8).
4956static void TryStringLiteralInitialization(Sema &S,
4957 const InitializedEntity &Entity,
4958 const InitializationKind &Kind,
4959 Expr *Initializer,
4960 InitializationSequence &Sequence) {
4961 Sequence.AddStringInitStep(Entity.getType());
4962}
4963
4964/// Attempt value initialization (C++ [dcl.init]p7).
4965static void TryValueInitialization(Sema &S,
4966 const InitializedEntity &Entity,
4967 const InitializationKind &Kind,
4968 InitializationSequence &Sequence,
4969 InitListExpr *InitList) {
4970 assert((!InitList || InitList->getNumInits() == 0) &&
4971 "Shouldn't use value-init for non-empty init lists");
4972
4973 // C++98 [dcl.init]p5, C++11 [dcl.init]p7:
4974 //
4975 // To value-initialize an object of type T means:
4976 QualType T = Entity.getType();
4977
4978 // -- if T is an array type, then each element is value-initialized;
4979 T = S.Context.getBaseElementType(T);
4980
4981 if (const RecordType *RT = T->getAs<RecordType>()) {
4982 if (CXXRecordDecl *ClassDecl = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RT->getDecl())) {
4983 bool NeedZeroInitialization = true;
4984 // C++98:
4985 // -- if T is a class type (clause 9) with a user-declared constructor
4986 // (12.1), then the default constructor for T is called (and the
4987 // initialization is ill-formed if T has no accessible default
4988 // constructor);
4989 // C++11:
4990 // -- if T is a class type (clause 9) with either no default constructor
4991 // (12.1 [class.ctor]) or a default constructor that is user-provided
4992 // or deleted, then the object is default-initialized;
4993 //
4994 // Note that the C++11 rule is the same as the C++98 rule if there are no
4995 // defaulted or deleted constructors, so we just use it unconditionally.
4996 CXXConstructorDecl *CD = S.LookupDefaultConstructor(ClassDecl);
4997 if (!CD || !CD->getCanonicalDecl()->isDefaulted() || CD->isDeleted())
4998 NeedZeroInitialization = false;
4999
5000 // -- if T is a (possibly cv-qualified) non-union class type without a
5001 // user-provided or deleted default constructor, then the object is
5002 // zero-initialized and, if T has a non-trivial default constructor,
5003 // default-initialized;
5004 // The 'non-union' here was removed by DR1502. The 'non-trivial default
5005 // constructor' part was removed by DR1507.
5006 if (NeedZeroInitialization)
5007 Sequence.AddZeroInitializationStep(Entity.getType());
5008
5009 // C++03:
5010 // -- if T is a non-union class type without a user-declared constructor,
5011 // then every non-static data member and base class component of T is
5012 // value-initialized;
5013 // [...] A program that calls for [...] value-initialization of an
5014 // entity of reference type is ill-formed.
5015 //
5016 // C++11 doesn't need this handling, because value-initialization does not
5017 // occur recursively there, and the implicit default constructor is
5018 // defined as deleted in the problematic cases.
5019 if (!S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11 &&
5020 ClassDecl->hasUninitializedReferenceMember()) {
5021 Sequence.SetFailed(InitializationSequence::FK_TooManyInitsForReference);
5022 return;
5023 }
5024
5025 // If this is list-value-initialization, pass the empty init list on when
5026 // building the constructor call. This affects the semantics of a few
5027 // things (such as whether an explicit default constructor can be called).
5028 Expr *InitListAsExpr = InitList;
5029 MultiExprArg Args(&InitListAsExpr, InitList ? 1 : 0);
5030 bool InitListSyntax = InitList;
5031
5032 // FIXME: Instead of creating a CXXConstructExpr of array type here,
5033 // wrap a class-typed CXXConstructExpr in an ArrayInitLoopExpr.
5034 return TryConstructorInitialization(
5035 S, Entity, Kind, Args, T, Entity.getType(), Sequence, InitListSyntax);
5036 }
5037 }
5038
5039 Sequence.AddZeroInitializationStep(Entity.getType());
5040}
5041
5042/// Attempt default initialization (C++ [dcl.init]p6).
5043static void TryDefaultInitialization(Sema &S,
5044 const InitializedEntity &Entity,
5045 const InitializationKind &Kind,
5046 InitializationSequence &Sequence) {
5047 assert(Kind.getKind() == InitializationKind::IK_Default);
5048
5049 // C++ [dcl.init]p6:
5050 // To default-initialize an object of type T means:
5051 // - if T is an array type, each element is default-initialized;
5052 QualType DestType = S.Context.getBaseElementType(Entity.getType());
5053
5054 // - if T is a (possibly cv-qualified) class type (Clause 9), the default
5055 // constructor for T is called (and the initialization is ill-formed if
5056 // T has no accessible default constructor);
5057 if (DestType->isRecordType() && S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
5058 TryConstructorInitialization(S, Entity, Kind, None, DestType,
5059 Entity.getType(), Sequence);
5060 return;
5061 }
5062
5063 // - otherwise, no initialization is performed.
5064
5065 // If a program calls for the default initialization of an object of
5066 // a const-qualified type T, T shall be a class type with a user-provided
5067 // default constructor.
5068 if (DestType.isConstQualified() && S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
5069 if (!maybeRecoverWithZeroInitialization(S, Sequence, Entity))
5070 Sequence.SetFailed(InitializationSequence::FK_DefaultInitOfConst);
5071 return;
5072 }
5073
5074 // If the destination type has a lifetime property, zero-initialize it.
5075 if (DestType.getQualifiers().hasObjCLifetime()) {
5076 Sequence.AddZeroInitializationStep(Entity.getType());
5077 return;
5078 }
5079}
5080
5081/// Attempt a user-defined conversion between two types (C++ [dcl.init]),
5082/// which enumerates all conversion functions and performs overload resolution
5083/// to select the best.
5084static void TryUserDefinedConversion(Sema &S,
5085 QualType DestType,
5086 const InitializationKind &Kind,
5087 Expr *Initializer,
5088 InitializationSequence &Sequence,
5089 bool TopLevelOfInitList) {
5090 assert(!DestType->isReferenceType() && "References are handled elsewhere");
5091 QualType SourceType = Initializer->getType();
5092 assert((DestType->isRecordType() || SourceType->isRecordType()) &&
5093 "Must have a class type to perform a user-defined conversion");
5094
5095 // Build the candidate set directly in the initialization sequence
5096 // structure, so that it will persist if we fail.
5097 OverloadCandidateSet &CandidateSet = Sequence.getFailedCandidateSet();
5098 CandidateSet.clear(OverloadCandidateSet::CSK_InitByUserDefinedConversion);
5099
5100 // Determine whether we are allowed to call explicit constructors or
5101 // explicit conversion operators.
5102 bool AllowExplicit = Kind.AllowExplicit();
5103
5104 if (const RecordType *DestRecordType = DestType->getAs<RecordType>()) {
5105 // The type we're converting to is a class type. Enumerate its constructors
5106 // to see if there is a suitable conversion.
5107 CXXRecordDecl *DestRecordDecl
5108 = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(DestRecordType->getDecl());
5109
5110 // Try to complete the type we're converting to.
5111 if (S.isCompleteType(Kind.getLocation(), DestType)) {
5112 for (NamedDecl *D : S.LookupConstructors(DestRecordDecl)) {
5113 auto Info = getConstructorInfo(D);
5114 if (!Info.Constructor)
5115 continue;
5116
5117 if (!Info.Constructor->isInvalidDecl() &&
5118 Info.Constructor->isConvertingConstructor(AllowExplicit)) {
5119 if (Info.ConstructorTmpl)
5120 S.AddTemplateOverloadCandidate(
5121 Info.ConstructorTmpl, Info.FoundDecl,
5122 /*ExplicitArgs*/ nullptr, Initializer, CandidateSet,
5123 /*SuppressUserConversions=*/true,
5124 /*PartialOverloading*/ false, AllowExplicit);
5125 else
5126 S.AddOverloadCandidate(Info.Constructor, Info.FoundDecl,
5127 Initializer, CandidateSet,
5128 /*SuppressUserConversions=*/true,
5129 /*PartialOverloading*/ false, AllowExplicit);
5130 }
5131 }
5132 }
5133 }
5134
5135 SourceLocation DeclLoc = Initializer->getBeginLoc();
5136
5137 if (const RecordType *SourceRecordType = SourceType->getAs<RecordType>()) {
5138 // The type we're converting from is a class type, enumerate its conversion
5139 // functions.
5140
5141 // We can only enumerate the conversion functions for a complete type; if
5142 // the type isn't complete, simply skip this step.
5143 if (S.isCompleteType(DeclLoc, SourceType)) {
5144 CXXRecordDecl *SourceRecordDecl
5145 = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(SourceRecordType->getDecl());
5146
5147 const auto &Conversions =
5148 SourceRecordDecl->getVisibleConversionFunctions();
5149 for (auto I = Conversions.begin(), E = Conversions.end(); I != E; ++I) {
5150 NamedDecl *D = *I;
5151 CXXRecordDecl *ActingDC = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(D->getDeclContext());
5152 if (isa<UsingShadowDecl>(D))
5153 D = cast<UsingShadowDecl>(D)->getTargetDecl();
5154
5155 FunctionTemplateDecl *ConvTemplate = dyn_cast<FunctionTemplateDecl>(D);
5156 CXXConversionDecl *Conv;
5157 if (ConvTemplate)
5158 Conv = cast<CXXConversionDecl>(ConvTemplate->getTemplatedDecl());
5159 else
5160 Conv = cast<CXXConversionDecl>(D);
5161
5162 if (AllowExplicit || !Conv->isExplicit()) {
5163 if (ConvTemplate)
5164 S.AddTemplateConversionCandidate(
5165 ConvTemplate, I.getPair(), ActingDC, Initializer, DestType,
5166 CandidateSet, AllowExplicit, AllowExplicit);
5167 else
5168 S.AddConversionCandidate(Conv, I.getPair(), ActingDC, Initializer,
5169 DestType, CandidateSet, AllowExplicit,
5170 AllowExplicit);
5171 }
5172 }
5173 }
5174 }
5175
5176 // Perform overload resolution. If it fails, return the failed result.
5177 OverloadCandidateSet::iterator Best;
5178 if (OverloadingResult Result
5179 = CandidateSet.BestViableFunction(S, DeclLoc, Best)) {
5180 Sequence.SetOverloadFailure(
5181 InitializationSequence::FK_UserConversionOverloadFailed,
5182 Result);
5183 return;
5184 }
5185
5186 FunctionDecl *Function = Best->Function;
5187 Function->setReferenced();
5188 bool HadMultipleCandidates = (CandidateSet.size() > 1);
5189
5190 if (isa<CXXConstructorDecl>(Function)) {
5191 // Add the user-defined conversion step. Any cv-qualification conversion is
5192 // subsumed by the initialization. Per DR5, the created temporary is of the
5193 // cv-unqualified type of the destination.
5194 Sequence.AddUserConversionStep(Function, Best->FoundDecl,
5195 DestType.getUnqualifiedType(),
5196 HadMultipleCandidates);
5197
5198 // C++14 and before:
5199 // - if the function is a constructor, the call initializes a temporary
5200 // of the cv-unqualified version of the destination type. The [...]
5201 // temporary [...] is then used to direct-initialize, according to the
5202 // rules above, the object that is the destination of the
5203 // copy-initialization.
5204 // Note that this just performs a simple object copy from the temporary.
5205 //
5206 // C++17:
5207 // - if the function is a constructor, the call is a prvalue of the
5208 // cv-unqualified version of the destination type whose return object
5209 // is initialized by the constructor. The call is used to
5210 // direct-initialize, according to the rules above, the object that
5211 // is the destination of the copy-initialization.
5212 // Therefore we need to do nothing further.
5213 //
5214 // FIXME: Mark this copy as extraneous.
5215 if (!S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus17)
5216 Sequence.AddFinalCopy(DestType);
5217 else if (DestType.hasQualifiers())
5218 Sequence.AddQualificationConversionStep(DestType, VK_RValue);
5219 return;
5220 }
5221
5222 // Add the user-defined conversion step that calls the conversion function.
5223 QualType ConvType = Function->getCallResultType();
5224 Sequence.AddUserConversionStep(Function, Best->FoundDecl, ConvType,
5225 HadMultipleCandidates);
5226
5227 if (ConvType->getAs<RecordType>()) {
5228 // The call is used to direct-initialize [...] the object that is the
5229 // destination of the copy-initialization.
5230 //
5231 // In C++17, this does not call a constructor if we enter /17.6.1:
5232 // - If the initializer expression is a prvalue and the cv-unqualified
5233 // version of the source type is the same as the class of the
5234 // destination [... do not make an extra copy]
5235 //
5236 // FIXME: Mark this copy as extraneous.
5237 if (!S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus17 ||
5238 Function->getReturnType()->isReferenceType() ||
5239 !S.Context.hasSameUnqualifiedType(ConvType, DestType))
5240 Sequence.AddFinalCopy(DestType);
5241 else if (!S.Context.hasSameType(ConvType, DestType))
5242 Sequence.AddQualificationConversionStep(DestType, VK_RValue);
5243 return;
5244 }
5245
5246 // If the conversion following the call to the conversion function
5247 // is interesting, add it as a separate step.
5248 if (Best->FinalConversion.First || Best->FinalConversion.Second ||
5249 Best->FinalConversion.Third) {
5250 ImplicitConversionSequence ICS;
5251 ICS.setStandard(Best->FinalConversion);
5252 Sequence.AddConversionSequenceStep(ICS, DestType, TopLevelOfInitList);
5253 }
5254}
5255
5256/// An egregious hack for compatibility with libstdc++-4.2: in <tr1/hashtable>,
5257/// a function with a pointer return type contains a 'return false;' statement.
5258/// In C++11, 'false' is not a null pointer, so this breaks the build of any
5259/// code using that header.
5260///
5261/// Work around this by treating 'return false;' as zero-initializing the result
5262/// if it's used in a pointer-returning function in a system header.
5263static bool isLibstdcxxPointerReturnFalseHack(Sema &S,
5264 const InitializedEntity &Entity,
5265 const Expr *Init) {
5266 return S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11 &&
5267 Entity.getKind() == InitializedEntity::EK_Result &&
5268 Entity.getType()->isPointerType() &&
5269 isa<CXXBoolLiteralExpr>(Init) &&
5270 !cast<CXXBoolLiteralExpr>(Init)->getValue() &&
5271 S.getSourceManager().isInSystemHeader(Init->getExprLoc());
5272}
5273
5274/// The non-zero enum values here are indexes into diagnostic alternatives.
5275enum InvalidICRKind { IIK_okay, IIK_nonlocal, IIK_nonscalar };
5276
5277/// Determines whether this expression is an acceptable ICR source.
5278static InvalidICRKind isInvalidICRSource(ASTContext &C, Expr *e,
5279 bool isAddressOf, bool &isWeakAccess) {
5280 // Skip parens.
5281 e = e->IgnoreParens();
5282
5283 // Skip address-of nodes.
5284 if (UnaryOperator *op = dyn_cast<UnaryOperator>(e)) {
5285 if (op->getOpcode() == UO_AddrOf)
5286 return isInvalidICRSource(C, op->getSubExpr(), /*addressof*/ true,
5287 isWeakAccess);
5288
5289 // Skip certain casts.
5290 } else if (CastExpr *ce = dyn_cast<CastExpr>(e)) {
5291 switch (ce->getCastKind()) {
5292 case CK_Dependent:
5293 case CK_BitCast:
5294 case CK_LValueBitCast:
5295 case CK_NoOp:
5296 return isInvalidICRSource(C, ce->getSubExpr(), isAddressOf, isWeakAccess);
5297
5298 case CK_ArrayToPointerDecay:
5299 return IIK_nonscalar;
5300
5301 case CK_NullToPointer:
5302 return IIK_okay;
5303
5304 default:
5305 break;
5306 }
5307
5308 // If we have a declaration reference, it had better be a local variable.
5309 } else if (isa<DeclRefExpr>(e)) {
5310 // set isWeakAccess to true, to mean that there will be an implicit
5311 // load which requires a cleanup.
5312 if (e->getType().getObjCLifetime() == Qualifiers::OCL_Weak)
5313 isWeakAccess = true;
5314
5315 if (!isAddressOf) return IIK_nonlocal;
5316
5317 VarDecl *var = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(cast<DeclRefExpr>(e)->getDecl());
5318 if (!var) return IIK_nonlocal;
5319
5320 return (var->hasLocalStorage() ? IIK_okay : IIK_nonlocal);
5321
5322 // If we have a conditional operator, check both sides.
5323 } else if (ConditionalOperator *cond = dyn_cast<ConditionalOperator>(e)) {
5324 if (InvalidICRKind iik = isInvalidICRSource(C, cond->getLHS(), isAddressOf,
5325 isWeakAccess))
5326 return iik;
5327
5328 return isInvalidICRSource(C, cond->getRHS(), isAddressOf, isWeakAccess);
5329
5330 // These are never scalar.
5331 } else if (isa<ArraySubscriptExpr>(e)) {
5332 return IIK_nonscalar;
5333
5334 // Otherwise, it needs to be a null pointer constant.
5335 } else {
5336 return (e->isNullPointerConstant(C, Expr::NPC_ValueDependentIsNull)
5337 ? IIK_okay : IIK_nonlocal);
5338 }
5339
5340 return IIK_nonlocal;
5341}
5342
5343/// Check whether the given expression is a valid operand for an
5344/// indirect copy/restore.
5345static void checkIndirectCopyRestoreSource(Sema &S, Expr *src) {
5346 assert(src->isRValue());
5347 bool isWeakAccess = false;
5348 InvalidICRKind iik = isInvalidICRSource(S.Context, src, false, isWeakAccess);
5349 // If isWeakAccess to true, there will be an implicit
5350 // load which requires a cleanup.
5351 if (S.getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount && isWeakAccess)
5352 S.Cleanup.setExprNeedsCleanups(true);
5353
5354 if (iik == IIK_okay) return;
5355
5356 S.Diag(src->getExprLoc(), diag::err_arc_nonlocal_writeback)
5357 << ((unsigned) iik - 1) // shift index into diagnostic explanations
5358 << src->getSourceRange();
5359}
5360
5361/// Determine whether we have compatible array types for the
5362/// purposes of GNU by-copy array initialization.
5363static bool hasCompatibleArrayTypes(ASTContext &Context, const ArrayType *Dest,
5364 const ArrayType *Source) {
5365 // If the source and destination array types are equivalent, we're
5366 // done.
5367 if (Context.hasSameType(QualType(Dest, 0), QualType(Source, 0)))
5368 return true;
5369
5370 // Make sure that the element types are the same.
5371 if (!Context.hasSameType(Dest->getElementType(), Source->getElementType()))
5372 return false;
5373
5374 // The only mismatch we allow is when the destination is an
5375 // incomplete array type and the source is a constant array type.
5376 return Source->isConstantArrayType() && Dest->isIncompleteArrayType();
5377}
5378
5379static bool tryObjCWritebackConversion(Sema &S,
5380 InitializationSequence &Sequence,
5381 const InitializedEntity &Entity,
5382 Expr *Initializer) {
5383 bool ArrayDecay = false;
5384 QualType ArgType = Initializer->getType();
5385 QualType ArgPointee;
5386 if (const ArrayType *ArgArrayType = S.Context.getAsArrayType(ArgType)) {
5387 ArrayDecay = true;
5388 ArgPointee = ArgArrayType->getElementType();
5389 ArgType = S.Context.getPointerType(ArgPointee);
5390 }
5391
5392 // Handle write-back conversion.
5393 QualType ConvertedArgType;
5394 if (!S.isObjCWritebackConversion(ArgType, Entity.getType(),
5395 ConvertedArgType))
5396 return false;
5397
5398 // We should copy unless we're passing to an argument explicitly
5399 // marked 'out'.
5400 bool ShouldCopy = true;
5401 if (ParmVarDecl *param = cast_or_null<ParmVarDecl>(Entity.getDecl()))
5402 ShouldCopy = (param->getObjCDeclQualifier() != ParmVarDecl::OBJC_TQ_Out);
5403
5404 // Do we need an lvalue conversion?
5405 if (ArrayDecay || Initializer->isGLValue()) {
5406 ImplicitConversionSequence ICS;
5407 ICS.setStandard(ImplicitConversionSequence::MemsetToZero);
5408 ICS.Standard.setAsIdentityConversion();
5409
5410 QualType ResultType;
5411 if (ArrayDecay) {
5412 ICS.Standard.First = ICK_Array_To_Pointer;
5413 ResultType = S.Context.getPointerType(ArgPointee);
5414 } else {
5415 ICS.Standard.First = ICK_Lvalue_To_Rvalue;
5416 ResultType = Initializer->getType().getNonLValueExprType(S.Context);
5417 }
5418
5419 Sequence.AddConversionSequenceStep(ICS, ResultType);
5420 }
5421
5422 Sequence.AddPassByIndirectCopyRestoreStep(Entity.getType(), ShouldCopy);
5423 return true;
5424}
5425
5426static bool TryOCLSamplerInitialization(Sema &S,
5427 InitializationSequence &Sequence,
5428 QualType DestType,
5429 Expr *Initializer) {
5430 if (!S.getLangOpts().OpenCL || !DestType->isSamplerT() ||
5431 (!Initializer->isIntegerConstantExpr(S.Context) &&
5432 !Initializer->getType()->isSamplerT()))
5433 return false;
5434
5435 Sequence.AddOCLSamplerInitStep(DestType);
5436 return true;
5437}
5438
5439static bool IsZeroInitializer(Expr *Initializer, Sema &S) {
5440 return Initializer->isIntegerConstantExpr(S.getASTContext()) &&
5441 (Initializer->EvaluateKnownConstInt(S.getASTContext()) == 0);
5442}
5443
5444static bool TryOCLZeroOpaqueTypeInitialization(Sema &S,
5445 InitializationSequence &Sequence,
5446 QualType DestType,
5447 Expr *Initializer) {
5448 if (!S.getLangOpts().OpenCL)
5449 return false;
5450
5451 //
5452 // OpenCL 1.2 spec, s6.12.10
5453 //
5454 // The event argument can also be used to associate the
5455 // async_work_group_copy with a previous async copy allowing
5456 // an event to be shared by multiple async copies; otherwise
5457 // event should be zero.
5458 //
5459 if (DestType->isEventT() || DestType->isQueueT()) {
5460 if (!IsZeroInitializer(Initializer, S))
5461 return false;
5462
5463 Sequence.AddOCLZeroOpaqueTypeStep(DestType);
5464 return true;
5465 }
5466
5467 // We should allow zero initialization for all types defined in the
5468 // cl_intel_device_side_avc_motion_estimation extension, except
5469 // intel_sub_group_avc_mce_payload_t and intel_sub_group_avc_mce_result_t.
5470 if (S.getOpenCLOptions().isEnabled(
5471 "cl_intel_device_side_avc_motion_estimation") &&
5472 DestType->isOCLIntelSubgroupAVCType()) {
5473 if (DestType->isOCLIntelSubgroupAVCMcePayloadType() ||
5474 DestType->isOCLIntelSubgroupAVCMceResultType())
5475 return false;
5476 if (!IsZeroInitializer(Initializer, S))
5477 return false;
5478
5479 Sequence.AddOCLZeroOpaqueTypeStep(DestType);
5480 return true;
5481 }
5482
5483 return false;
5484}
5485
5486InitializationSequence::InitializationSequence(Sema &S,
5487 const InitializedEntity &Entity,
5488 const InitializationKind &Kind,
5489 MultiExprArg Args,
5490 bool TopLevelOfInitList,
5491 bool TreatUnavailableAsInvalid)
5492 : FailedCandidateSet(Kind.getLocation(), OverloadCandidateSet::CSK_Normal) {
5493 InitializeFrom(S, Entity, Kind, Args, TopLevelOfInitList,
5494 TreatUnavailableAsInvalid);
5495}
5496
5497/// Tries to get a FunctionDecl out of `E`. If it succeeds and we can take the
5498/// address of that function, this returns true. Otherwise, it returns false.
5499static bool isExprAnUnaddressableFunction(Sema &S, const Expr *E) {
5500 auto *DRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(E);
5501 if (!DRE || !isa<FunctionDecl>(DRE->getDecl()))
5502 return false;
5503
5504 return !S.checkAddressOfFunctionIsAvailable(
5505 cast<FunctionDecl>(DRE->getDecl()));
5506}
5507
5508/// Determine whether we can perform an elementwise array copy for this kind
5509/// of entity.
5510static bool canPerformArrayCopy(const InitializedEntity &Entity) {
5511 switch (Entity.getKind()) {
5512 case InitializedEntity::EK_LambdaCapture:
5513 // C++ [expr.prim.lambda]p24:
5514 // For array members, the array elements are direct-initialized in
5515 // increasing subscript order.
5516 return true;
5517
5518 case InitializedEntity::EK_Variable:
5519 // C++ [dcl.decomp]p1:
5520 // [...] each element is copy-initialized or direct-initialized from the
5521 // corresponding element of the assignment-expression [...]
5522 return isa<DecompositionDecl>(Entity.getDecl());
5523
5524 case InitializedEntity::EK_Member:
5525 // C++ [class.copy.ctor]p14:
5526 // - if the member is an array, each element is direct-initialized with
5527 // the corresponding subobject of x
5528 return Entity.isImplicitMemberInitializer();
5529
5530 case InitializedEntity::EK_ArrayElement:
5531 // All the above cases are intended to apply recursively, even though none
5532 // of them actually say that.
5533 if (auto *E = Entity.getParent())
5534 return canPerformArrayCopy(*E);
5535 break;
5536
5537 default:
5538 break;
5539 }
5540
5541 return false;
5542}
5543
5544void InitializationSequence::InitializeFrom(Sema &S,
5545 const InitializedEntity &Entity,
5546 const InitializationKind &Kind,
5547 MultiExprArg Args,
5548 bool TopLevelOfInitList,
5549 bool TreatUnavailableAsInvalid) {
5550 ASTContext &Context = S.Context;
5551
5552 // Eliminate non-overload placeholder types in the arguments. We
5553 // need to do this before checking whether types are dependent
5554 // because lowering a pseudo-object expression might well give us
5555 // something of dependent type.
5556 for (unsigned I = 0, E = Args.size(); I != E; ++I)
5557 if (Args[I]->getType()->isNonOverloadPlaceholderType()) {
5558 // FIXME: should we be doing this here?
5559 ExprResult result = S.CheckPlaceholderExpr(Args[I]);
5560 if (result.isInvalid()) {
5561 SetFailed(FK_PlaceholderType);
5562 return;
5563 }
5564 Args[I] = result.get();
5565 }
5566
5567 // C++0x [dcl.init]p16:
5568 // The semantics of initializers are as follows. The destination type is
5569 // the type of the object or reference being initialized and the source
5570 // type is the type of the initializer expression. The source type is not
5571 // defined when the initializer is a braced-init-list or when it is a
5572 // parenthesized list of expressions.
5573 QualType DestType = Entity.getType();
5574
5575 if (DestType->isDependentType() ||
5576 Expr::hasAnyTypeDependentArguments(Args)) {
5577 SequenceKind = DependentSequence;
5578 return;
5579 }
5580
5581 // Almost everything is a normal sequence.
5582 setSequenceKind(NormalSequence);
5583
5584 QualType SourceType;
5585 Expr *Initializer = nullptr;
5586 if (Args.size() == 1) {
5587 Initializer = Args[0];
5588 if (S.getLangOpts().ObjC) {
5589 if (S.CheckObjCBridgeRelatedConversions(Initializer->getBeginLoc(),
5590 DestType, Initializer->getType(),
5591 Initializer) ||
5592 S.ConversionToObjCStringLiteralCheck(DestType, Initializer))
5593 Args[0] = Initializer;
5594 }
5595 if (!isa<InitListExpr>(Initializer))
5596 SourceType = Initializer->getType();
5597 }
5598
5599 // - If the initializer is a (non-parenthesized) braced-init-list, the
5600 // object is list-initialized (8.5.4).
5601 if (Kind.getKind() != InitializationKind::IK_Direct) {
5602 if (InitListExpr *InitList = dyn_cast_or_null<InitListExpr>(Initializer)) {
5603 TryListInitialization(S, Entity, Kind, InitList, *this,
5604 TreatUnavailableAsInvalid);
5605 return;
5606 }
5607 }
5608
5609 // - If the destination type is a reference type, see 8.5.3.
5610 if (DestType->isReferenceType()) {
5611 // C++0x [dcl.init.ref]p1:
5612 // A variable declared to be a T& or T&&, that is, "reference to type T"
5613 // (8.3.2), shall be initialized by an object, or function, of type T or
5614 // by an object that can be converted into a T.
5615 // (Therefore, multiple arguments are not permitted.)
5616 if (Args.size() != 1)
5617 SetFailed(FK_TooManyInitsForReference);
5618 // C++17 [dcl.init.ref]p5:
5619 // A reference [...] is initialized by an expression [...] as follows:
5620 // If the initializer is not an expression, presumably we should reject,
5621 // but the standard fails to actually say so.
5622 else if (isa<InitListExpr>(Args[0]))
5623 SetFailed(FK_ParenthesizedListInitForReference);
5624 else
5625 TryReferenceInitialization(S, Entity, Kind, Args[0], *this);
5626 return;
5627 }
5628
5629 // - If the initializer is (), the object is value-initialized.
5630 if (Kind.getKind() == InitializationKind::IK_Value ||
5631 (Kind.getKind() == InitializationKind::IK_Direct && Args.empty())) {
5632 TryValueInitialization(S, Entity, Kind, *this);
5633 return;
5634 }
5635
5636 // Handle default initialization.
5637 if (Kind.getKind() == InitializationKind::IK_Default) {
5638 TryDefaultInitialization(S, Entity, Kind, *this);
5639 return;
5640 }
5641
5642 // - If the destination type is an array of characters, an array of
5643 // char16_t, an array of char32_t, or an array of wchar_t, and the
5644 // initializer is a string literal, see 8.5.2.
5645 // - Otherwise, if the destination type is an array, the program is
5646 // ill-formed.
5647 if (const ArrayType *DestAT = Context.getAsArrayType(DestType)) {
5648 if (Initializer && isa<VariableArrayType>(DestAT)) {
5649 SetFailed(FK_VariableLengthArrayHasInitializer);
5650 return;
5651 }
5652
5653 if (Initializer) {
5654 switch (IsStringInit(Initializer, DestAT, Context)) {
5655 case SIF_None:
5656 TryStringLiteralInitialization(S, Entity, Kind, Initializer, *this);
5657 return;
5658 case SIF_NarrowStringIntoWideChar:
5659 SetFailed(FK_NarrowStringIntoWideCharArray);
5660 return;
5661 case SIF_WideStringIntoChar:
5662 SetFailed(FK_WideStringIntoCharArray);
5663 return;
5664 case SIF_IncompatWideStringIntoWideChar:
5665 SetFailed(FK_IncompatWideStringIntoWideChar);
5666 return;
5667 case SIF_PlainStringIntoUTF8Char:
5668 SetFailed(FK_PlainStringIntoUTF8Char);
5669 return;
5670 case SIF_UTF8StringIntoPlainChar:
5671 SetFailed(FK_UTF8StringIntoPlainChar);
5672 return;
5673 case SIF_Other:
5674 break;
5675 }
5676 }
5677
5678 // Some kinds of initialization permit an array to be initialized from
5679 // another array of the same type, and perform elementwise initialization.
5680 if (Initializer && isa<ConstantArrayType>(DestAT) &&
5681 S.Context.hasSameUnqualifiedType(Initializer->getType(),
5682 Entity.getType()) &&
5683 canPerformArrayCopy(Entity)) {
5684 // If source is a prvalue, use it directly.
5685 if (Initializer->getValueKind() == VK_RValue) {
5686 AddArrayInitStep(DestType, /*IsGNUExtension*/false);
5687 return;
5688 }
5689
5690 // Emit element-at-a-time copy loop.
5691 InitializedEntity Element =
5692 InitializedEntity::InitializeElement(S.Context, 0, Entity);
5693 QualType InitEltT =
5694 Context.getAsArrayType(Initializer->getType())->getElementType();
5695 OpaqueValueExpr OVE(Initializer->getExprLoc(), InitEltT,
5696 Initializer->getValueKind(),
5697 Initializer->getObjectKind());
5698 Expr *OVEAsExpr = &OVE;
5699 InitializeFrom(S, Element, Kind, OVEAsExpr, TopLevelOfInitList,
5700 TreatUnavailableAsInvalid);
5701 if (!Failed())
5702 AddArrayInitLoopStep(Entity.getType(), InitEltT);
5703 return;
5704 }
5705
5706 // Note: as an GNU C extension, we allow initialization of an
5707 // array from a compound literal that creates an array of the same
5708 // type, so long as the initializer has no side effects.
5709 if (!S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus && Initializer &&
5710 isa<CompoundLiteralExpr>(Initializer->IgnoreParens()) &&
5711 Initializer->getType()->isArrayType()) {
5712 const ArrayType *SourceAT
5713 = Context.getAsArrayType(Initializer->getType());
5714 if (!hasCompatibleArrayTypes(S.Context, DestAT, SourceAT))
5715 SetFailed(FK_ArrayTypeMismatch);
5716 else if (Initializer->HasSideEffects(S.Context))
5717 SetFailed(FK_NonConstantArrayInit);
5718 else {
5719 AddArrayInitStep(DestType, /*IsGNUExtension*/true);
5720 }
5721 }
5722 // Note: as a GNU C++ extension, we allow list-initialization of a
5723 // class member of array type from a parenthesized initializer list.
5724 else if (S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus &&
5725 Entity.getKind() == InitializedEntity::EK_Member &&
5726 Initializer && isa<InitListExpr>(Initializer)) {
5727 TryListInitialization(S, Entity, Kind, cast<InitListExpr>(Initializer),
5728 *this, TreatUnavailableAsInvalid);
5729 AddParenthesizedArrayInitStep(DestType);
5730 } else if (DestAT->getElementType()->isCharType())
5731 SetFailed(FK_ArrayNeedsInitListOrStringLiteral);
5732 else if (IsWideCharCompatible(DestAT->getElementType(), Context))
5733 SetFailed(FK_ArrayNeedsInitListOrWideStringLiteral);
5734 else
5735 SetFailed(FK_ArrayNeedsInitList);
5736
5737 return;
5738 }
5739
5740 // Determine whether we should consider writeback conversions for
5741 // Objective-C ARC.
5742 bool allowObjCWritebackConversion = S.getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount &&
5743 Entity.isParameterKind();
5744
5745 // We're at the end of the line for C: it's either a write-back conversion
5746 // or it's a C assignment. There's no need to check anything else.
5747 if (!S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
5748 // If allowed, check whether this is an Objective-C writeback conversion.
5749 if (allowObjCWritebackConversion &&
5750 tryObjCWritebackConversion(S, *this, Entity, Initializer)) {
5751 return;
5752 }
5753
5754 if (TryOCLSamplerInitialization(S, *this, DestType, Initializer))
5755 return;
5756
5757 if (TryOCLZeroOpaqueTypeInitialization(S, *this, DestType, Initializer))
5758 return;
5759
5760 // Handle initialization in C
5761 AddCAssignmentStep(DestType);
5762 MaybeProduceObjCObject(S, *this, Entity);
5763 return;
5764 }
5765
5766 assert(S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus);
5767
5768 // - If the destination type is a (possibly cv-qualified) class type:
5769 if (DestType->isRecordType()) {
5770 // - If the initialization is direct-initialization, or if it is
5771 // copy-initialization where the cv-unqualified version of the
5772 // source type is the same class as, or a derived class of, the
5773 // class of the destination, constructors are considered. [...]
5774 if (Kind.getKind() == InitializationKind::IK_Direct ||
5775 (Kind.getKind() == InitializationKind::IK_Copy &&
5776 (Context.hasSameUnqualifiedType(SourceType, DestType) ||
5777 S.IsDerivedFrom(Initializer->getBeginLoc(), SourceType, DestType))))
5778 TryConstructorInitialization(S, Entity, Kind, Args,
5779 DestType, DestType, *this);
5780 // - Otherwise (i.e., for the remaining copy-initialization cases),
5781 // user-defined conversion sequences that can convert from the source
5782 // type to the destination type or (when a conversion function is
5783 // used) to a derived class thereof are enumerated as described in
5784 // 13.3.1.4, and the best one is chosen through overload resolution
5785 // (13.3).
5786 else
5787 TryUserDefinedConversion(S, DestType, Kind, Initializer, *this,
5788 TopLevelOfInitList);
5789 return;
5790 }
5791
5792 assert(Args.size() >= 1 && "Zero-argument case handled above");
5793
5794 // The remaining cases all need a source type.
5795 if (Args.size() > 1) {
5796 SetFailed(FK_TooManyInitsForScalar);
5797 return;
5798 } else if (isa<InitListExpr>(Args[0])) {
5799 SetFailed(FK_ParenthesizedListInitForScalar);
5800 return;
5801 }
5802
5803 // - Otherwise, if the source type is a (possibly cv-qualified) class
5804 // type, conversion functions are considered.
5805 if (!SourceType.isNull() && SourceType->isRecordType()) {
5806 // For a conversion to _Atomic(T) from either T or a class type derived
5807 // from T, initialize the T object then convert to _Atomic type.
5808 bool NeedAtomicConversion = false;
5809 if (const AtomicType *Atomic = DestType->getAs<AtomicType>()) {
5810 if (Context.hasSameUnqualifiedType(SourceType, Atomic->getValueType()) ||
5811 S.IsDerivedFrom(Initializer->getBeginLoc(), SourceType,
5812 Atomic->getValueType())) {
5813 DestType = Atomic->getValueType();
5814 NeedAtomicConversion = true;
5815 }
5816 }
5817
5818 TryUserDefinedConversion(S, DestType, Kind, Initializer, *this,
5819 TopLevelOfInitList);
5820 MaybeProduceObjCObject(S, *this, Entity);
5821 if (!Failed() && NeedAtomicConversion)
5822 AddAtomicConversionStep(Entity.getType());
5823 return;
5824 }
5825
5826 // - Otherwise, the initial value of the object being initialized is the
5827 // (possibly converted) value of the initializer expression. Standard
5828 // conversions (Clause 4) will be used, if necessary, to convert the
5829 // initializer expression to the cv-unqualified version of the
5830 // destination type; no user-defined conversions are considered.
5831
5832 ImplicitConversionSequence ICS
5833 = S.TryImplicitConversion(Initializer, DestType,
5834 /*SuppressUserConversions*/true,
5835 /*AllowExplicitConversions*/ false,
5836 /*InOverloadResolution*/ false,
5837 /*CStyle=*/Kind.isCStyleOrFunctionalCast(),
5838 allowObjCWritebackConversion);
5839
5840 if (ICS.isStandard() &&
5841 ICS.Standard.Second == ICK_Writeback_Conversion) {
5842 // Objective-C ARC writeback conversion.
5843
5844 // We should copy unless we're passing to an argument explicitly
5845 // marked 'out'.
5846 bool ShouldCopy = true;
5847 if (ParmVarDecl *Param = cast_or_null<ParmVarDecl>(Entity.getDecl()))
5848 ShouldCopy = (Param->getObjCDeclQualifier() != ParmVarDecl::OBJC_TQ_Out);
5849
5850 // If there was an lvalue adjustment, add it as a separate conversion.
5851 if (ICS.Standard.First == ICK_Array_To_Pointer ||
5852 ICS.Standard.First == ICK_Lvalue_To_Rvalue) {
5853 ImplicitConversionSequence LvalueICS;
5854 LvalueICS.setStandard(ImplicitConversionSequence::MemsetToZero);
5855 LvalueICS.Standard.setAsIdentityConversion();
5856 LvalueICS.Standard.setAllToTypes(ICS.Standard.getToType(0));
5857 LvalueICS.Standard.First = ICS.Standard.First;
5858 AddConversionSequenceStep(LvalueICS, ICS.Standard.getToType(0));
5859 }
5860
5861 AddPassByIndirectCopyRestoreStep(DestType, ShouldCopy);
5862 } else if (ICS.isBad()) {
5863 DeclAccessPair dap;
5864 if (isLibstdcxxPointerReturnFalseHack(S, Entity, Initializer)) {
5865 AddZeroInitializationStep(Entity.getType());
5866 } else if (Initializer->getType() == Context.OverloadTy &&
5867 !S.ResolveAddressOfOverloadedFunction(Initializer, DestType,
5868 false, dap))
5869 SetFailed(InitializationSequence::FK_AddressOfOverloadFailed);
5870 else if (Initializer->getType()->isFunctionType() &&
5871 isExprAnUnaddressableFunction(S, Initializer))
5872 SetFailed(InitializationSequence::FK_AddressOfUnaddressableFunction);
5873 else
5874 SetFailed(InitializationSequence::FK_ConversionFailed);
5875 } else {
5876 if (ICS.isStandard() && ICS.Standard.Third == ICK_Qualification) {
5877 if (SourceType->isCHERICapabilityType(Context) &&
5878 !DestType->isCHERICapabilityType(Context)) {
5879 SetFailed(InitializationSequence::FK_ConversionFromCapabilityFailed);
5880 return;
5881 } else if (DestType->isCHERICapabilityType(Context) &&
5882 !SourceType->isCHERICapabilityType(Context)) {
5883 // pointer-to-capability conversions are checked elsewhere
5884 }
5885 }
5886 AddConversionSequenceStep(ICS, DestType, TopLevelOfInitList);
5887
5888 MaybeProduceObjCObject(S, *this, Entity);
5889 }
5890}
5891
5892InitializationSequence::~InitializationSequence() {
5893 for (auto &S : Steps)
5894 S.Destroy();
5895}
5896
5897//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
5898// Perform initialization
5899//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
5900static Sema::AssignmentAction
5901getAssignmentAction(const InitializedEntity &Entity, bool Diagnose = false) {
5902 switch(Entity.getKind()) {
5903 case InitializedEntity::EK_Variable:
5904 case InitializedEntity::EK_New:
5905 case InitializedEntity::EK_Exception:
5906 case InitializedEntity::EK_Base:
5907 case InitializedEntity::EK_Delegating:
5908 return Sema::AA_Initializing;
5909
5910 case InitializedEntity::EK_Parameter:
5911 if (Entity.getDecl() &&
5912 isa<ObjCMethodDecl>(Entity.getDecl()->getDeclContext()))
5913 return Sema::AA_Sending;
5914
5915 return Sema::AA_Passing;
5916
5917 case InitializedEntity::EK_Parameter_CF_Audited:
5918 if (Entity.getDecl() &&
5919 isa<ObjCMethodDecl>(Entity.getDecl()->getDeclContext()))
5920 return Sema::AA_Sending;
5921
5922 return !Diagnose ? Sema::AA_Passing : Sema::AA_Passing_CFAudited;
5923
5924 case InitializedEntity::EK_Result:
5925 case InitializedEntity::EK_StmtExprResult: // FIXME: Not quite right.
5926 return Sema::AA_Returning;
5927
5928 case InitializedEntity::EK_Temporary:
5929 case InitializedEntity::EK_RelatedResult:
5930 // FIXME: Can we tell apart casting vs. converting?
5931 return Sema::AA_Casting;
5932
5933 case InitializedEntity::EK_Member:
5934 case InitializedEntity::EK_Binding:
5935 case InitializedEntity::EK_ArrayElement:
5936 case InitializedEntity::EK_VectorElement:
5937 case InitializedEntity::EK_ComplexElement:
5938 case InitializedEntity::EK_BlockElement:
5939 case InitializedEntity::EK_LambdaToBlockConversionBlockElement:
5940 case InitializedEntity::EK_LambdaCapture:
5941 case InitializedEntity::EK_CompoundLiteralInit:
5942 return Sema::AA_Initializing;
5943 }
5944
5945 llvm_unreachable("Invalid EntityKind!");
5946}
5947
5948/// Whether we should bind a created object as a temporary when
5949/// initializing the given entity.
5950static bool shouldBindAsTemporary(const InitializedEntity &Entity) {
5951 switch (Entity.getKind()) {
5952 case InitializedEntity::EK_ArrayElement:
5953 case InitializedEntity::EK_Member:
5954 case InitializedEntity::EK_Result:
5955 case InitializedEntity::EK_StmtExprResult:
5956 case InitializedEntity::EK_New:
5957 case InitializedEntity::EK_Variable:
5958 case InitializedEntity::EK_Base:
5959 case InitializedEntity::EK_Delegating:
5960 case InitializedEntity::EK_VectorElement:
5961 case InitializedEntity::EK_ComplexElement:
5962 case InitializedEntity::EK_Exception:
5963 case InitializedEntity::EK_BlockElement:
5964 case InitializedEntity::EK_LambdaToBlockConversionBlockElement:
5965 case InitializedEntity::EK_LambdaCapture:
5966 case InitializedEntity::EK_CompoundLiteralInit:
5967 return false;
5968
5969 case InitializedEntity::EK_Parameter:
5970 case InitializedEntity::EK_Parameter_CF_Audited:
5971 case InitializedEntity::EK_Temporary:
5972 case InitializedEntity::EK_RelatedResult:
5973 case InitializedEntity::EK_Binding:
5974 return true;
5975 }
5976
5977 llvm_unreachable("missed an InitializedEntity kind?");
5978}
5979
5980/// Whether the given entity, when initialized with an object
5981/// created for that initialization, requires destruction.
5982static bool shouldDestroyEntity(const InitializedEntity &Entity) {
5983 switch (Entity.getKind()) {
5984 case InitializedEntity::EK_Result:
5985 case InitializedEntity::EK_StmtExprResult:
5986 case InitializedEntity::EK_New:
5987 case InitializedEntity::EK_Base:
5988 case InitializedEntity::EK_Delegating:
5989 case InitializedEntity::EK_VectorElement:
5990 case InitializedEntity::EK_ComplexElement:
5991 case InitializedEntity::EK_BlockElement:
5992 case InitializedEntity::EK_LambdaToBlockConversionBlockElement:
5993 case InitializedEntity::EK_LambdaCapture:
5994 return false;
5995
5996 case InitializedEntity::EK_Member:
5997 case InitializedEntity::EK_Binding:
5998 case InitializedEntity::EK_Variable:
5999 case InitializedEntity::EK_Parameter:
6000 case InitializedEntity::EK_Parameter_CF_Audited:
6001 case InitializedEntity::EK_Temporary:
6002 case InitializedEntity::EK_ArrayElement:
6003 case InitializedEntity::EK_Exception:
6004 case InitializedEntity::EK_CompoundLiteralInit:
6005 case InitializedEntity::EK_RelatedResult:
6006 return true;
6007 }
6008
6009 llvm_unreachable("missed an InitializedEntity kind?");
6010}
6011
6012/// Get the location at which initialization diagnostics should appear.
6013static SourceLocation getInitializationLoc(const InitializedEntity &Entity,
6014 Expr *Initializer) {
6015 switch (Entity.getKind()) {
6016 case InitializedEntity::EK_Result:
6017 case InitializedEntity::EK_StmtExprResult:
6018 return Entity.getReturnLoc();
6019
6020 case InitializedEntity::EK_Exception:
6021 return Entity.getThrowLoc();
6022
6023 case InitializedEntity::EK_Variable:
6024 case InitializedEntity::EK_Binding:
6025 return Entity.getDecl()->getLocation();
6026
6027 case InitializedEntity::EK_LambdaCapture:
6028 return Entity.getCaptureLoc();
6029
6030 case InitializedEntity::EK_ArrayElement:
6031 case InitializedEntity::EK_Member:
6032 case InitializedEntity::EK_Parameter:
6033 case InitializedEntity::EK_Parameter_CF_Audited:
6034 case InitializedEntity::EK_Temporary:
6035 case InitializedEntity::EK_New:
6036 case InitializedEntity::EK_Base:
6037 case InitializedEntity::EK_Delegating:
6038 case InitializedEntity::EK_VectorElement:
6039 case InitializedEntity::EK_ComplexElement:
6040 case InitializedEntity::EK_BlockElement:
6041 case InitializedEntity::EK_LambdaToBlockConversionBlockElement:
6042 case InitializedEntity::EK_CompoundLiteralInit:
6043 case InitializedEntity::EK_RelatedResult:
6044 return Initializer->getBeginLoc();
6045 }
6046 llvm_unreachable("missed an InitializedEntity kind?");
6047}
6048
6049/// Make a (potentially elidable) temporary copy of the object
6050/// provided by the given initializer by calling the appropriate copy
6051/// constructor.
6052///
6053/// \param S The Sema object used for type-checking.
6054///
6055/// \param T The type of the temporary object, which must either be
6056/// the type of the initializer expression or a superclass thereof.
6057///
6058/// \param Entity The entity being initialized.
6059///
6060/// \param CurInit The initializer expression.
6061///
6062/// \param IsExtraneousCopy Whether this is an "extraneous" copy that
6063/// is permitted in C++03 (but not C++0x) when binding a reference to
6064/// an rvalue.
6065///
6066/// \returns An expression that copies the initializer expression into
6067/// a temporary object, or an error expression if a copy could not be
6068/// created.
6069static ExprResult CopyObject(Sema &S,
6070 QualType T,
6071 const InitializedEntity &Entity,
6072 ExprResult CurInit,
6073 bool IsExtraneousCopy) {
6074 if (CurInit.isInvalid())
6075 return CurInit;
6076 // Determine which class type we're copying to.
6077 Expr *CurInitExpr = (Expr *)CurInit.get();
6078 CXXRecordDecl *Class = nullptr;
6079 if (const RecordType *Record = T->getAs<RecordType>())
6080 Class = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(Record->getDecl());
6081 if (!Class)
6082 return CurInit;
6083
6084 SourceLocation Loc = getInitializationLoc(Entity, CurInit.get());
6085
6086 // Make sure that the type we are copying is complete.
6087 if (S.RequireCompleteType(Loc, T, diag::err_temp_copy_incomplete))
6088 return CurInit;
6089
6090 // Perform overload resolution using the class's constructors. Per
6091 // C++11 [dcl.init]p16, second bullet for class types, this initialization
6092 // is direct-initialization.
6093 OverloadCandidateSet CandidateSet(Loc, OverloadCandidateSet::CSK_Normal);
6094 DeclContext::lookup_result Ctors = S.LookupConstructors(Class);
6095
6096 OverloadCandidateSet::iterator Best;
6097 switch (ResolveConstructorOverload(
6098 S, Loc, CurInitExpr, CandidateSet, T, Ctors, Best,
6099 /*CopyInitializing=*/false, /*AllowExplicit=*/true,
6100 /*OnlyListConstructors=*/false, /*IsListInit=*/false,
6101 /*SecondStepOfCopyInit=*/true)) {
6102 case OR_Success:
6103 break;
6104
6105 case OR_No_Viable_Function:
6106 CandidateSet.NoteCandidates(
6107 PartialDiagnosticAt(
6108 Loc, S.PDiag(IsExtraneousCopy && !S.isSFINAEContext()
6109 ? diag::ext_rvalue_to_reference_temp_copy_no_viable
6110 : diag::err_temp_copy_no_viable)
6111 << (int)Entity.getKind() << CurInitExpr->getType()
6112 << CurInitExpr->getSourceRange()),
6113 S, OCD_AllCandidates, CurInitExpr);
6114 if (!IsExtraneousCopy || S.isSFINAEContext())
6115 return ExprError();
6116 return CurInit;
6117
6118 case OR_Ambiguous:
6119 CandidateSet.NoteCandidates(
6120 PartialDiagnosticAt(Loc, S.PDiag(diag::err_temp_copy_ambiguous)
6121 << (int)Entity.getKind()
6122 << CurInitExpr->getType()
6123 << CurInitExpr->getSourceRange()),
6124 S, OCD_ViableCandidates, CurInitExpr);
6125 return ExprError();
6126
6127 case OR_Deleted:
6128 S.Diag(Loc, diag::err_temp_copy_deleted)
6129 << (int)Entity.getKind() << CurInitExpr->getType()
6130 << CurInitExpr->getSourceRange();
6131 S.NoteDeletedFunction(Best->Function);
6132 return ExprError();
6133 }
6134
6135 bool HadMultipleCandidates = CandidateSet.size() > 1;
6136
6137 CXXConstructorDecl *Constructor = cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(Best->Function);
6138 SmallVector<Expr*, 8> ConstructorArgs;
6139 CurInit.get(); // Ownership transferred into MultiExprArg, below.
6140
6141 S.CheckConstructorAccess(Loc, Constructor, Best->FoundDecl, Entity,
6142 IsExtraneousCopy);
6143
6144 if (IsExtraneousCopy) {
6145 // If this is a totally extraneous copy for C++03 reference
6146 // binding purposes, just return the original initialization
6147 // expression. We don't generate an (elided) copy operation here
6148 // because doing so would require us to pass down a flag to avoid
6149 // infinite recursion, where each step adds another extraneous,
6150 // elidable copy.
6151
6152 // Instantiate the default arguments of any extra parameters in
6153 // the selected copy constructor, as if we were going to create a
6154 // proper call to the copy constructor.
6155 for (unsigned I = 1, N = Constructor->getNumParams(); I != N; ++I) {
6156 ParmVarDecl *Parm = Constructor->getParamDecl(I);
6157 if (S.RequireCompleteType(Loc, Parm->getType(),
6158 diag::err_call_incomplete_argument))
6159 break;
6160
6161 // Build the default argument expression; we don't actually care
6162 // if this succeeds or not, because this routine will complain
6163 // if there was a problem.
6164 S.BuildCXXDefaultArgExpr(Loc, Constructor, Parm);
6165 }
6166
6167 return CurInitExpr;
6168 }
6169
6170 // Determine the arguments required to actually perform the
6171 // constructor call (we might have derived-to-base conversions, or
6172 // the copy constructor may have default arguments).
6173 if (S.CompleteConstructorCall(Constructor, CurInitExpr, Loc, ConstructorArgs))
6174 return ExprError();
6175
6176 // C++0x [class.copy]p32:
6177 // When certain criteria are met, an implementation is allowed to
6178 // omit the copy/move construction of a class object, even if the
6179 // copy/move constructor and/or destructor for the object have
6180 // side effects. [...]
6181 // - when a temporary class object that has not been bound to a
6182 // reference (12.2) would be copied/moved to a class object
6183 // with the same cv-unqualified type, the copy/move operation
6184 // can be omitted by constructing the temporary object
6185 // directly into the target of the omitted copy/move
6186 //
6187 // Note that the other three bullets are handled elsewhere. Copy
6188 // elision for return statements and throw expressions are handled as part
6189 // of constructor initialization, while copy elision for exception handlers
6190 // is handled by the run-time.
6191 //
6192 // FIXME: If the function parameter is not the same type as the temporary, we
6193 // should still be able to elide the copy, but we don't have a way to
6194 // represent in the AST how much should be elided in this case.
6195 bool Elidable =
6196 CurInitExpr->isTemporaryObject(S.Context, Class) &&
6197 S.Context.hasSameUnqualifiedType(
6198 Best->Function->getParamDecl(0)->getType().getNonReferenceType(),
6199 CurInitExpr->getType());
6200
6201 // Actually perform the constructor call.
6202 CurInit = S.BuildCXXConstructExpr(Loc, T, Best->FoundDecl, Constructor,
6203 Elidable,
6204 ConstructorArgs,
6205 HadMultipleCandidates,
6206 /*ListInit*/ false,
6207 /*StdInitListInit*/ false,
6208 /*ZeroInit*/ false,
6209 CXXConstructExpr::CK_Complete,
6210 SourceRange());
6211
6212 // If we're supposed to bind temporaries, do so.
6213 if (!CurInit.isInvalid() && shouldBindAsTemporary(Entity))
6214 CurInit = S.MaybeBindToTemporary(CurInit.getAs<Expr>());
6215 return CurInit;
6216}
6217
6218/// Check whether elidable copy construction for binding a reference to
6219/// a temporary would have succeeded if we were building in C++98 mode, for
6220/// -Wc++98-compat.
6221static void CheckCXX98CompatAccessibleCopy(Sema &S,
6222 const InitializedEntity &Entity,
6223 Expr *CurInitExpr) {
6224 assert(S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11);
6225
6226 const RecordType *Record = CurInitExpr->getType()->getAs<RecordType>();
6227 if (!Record)
6228 return;
6229
6230 SourceLocation Loc = getInitializationLoc(Entity, CurInitExpr);
6231 if (S.Diags.isIgnored(diag::warn_cxx98_compat_temp_copy, Loc))
6232 return;
6233
6234 // Find constructors which would have been considered.
6235 OverloadCandidateSet CandidateSet(Loc, OverloadCandidateSet::CSK_Normal);
6236 DeclContext::lookup_result Ctors =
6237 S.LookupConstructors(cast<CXXRecordDecl>(Record->getDecl()));
6238
6239 // Perform overload resolution.
6240 OverloadCandidateSet::iterator Best;
6241 OverloadingResult OR = ResolveConstructorOverload(
6242 S, Loc, CurInitExpr, CandidateSet, CurInitExpr->getType(), Ctors, Best,
6243 /*CopyInitializing=*/false, /*AllowExplicit=*/true,
6244 /*OnlyListConstructors=*/false, /*IsListInit=*/false,
6245 /*SecondStepOfCopyInit=*/true);
6246
6247 PartialDiagnostic Diag = S.PDiag(diag::warn_cxx98_compat_temp_copy)
6248 << OR << (int)Entity.getKind() << CurInitExpr->getType()
6249 << CurInitExpr->getSourceRange();
6250
6251 switch (OR) {
6252 case OR_Success:
6253 S.CheckConstructorAccess(Loc, cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(Best->Function),
6254 Best->FoundDecl, Entity, Diag);
6255 // FIXME: Check default arguments as far as that's possible.
6256 break;
6257
6258 case OR_No_Viable_Function:
6259 CandidateSet.NoteCandidates(PartialDiagnosticAt(Loc, Diag), S,
6260 OCD_AllCandidates, CurInitExpr);
6261 break;
6262
6263 case OR_Ambiguous:
6264 CandidateSet.NoteCandidates(PartialDiagnosticAt(Loc, Diag), S,
6265 OCD_ViableCandidates, CurInitExpr);
6266 break;
6267
6268 case OR_Deleted:
6269 S.Diag(Loc, Diag);
6270 S.NoteDeletedFunction(Best->Function);
6271 break;
6272 }
6273}
6274
6275void InitializationSequence::PrintInitLocationNote(Sema &S,
6276 const InitializedEntity &Entity) {
6277 if (Entity.isParameterKind() && Entity.getDecl()) {
6278 if (Entity.getDecl()->getLocation().isInvalid())
6279 return;
6280
6281 if (Entity.getDecl()->getDeclName())
6282 S.Diag(Entity.getDecl()->getLocation(), diag::note_parameter_named_here)
6283 << Entity.getDecl()->getDeclName();
6284 else
6285 S.Diag(Entity.getDecl()->getLocation(), diag::note_parameter_here);
6286 }
6287 else if (Entity.getKind() == InitializedEntity::EK_RelatedResult &&
6288 Entity.getMethodDecl())
6289 S.Diag(Entity.getMethodDecl()->getLocation(),
6290 diag::note_method_return_type_change)
6291 << Entity.getMethodDecl()->getDeclName();
6292}
6293
6294/// Returns true if the parameters describe a constructor initialization of
6295/// an explicit temporary object, e.g. "Point(x, y)".
6296static bool isExplicitTemporary(const InitializedEntity &Entity,
6297 const InitializationKind &Kind,
6298 unsigned NumArgs) {
6299 switch (Entity.getKind()) {
6300 case InitializedEntity::EK_Temporary:
6301 case InitializedEntity::EK_CompoundLiteralInit:
6302 case InitializedEntity::EK_RelatedResult:
6303 break;
6304 default:
6305 return false;
6306 }
6307
6308 switch (Kind.getKind()) {
6309 case InitializationKind::IK_DirectList:
6310 return true;
6311 // FIXME: Hack to work around cast weirdness.
6312 case InitializationKind::IK_Direct:
6313 case InitializationKind::IK_Value:
6314 return NumArgs != 1;
6315 default:
6316 return false;
6317 }
6318}
6319
6320static ExprResult
6321PerformConstructorInitialization(Sema &S,
6322 const InitializedEntity &Entity,
6323 const InitializationKind &Kind,
6324 MultiExprArg Args,
6325 const InitializationSequence::Step& Step,
6326 bool &ConstructorInitRequiresZeroInit,
6327 bool IsListInitialization,
6328 bool IsStdInitListInitialization,
6329 SourceLocation LBraceLoc,
6330 SourceLocation RBraceLoc) {
6331 unsigned NumArgs = Args.size();
6332 CXXConstructorDecl *Constructor
6333 = cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(Step.Function.Function);
6334 bool HadMultipleCandidates = Step.Function.HadMultipleCandidates;
6335
6336 // Build a call to the selected constructor.
6337 SmallVector<Expr*, 8> ConstructorArgs;
6338 SourceLocation Loc = (Kind.isCopyInit() && Kind.getEqualLoc().isValid())
6339 ? Kind.getEqualLoc()
6340 : Kind.getLocation();
6341
6342 if (Kind.getKind() == InitializationKind::IK_Default) {
6343 // Force even a trivial, implicit default constructor to be
6344 // semantically checked. We do this explicitly because we don't build
6345 // the definition for completely trivial constructors.
6346 assert(Constructor->getParent() && "No parent class for constructor.");
6347 if (Constructor->isDefaulted() && Constructor->isDefaultConstructor() &&
6348 Constructor->isTrivial() && !Constructor->isUsed(false))
6349 S.DefineImplicitDefaultConstructor(Loc, Constructor);
6350 }
6351
6352 ExprResult CurInit((Expr *)nullptr);
6353
6354 // C++ [over.match.copy]p1:
6355 // - When initializing a temporary to be bound to the first parameter
6356 // of a constructor that takes a reference to possibly cv-qualified
6357 // T as its first argument, called with a single argument in the
6358 // context of direct-initialization, explicit conversion functions
6359 // are also considered.
6360 bool AllowExplicitConv =
6361 Kind.AllowExplicit() && !Kind.isCopyInit() && Args.size() == 1 &&
6362 hasCopyOrMoveCtorParam(S.Context,
6363 getConstructorInfo(Step.Function.FoundDecl));
6364
6365 // Determine the arguments required to actually perform the constructor
6366 // call.
6367 if (S.CompleteConstructorCall(Constructor, Args,
6368 Loc, ConstructorArgs,
6369 AllowExplicitConv,
6370 IsListInitialization))
6371 return ExprError();
6372
6373
6374 if (isExplicitTemporary(Entity, Kind, NumArgs)) {
6375 // An explicitly-constructed temporary, e.g., X(1, 2).
6376 if (S.DiagnoseUseOfDecl(Constructor, Loc))
6377 return ExprError();
6378
6379 TypeSourceInfo *TSInfo = Entity.getTypeSourceInfo();
6380 if (!TSInfo)
6381 TSInfo = S.Context.getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(Entity.getType(), Loc);
6382 SourceRange ParenOrBraceRange =
6383 (Kind.getKind() == InitializationKind::IK_DirectList)
6384 ? SourceRange(LBraceLoc, RBraceLoc)
6385 : Kind.getParenOrBraceRange();
6386
6387 if (auto *Shadow = dyn_cast<ConstructorUsingShadowDecl>(
6388 Step.Function.FoundDecl.getDecl())) {
6389 Constructor = S.findInheritingConstructor(Loc, Constructor, Shadow);
6390 if (S.DiagnoseUseOfDecl(Constructor, Loc))
6391 return ExprError();
6392 }
6393 S.MarkFunctionReferenced(Loc, Constructor);
6394
6395 CurInit = CXXTemporaryObjectExpr::Create(
6396 S.Context, Constructor,
6397 Entity.getType().getNonLValueExprType(S.Context), TSInfo,
6398 ConstructorArgs, ParenOrBraceRange, HadMultipleCandidates,
6399 IsListInitialization, IsStdInitListInitialization,
6400 ConstructorInitRequiresZeroInit);
6401 } else {
6402 CXXConstructExpr::ConstructionKind ConstructKind =
6403 CXXConstructExpr::CK_Complete;
6404
6405 if (Entity.getKind() == InitializedEntity::EK_Base) {
6406 ConstructKind = Entity.getBaseSpecifier()->isVirtual() ?
6407 CXXConstructExpr::CK_VirtualBase :
6408 CXXConstructExpr::CK_NonVirtualBase;
6409 } else if (Entity.getKind() == InitializedEntity::EK_Delegating) {
6410 ConstructKind = CXXConstructExpr::CK_Delegating;
6411 }
6412
6413 // Only get the parenthesis or brace range if it is a list initialization or
6414 // direct construction.
6415 SourceRange ParenOrBraceRange;
6416 if (IsListInitialization)
6417 ParenOrBraceRange = SourceRange(LBraceLoc, RBraceLoc);
6418 else if (Kind.getKind() == InitializationKind::IK_Direct)
6419 ParenOrBraceRange = Kind.getParenOrBraceRange();
6420
6421 // If the entity allows NRVO, mark the construction as elidable
6422 // unconditionally.
6423 if (Entity.allowsNRVO())
6424 CurInit = S.BuildCXXConstructExpr(Loc, Step.Type,
6425 Step.Function.FoundDecl,
6426 Constructor, /*Elidable=*/true,
6427 ConstructorArgs,
6428 HadMultipleCandidates,
6429 IsListInitialization,
6430 IsStdInitListInitialization,
6431 ConstructorInitRequiresZeroInit,
6432 ConstructKind,
6433 ParenOrBraceRange);
6434 else
6435 CurInit = S.BuildCXXConstructExpr(Loc, Step.Type,
6436 Step.Function.FoundDecl,
6437 Constructor,
6438 ConstructorArgs,
6439 HadMultipleCandidates,
6440 IsListInitialization,
6441 IsStdInitListInitialization,
6442 ConstructorInitRequiresZeroInit,
6443 ConstructKind,
6444 ParenOrBraceRange);
6445 }
6446 if (CurInit.isInvalid())
6447 return ExprError();
6448
6449 // Only check access if all of that succeeded.
6450 S.CheckConstructorAccess(Loc, Constructor, Step.Function.FoundDecl, Entity);
6451 if (S.DiagnoseUseOfDecl(Step.Function.FoundDecl, Loc))
6452 return ExprError();
6453
6454 if (const ArrayType *AT = S.Context.getAsArrayType(Entity.getType()))
6455 if (checkDestructorReference(S.Context.getBaseElementType(AT), Loc, S))
6456 return ExprError();
6457
6458 if (shouldBindAsTemporary(Entity))
6459 CurInit = S.MaybeBindToTemporary(CurInit.get());
6460
6461 return CurInit;
6462}
6463
6464namespace {
6465enum LifetimeKind {
6466 /// The lifetime of a temporary bound to this entity ends at the end of the
6467 /// full-expression, and that's (probably) fine.
6468 LK_FullExpression,
6469
6470 /// The lifetime of a temporary bound to this entity is extended to the
6471 /// lifeitme of the entity itself.
6472 LK_Extended,
6473
6474 /// The lifetime of a temporary bound to this entity probably ends too soon,
6475 /// because the entity is allocated in a new-expression.
6476 LK_New,
6477
6478 /// The lifetime of a temporary bound to this entity ends too soon, because
6479 /// the entity is a return object.
6480 LK_Return,
6481
