6482 /// The lifetime of a temporary bound to this entity ends too soon, because
6483 /// the entity is the result of a statement expression.
6484 LK_StmtExprResult,
6485
6486 /// This is a mem-initializer: if it would extend a temporary (other than via
6487 /// a default member initializer), the program is ill-formed.
6488 LK_MemInitializer,
6489};
6490using LifetimeResult =
6491 llvm::PointerIntPair<const InitializedEntity *, 3, LifetimeKind>;
6492}
6493
6494/// Determine the declaration which an initialized entity ultimately refers to,
6495/// for the purpose of lifetime-extending a temporary bound to a reference in
6496/// the initialization of \p Entity.
6497static LifetimeResult getEntityLifetime(
6498 const InitializedEntity *Entity,
6499 const InitializedEntity *InitField = nullptr) {
6500 // C++11 [class.temporary]p5:
6501 switch (Entity->getKind()) {
6502 case InitializedEntity::EK_Variable:
6503 // The temporary [...] persists for the lifetime of the reference
6504 return {Entity, LK_Extended};
6505
6506 case InitializedEntity::EK_Member:
6507 // For subobjects, we look at the complete object.
6508 if (Entity->getParent())
6509 return getEntityLifetime(Entity->getParent(), Entity);
6510
6511 // except:
6512 // C++17 [class.base.init]p8:
6513 // A temporary expression bound to a reference member in a
6514 // mem-initializer is ill-formed.
6515 // C++17 [class.base.init]p11:
6516 // A temporary expression bound to a reference member from a
6517 // default member initializer is ill-formed.
6518 //
6519 // The context of p11 and its example suggest that it's only the use of a
6520 // default member initializer from a constructor that makes the program
6521 // ill-formed, not its mere existence, and that it can even be used by
6522 // aggregate initialization.
6523 return {Entity, Entity->isDefaultMemberInitializer() ? LK_Extended
6524 : LK_MemInitializer};
6525
6526 case InitializedEntity::EK_Binding:
6527 // Per [dcl.decomp]p3, the binding is treated as a variable of reference
6528 // type.
6529 return {Entity, LK_Extended};
6530
6531 case InitializedEntity::EK_Parameter:
6532 case InitializedEntity::EK_Parameter_CF_Audited:
6533 // -- A temporary bound to a reference parameter in a function call
6534 // persists until the completion of the full-expression containing
6535 // the call.
6536 return {nullptr, LK_FullExpression};
6537
6538 case InitializedEntity::EK_Result:
6539 // -- The lifetime of a temporary bound to the returned value in a
6540 // function return statement is not extended; the temporary is
6541 // destroyed at the end of the full-expression in the return statement.
6542 return {nullptr, LK_Return};
6543
6544 case InitializedEntity::EK_StmtExprResult:
6545 // FIXME: Should we lifetime-extend through the result of a statement
6546 // expression?
6547 return {nullptr, LK_StmtExprResult};
6548
6549 case InitializedEntity::EK_New:
6550 // -- A temporary bound to a reference in a new-initializer persists
6551 // until the completion of the full-expression containing the
6552 // new-initializer.
6553 return {nullptr, LK_New};
6554
6555 case InitializedEntity::EK_Temporary:
6556 case InitializedEntity::EK_CompoundLiteralInit:
6557 case InitializedEntity::EK_RelatedResult:
6558 // We don't yet know the storage duration of the surrounding temporary.
6559 // Assume it's got full-expression duration for now, it will patch up our
6560 // storage duration if that's not correct.
6561 return {nullptr, LK_FullExpression};
6562
6563 case InitializedEntity::EK_ArrayElement:
6564 // For subobjects, we look at the complete object.
6565 return getEntityLifetime(Entity->getParent(), InitField);
6566
6567 case InitializedEntity::EK_Base:
6568 // For subobjects, we look at the complete object.
6569 if (Entity->getParent())
6570 return getEntityLifetime(Entity->getParent(), InitField);
6571 return {InitField, LK_MemInitializer};
6572
6573 case InitializedEntity::EK_Delegating:
6574 // We can reach this case for aggregate initialization in a constructor:
6575 // struct A { int &&r; };
6576 // struct B : A { B() : A{0} {} };
6577 // In this case, use the outermost field decl as the context.
6578 return {InitField, LK_MemInitializer};
6579
6580 case InitializedEntity::EK_BlockElement:
6581 case InitializedEntity::EK_LambdaToBlockConversionBlockElement:
6582 case InitializedEntity::EK_LambdaCapture:
6583 case InitializedEntity::EK_VectorElement:
6584 case InitializedEntity::EK_ComplexElement:
6585 return {nullptr, LK_FullExpression};
6586
6587 case InitializedEntity::EK_Exception:
6588 // FIXME: Can we diagnose lifetime problems with exceptions?
6589 return {nullptr, LK_FullExpression};
6590 }
6591 llvm_unreachable("unknown entity kind");
6592}
6593
6594namespace {
6595enum ReferenceKind {
6596 /// Lifetime would be extended by a reference binding to a temporary.
6597 RK_ReferenceBinding,
6598 /// Lifetime would be extended by a std::initializer_list object binding to
6599 /// its backing array.
6600 RK_StdInitializerList,
6601};
6602
6603/// A temporary or local variable. This will be one of:
6604/// * A MaterializeTemporaryExpr.
6605/// * A DeclRefExpr whose declaration is a local.
6606/// * An AddrLabelExpr.
6607/// * A BlockExpr for a block with captures.
6608using Local = Expr*;
6609
6610/// Expressions we stepped over when looking for the local state. Any steps
6611/// that would inhibit lifetime extension or take us out of subexpressions of
6612/// the initializer are included.
6613struct IndirectLocalPathEntry {
6614 enum EntryKind {
6615 DefaultInit,
6616 AddressOf,
6617 VarInit,
6618 LValToRVal,
6619 LifetimeBoundCall,
6620 } Kind;
6621 Expr *E;
6622 const Decl *D = nullptr;
6623 IndirectLocalPathEntry() {}
6624 IndirectLocalPathEntry(EntryKind K, Expr *E) : Kind(K), E(E) {}
6625 IndirectLocalPathEntry(EntryKind K, Expr *E, const Decl *D)
6626 : Kind(K), E(E), D(D) {}
6627};
6628
6629using IndirectLocalPath = llvm::SmallVectorImpl<IndirectLocalPathEntry>;
6630
6631struct RevertToOldSizeRAII {
6632 IndirectLocalPath &Path;
6633 unsigned OldSize = Path.size();
6634 RevertToOldSizeRAII(IndirectLocalPath &Path) : Path(Path) {}
6635 ~RevertToOldSizeRAII() { Path.resize(OldSize); }
6636};
6637
6638using LocalVisitor = llvm::function_ref<bool(IndirectLocalPath &Path, Local L,
6639 ReferenceKind RK)>;
6640}
6641
6642static bool isVarOnPath(IndirectLocalPath &Path, VarDecl *VD) {
6643 for (auto E : Path)
6644 if (E.Kind == IndirectLocalPathEntry::VarInit && E.D == VD)
6645 return true;
6646 return false;
6647}
6648
6649static bool pathContainsInit(IndirectLocalPath &Path) {
6650 return llvm::any_of(Path, [=](IndirectLocalPathEntry E) {
6651 return E.Kind == IndirectLocalPathEntry::DefaultInit ||
6652 E.Kind == IndirectLocalPathEntry::VarInit;
6653 });
6654}
6655
6656static void visitLocalsRetainedByInitializer(IndirectLocalPath &Path,
6657 Expr *Init, LocalVisitor Visit,
6658 bool RevisitSubinits);
6659
6660static void visitLocalsRetainedByReferenceBinding(IndirectLocalPath &Path,
6661 Expr *Init, ReferenceKind RK,
6662 LocalVisitor Visit);
6663
6664static bool implicitObjectParamIsLifetimeBound(const FunctionDecl *FD) {
6665 const TypeSourceInfo *TSI = FD->getTypeSourceInfo();
6666 if (!TSI)
6667 return false;
6668 // Don't declare this variable in the second operand of the for-statement;
6669 // GCC miscompiles that by ending its lifetime before evaluating the
6670 // third operand. See gcc.gnu.org/PR86769.
6671 AttributedTypeLoc ATL;
6672 for (TypeLoc TL = TSI->getTypeLoc();
6673 (ATL = TL.getAsAdjusted<AttributedTypeLoc>());
6674 TL = ATL.getModifiedLoc()) {
6675 if (ATL.getAttrAs<LifetimeBoundAttr>())
6676 return true;
6677 }
6678 return false;
6679}
6680
6681static void visitLifetimeBoundArguments(IndirectLocalPath &Path, Expr *Call,
6682 LocalVisitor Visit) {
6683 const FunctionDecl *Callee;
6684 ArrayRef<Expr*> Args;
6685
6686 if (auto *CE = dyn_cast<CallExpr>(Call)) {
6687 Callee = CE->getDirectCallee();
6688 Args = llvm::makeArrayRef(CE->getArgs(), CE->getNumArgs());
6689 } else {
6690 auto *CCE = cast<CXXConstructExpr>(Call);
6691 Callee = CCE->getConstructor();
6692 Args = llvm::makeArrayRef(CCE->getArgs(), CCE->getNumArgs());
6693 }
6694 if (!Callee)
6695 return;
6696
6697 Expr *ObjectArg = nullptr;
6698 if (isa<CXXOperatorCallExpr>(Call) && Callee->isCXXInstanceMember()) {
6699 ObjectArg = Args[0];
6700 Args = Args.slice(1);
6701 } else if (auto *MCE = dyn_cast<CXXMemberCallExpr>(Call)) {
6702 ObjectArg = MCE->getImplicitObjectArgument();
6703 }
6704
6705 auto VisitLifetimeBoundArg = [&](const Decl *D, Expr *Arg) {
6706 Path.push_back({IndirectLocalPathEntry::LifetimeBoundCall, Arg, D});
6707 if (Arg->isGLValue())
6708 visitLocalsRetainedByReferenceBinding(Path, Arg, RK_ReferenceBinding,
6709 Visit);
6710 else
6711 visitLocalsRetainedByInitializer(Path, Arg, Visit, true);
6712 Path.pop_back();
6713 };
6714
6715 if (ObjectArg && implicitObjectParamIsLifetimeBound(Callee))
6716 VisitLifetimeBoundArg(Callee, ObjectArg);
6717
6718 for (unsigned I = 0,
6719 N = std::min<unsigned>(Callee->getNumParams(), Args.size());
6720 I != N; ++I) {
6721 if (Callee->getParamDecl(I)->hasAttr<LifetimeBoundAttr>())
6722 VisitLifetimeBoundArg(Callee->getParamDecl(I), Args[I]);
6723 }
6724}
6725
6726/// Visit the locals that would be reachable through a reference bound to the
6727/// glvalue expression \c Init.
6728static void visitLocalsRetainedByReferenceBinding(IndirectLocalPath &Path,
6729 Expr *Init, ReferenceKind RK,
6730 LocalVisitor Visit) {
6731 RevertToOldSizeRAII RAII(Path);
6732
6733 // Walk past any constructs which we can lifetime-extend across.
6734 Expr *Old;
6735 do {
6736 Old = Init;
6737
6738 if (auto *FE = dyn_cast<FullExpr>(Init))
6739 Init = FE->getSubExpr();
6740
6741 if (InitListExpr *ILE = dyn_cast<InitListExpr>(Init)) {
6742 // If this is just redundant braces around an initializer, step over it.
6743 if (ILE->isTransparent())
6744 Init = ILE->getInit(0);
6745 }
6746
6747 // Step over any subobject adjustments; we may have a materialized
6748 // temporary inside them.
6749 Init = const_cast<Expr *>(Init->skipRValueSubobjectAdjustments());
6750
6751 // Per current approach for DR1376, look through casts to reference type
6752 // when performing lifetime extension.
6753 if (CastExpr *CE = dyn_cast<CastExpr>(Init))
6754 if (CE->getSubExpr()->isGLValue())
6755 Init = CE->getSubExpr();
6756
6757 // Per the current approach for DR1299, look through array element access
6758 // on array glvalues when performing lifetime extension.
6759 if (auto *ASE = dyn_cast<ArraySubscriptExpr>(Init)) {
6760 Init = ASE->getBase();
6761 auto *ICE = dyn_cast<ImplicitCastExpr>(Init);
6762 if (ICE && ICE->getCastKind() == CK_ArrayToPointerDecay)
6763 Init = ICE->getSubExpr();
6764 else
6765 // We can't lifetime extend through this but we might still find some
6766 // retained temporaries.
6767 return visitLocalsRetainedByInitializer(Path, Init, Visit, true);
6768 }
6769
6770 // Step into CXXDefaultInitExprs so we can diagnose cases where a
6771 // constructor inherits one as an implicit mem-initializer.
6772 if (auto *DIE = dyn_cast<CXXDefaultInitExpr>(Init)) {
6773 Path.push_back(
6774 {IndirectLocalPathEntry::DefaultInit, DIE, DIE->getField()});
6775 Init = DIE->getExpr();
6776 }
6777 } while (Init != Old);
6778
6779 if (auto *MTE = dyn_cast<MaterializeTemporaryExpr>(Init)) {
6780 if (Visit(Path, Local(MTE), RK))
6781 visitLocalsRetainedByInitializer(Path, MTE->GetTemporaryExpr(), Visit,
6782 true);
6783 }
6784
6785 if (isa<CallExpr>(Init))
6786 return visitLifetimeBoundArguments(Path, Init, Visit);
6787
6788 switch (Init->getStmtClass()) {
6789 case Stmt::DeclRefExprClass: {
6790 // If we find the name of a local non-reference parameter, we could have a
6791 // lifetime problem.
6792 auto *DRE = cast<DeclRefExpr>(Init);
6793 auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(DRE->getDecl());
6794 if (VD && VD->hasLocalStorage() &&
6795 !DRE->refersToEnclosingVariableOrCapture()) {
6796 if (!VD->getType()->isReferenceType()) {
6797 Visit(Path, Local(DRE), RK);
6798 } else if (isa<ParmVarDecl>(DRE->getDecl())) {
6799 // The lifetime of a reference parameter is unknown; assume it's OK
6800 // for now.
6801 break;
6802 } else if (VD->getInit() && !isVarOnPath(Path, VD)) {
6803 Path.push_back({IndirectLocalPathEntry::VarInit, DRE, VD});
6804 visitLocalsRetainedByReferenceBinding(Path, VD->getInit(),
6805 RK_ReferenceBinding, Visit);
6806 }
6807 }
6808 break;
6809 }
6810
6811 case Stmt::UnaryOperatorClass: {
6812 // The only unary operator that make sense to handle here
6813 // is Deref. All others don't resolve to a "name." This includes
6814 // handling all sorts of rvalues passed to a unary operator.
6815 const UnaryOperator *U = cast<UnaryOperator>(Init);
6816 if (U->getOpcode() == UO_Deref)
6817 visitLocalsRetainedByInitializer(Path, U->getSubExpr(), Visit, true);
6818 break;
6819 }
6820
6821 case Stmt::OMPArraySectionExprClass: {
6822 visitLocalsRetainedByInitializer(
6823 Path, cast<OMPArraySectionExpr>(Init)->getBase(), Visit, true);
6824 break;
6825 }
6826
6827 case Stmt::ConditionalOperatorClass:
6828 case Stmt::BinaryConditionalOperatorClass: {
6829 auto *C = cast<AbstractConditionalOperator>(Init);
6830 if (!C->getTrueExpr()->getType()->isVoidType())
6831 visitLocalsRetainedByReferenceBinding(Path, C->getTrueExpr(), RK, Visit);
6832 if (!C->getFalseExpr()->getType()->isVoidType())
6833 visitLocalsRetainedByReferenceBinding(Path, C->getFalseExpr(), RK, Visit);
6834 break;
6835 }
6836
6837 // FIXME: Visit the left-hand side of an -> or ->*.
6838
6839 default:
6840 break;
6841 }
6842}
6843
6844/// Visit the locals that would be reachable through an object initialized by
6845/// the prvalue expression \c Init.
6846static void visitLocalsRetainedByInitializer(IndirectLocalPath &Path,
6847 Expr *Init, LocalVisitor Visit,
6848 bool RevisitSubinits) {
6849 RevertToOldSizeRAII RAII(Path);
6850
6851 Expr *Old;
6852 do {
6853 Old = Init;
6854
6855 // Step into CXXDefaultInitExprs so we can diagnose cases where a
6856 // constructor inherits one as an implicit mem-initializer.
6857 if (auto *DIE = dyn_cast<CXXDefaultInitExpr>(Init)) {
6858 Path.push_back({IndirectLocalPathEntry::DefaultInit, DIE, DIE->getField()});
6859 Init = DIE->getExpr();
6860 }
6861
6862 if (auto *FE = dyn_cast<FullExpr>(Init))
6863 Init = FE->getSubExpr();
6864
6865 // Dig out the expression which constructs the extended temporary.
6866 Init = const_cast<Expr *>(Init->skipRValueSubobjectAdjustments());
6867
6868 if (CXXBindTemporaryExpr *BTE = dyn_cast<CXXBindTemporaryExpr>(Init))
6869 Init = BTE->getSubExpr();
6870
6871 Init = Init->IgnoreParens();
6872
6873 // Step over value-preserving rvalue casts.
6874 if (auto *CE = dyn_cast<CastExpr>(Init)) {
6875 switch (CE->getCastKind()) {
6876 case CK_LValueToRValue:
6877 // If we can match the lvalue to a const object, we can look at its
6878 // initializer.
6879 Path.push_back({IndirectLocalPathEntry::LValToRVal, CE});
6880 return visitLocalsRetainedByReferenceBinding(
6881 Path, Init, RK_ReferenceBinding,
6882 [&](IndirectLocalPath &Path, Local L, ReferenceKind RK) -> bool {
6883 if (auto *DRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(L)) {
6884 auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(DRE->getDecl());
6885 if (VD && VD->getType().isConstQualified() && VD->getInit() &&
6886 !isVarOnPath(Path, VD)) {
6887 Path.push_back({IndirectLocalPathEntry::VarInit, DRE, VD});
6888 visitLocalsRetainedByInitializer(Path, VD->getInit(), Visit, true);
6889 }
6890 } else if (auto *MTE = dyn_cast<MaterializeTemporaryExpr>(L)) {
6891 if (MTE->getType().isConstQualified())
6892 visitLocalsRetainedByInitializer(Path, MTE->GetTemporaryExpr(),
6893 Visit, true);
6894 }
6895 return false;
6896 });
6897
6898 // We assume that objects can be retained by pointers cast to integers,
6899 // but not if the integer is cast to floating-point type or to _Complex.
6900 // We assume that casts to 'bool' do not preserve enough information to
6901 // retain a local object.
6902 case CK_NoOp:
6903 case CK_BitCast:
6904 case CK_BaseToDerived:
6905 case CK_DerivedToBase:
6906 case CK_UncheckedDerivedToBase:
6907 case CK_Dynamic:
6908 case CK_ToUnion:
6909 case CK_UserDefinedConversion:
6910 case CK_ConstructorConversion:
6911 case CK_IntegralToPointer:
6912 case CK_PointerToIntegral:
6913 case CK_VectorSplat:
6914 case CK_IntegralCast:
6915 case CK_CPointerToObjCPointerCast:
6916 case CK_BlockPointerToObjCPointerCast:
6917 case CK_AnyPointerToBlockPointerCast:
6918 case CK_AddressSpaceConversion:
6919 break;
6920
6921 case CK_ArrayToPointerDecay:
6922 // Model array-to-pointer decay as taking the address of the array
6923 // lvalue.
6924 Path.push_back({IndirectLocalPathEntry::AddressOf, CE});
6925 return visitLocalsRetainedByReferenceBinding(Path, CE->getSubExpr(),
6926 RK_ReferenceBinding, Visit);
6927
6928 default:
6929 return;
6930 }
6931
6932 Init = CE->getSubExpr();
6933 }
6934 } while (Old != Init);
6935
6936 // C++17 [dcl.init.list]p6:
6937 // initializing an initializer_list object from the array extends the
6938 // lifetime of the array exactly like binding a reference to a temporary.
6939 if (auto *ILE = dyn_cast<CXXStdInitializerListExpr>(Init))
6940 return visitLocalsRetainedByReferenceBinding(Path, ILE->getSubExpr(),
6941 RK_StdInitializerList, Visit);
6942
6943 if (InitListExpr *ILE = dyn_cast<InitListExpr>(Init)) {
6944 // We already visited the elements of this initializer list while
6945 // performing the initialization. Don't visit them again unless we've
6946 // changed the lifetime of the initialized entity.
6947 if (!RevisitSubinits)
6948 return;
6949
6950 if (ILE->isTransparent())
6951 return visitLocalsRetainedByInitializer(Path, ILE->getInit(0), Visit,
6952 RevisitSubinits);
6953
6954 if (ILE->getType()->isArrayType()) {
6955 for (unsigned I = 0, N = ILE->getNumInits(); I != N; ++I)
6956 visitLocalsRetainedByInitializer(Path, ILE->getInit(I), Visit,
6957 RevisitSubinits);
6958 return;
6959 }
6960
6961 if (CXXRecordDecl *RD = ILE->getType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl()) {
6962 assert(RD->isAggregate() && "aggregate init on non-aggregate");
6963
6964 // If we lifetime-extend a braced initializer which is initializing an
6965 // aggregate, and that aggregate contains reference members which are
6966 // bound to temporaries, those temporaries are also lifetime-extended.
6967 if (RD->isUnion() && ILE->getInitializedFieldInUnion() &&
6968 ILE->getInitializedFieldInUnion()->getType()->isReferenceType())
6969 visitLocalsRetainedByReferenceBinding(Path, ILE->getInit(0),
6970 RK_ReferenceBinding, Visit);
6971 else {
6972 unsigned Index = 0;
6973 for (; Index < RD->getNumBases() && Index < ILE->getNumInits(); ++Index)
6974 visitLocalsRetainedByInitializer(Path, ILE->getInit(Index), Visit,
6975 RevisitSubinits);
6976 for (const auto *I : RD->fields()) {
6977 if (Index >= ILE->getNumInits())
6978 break;
6979 if (I->isUnnamedBitfield())
6980 continue;
6981 Expr *SubInit = ILE->getInit(Index);
6982 if (I->getType()->isReferenceType())
6983 visitLocalsRetainedByReferenceBinding(Path, SubInit,
6984 RK_ReferenceBinding, Visit);
6985 else
6986 // This might be either aggregate-initialization of a member or
6987 // initialization of a std::initializer_list object. Regardless,
6988 // we should recursively lifetime-extend that initializer.
6989 visitLocalsRetainedByInitializer(Path, SubInit, Visit,
6990 RevisitSubinits);
6991 ++Index;
6992 }
6993 }
6994 }
6995 return;
6996 }
6997
6998 // The lifetime of an init-capture is that of the closure object constructed
6999 // by a lambda-expression.
7000 if (auto *LE = dyn_cast<LambdaExpr>(Init)) {
7001 for (Expr *E : LE->capture_inits()) {
7002 if (!E)
7003 continue;
7004 if (E->isGLValue())
7005 visitLocalsRetainedByReferenceBinding(Path, E, RK_ReferenceBinding,
7006 Visit);
7007 else
7008 visitLocalsRetainedByInitializer(Path, E, Visit, true);
7009 }
7010 }
7011
7012 if (isa<CallExpr>(Init) || isa<CXXConstructExpr>(Init))
7013 return visitLifetimeBoundArguments(Path, Init, Visit);
7014
7015 switch (Init->getStmtClass()) {
7016 case Stmt::UnaryOperatorClass: {
7017 auto *UO = cast<UnaryOperator>(Init);
7018 // If the initializer is the address of a local, we could have a lifetime
7019 // problem.
7020 if (UO->getOpcode() == UO_AddrOf) {
7021 // If this is &rvalue, then it's ill-formed and we have already diagnosed
7022 // it. Don't produce a redundant warning about the lifetime of the
7023 // temporary.
7024 if (isa<MaterializeTemporaryExpr>(UO->getSubExpr()))
7025 return;
7026
7027 Path.push_back({IndirectLocalPathEntry::AddressOf, UO});
7028 visitLocalsRetainedByReferenceBinding(Path, UO->getSubExpr(),
7029 RK_ReferenceBinding, Visit);
7030 }
7031 break;
7032 }
7033
7034 case Stmt::BinaryOperatorClass: {
7035 // Handle pointer arithmetic.
7036 auto *BO = cast<BinaryOperator>(Init);
7037 BinaryOperatorKind BOK = BO->getOpcode();
7038 if (!BO->getType()->isPointerType() || (BOK != BO_Add && BOK != BO_Sub))
7039 break;
7040
7041 if (BO->getLHS()->getType()->isPointerType())
7042 visitLocalsRetainedByInitializer(Path, BO->getLHS(), Visit, true);
7043 else if (BO->getRHS()->getType()->isPointerType())
7044 visitLocalsRetainedByInitializer(Path, BO->getRHS(), Visit, true);
7045 break;
7046 }
7047
7048 case Stmt::ConditionalOperatorClass:
7049 case Stmt::BinaryConditionalOperatorClass: {
7050 auto *C = cast<AbstractConditionalOperator>(Init);
7051 // In C++, we can have a throw-expression operand, which has 'void' type
7052 // and isn't interesting from a lifetime perspective.
7053 if (!C->getTrueExpr()->getType()->isVoidType())
7054 visitLocalsRetainedByInitializer(Path, C->getTrueExpr(), Visit, true);
7055 if (!C->getFalseExpr()->getType()->isVoidType())
7056 visitLocalsRetainedByInitializer(Path, C->getFalseExpr(), Visit, true);
7057 break;
7058 }
7059
7060 case Stmt::BlockExprClass:
7061 if (cast<BlockExpr>(Init)->getBlockDecl()->hasCaptures()) {
7062 // This is a local block, whose lifetime is that of the function.
7063 Visit(Path, Local(cast<BlockExpr>(Init)), RK_ReferenceBinding);
7064 }
7065 break;
7066
7067 case Stmt::AddrLabelExprClass:
7068 // We want to warn if the address of a label would escape the function.
7069 Visit(Path, Local(cast<AddrLabelExpr>(Init)), RK_ReferenceBinding);
7070 break;
7071
7072 default:
7073 break;
7074 }
7075}
7076
7077/// Determine whether this is an indirect path to a temporary that we are
7078/// supposed to lifetime-extend along (but don't).
7079static bool shouldLifetimeExtendThroughPath(const IndirectLocalPath &Path) {
7080 for (auto Elem : Path) {
7081 if (Elem.Kind != IndirectLocalPathEntry::DefaultInit)
7082 return false;
7083 }
7084 return true;
7085}
7086
7087/// Find the range for the first interesting entry in the path at or after I.
7088static SourceRange nextPathEntryRange(const IndirectLocalPath &Path, unsigned I,
7089 Expr *E) {
7090 for (unsigned N = Path.size(); I != N; ++I) {
7091 switch (Path[I].Kind) {
7092 case IndirectLocalPathEntry::AddressOf:
7093 case IndirectLocalPathEntry::LValToRVal:
7094 case IndirectLocalPathEntry::LifetimeBoundCall:
7095 // These exist primarily to mark the path as not permitting or
7096 // supporting lifetime extension.
7097 break;
7098
7099 case IndirectLocalPathEntry::DefaultInit:
7100 case IndirectLocalPathEntry::VarInit:
7101 return Path[I].E->getSourceRange();
7102 }
7103 }
7104 return E->getSourceRange();
7105}
7106
7107void Sema::checkInitializerLifetime(const InitializedEntity &Entity,
7108 Expr *Init) {
7109 LifetimeResult LR = getEntityLifetime(&Entity);
7110 LifetimeKind LK = LR.getInt();
7111 const InitializedEntity *ExtendingEntity = LR.getPointer();
7112
7113 // If this entity doesn't have an interesting lifetime, don't bother looking
7114 // for temporaries within its initializer.
7115 if (LK == LK_FullExpression)
7116 return;
7117
7118 auto TemporaryVisitor = [&](IndirectLocalPath &Path, Local L,
7119 ReferenceKind RK) -> bool {
7120 SourceRange DiagRange = nextPathEntryRange(Path, 0, L);
7121 SourceLocation DiagLoc = DiagRange.getBegin();
7122
7123 switch (LK) {
7124 case LK_FullExpression:
7125 llvm_unreachable("already handled this");
7126
7127 case LK_Extended: {
7128 auto *MTE = dyn_cast<MaterializeTemporaryExpr>(L);
7129 if (!MTE) {
7130 // The initialized entity has lifetime beyond the full-expression,
7131 // and the local entity does too, so don't warn.
7132 //
7133 // FIXME: We should consider warning if a static / thread storage
7134 // duration variable retains an automatic storage duration local.
7135 return false;
7136 }
7137
7138 // Lifetime-extend the temporary.
7139 if (Path.empty()) {
7140 // Update the storage duration of the materialized temporary.
7141 // FIXME: Rebuild the expression instead of mutating it.
7142 MTE->setExtendingDecl(ExtendingEntity->getDecl(),
7143 ExtendingEntity->allocateManglingNumber());
7144 // Also visit the temporaries lifetime-extended by this initializer.
7145 return true;
7146 }
7147
7148 if (shouldLifetimeExtendThroughPath(Path)) {
7149 // We're supposed to lifetime-extend the temporary along this path (per
7150 // the resolution of DR1815), but we don't support that yet.
7151 //
7152 // FIXME: Properly handle this situation. Perhaps the easiest approach
7153 // would be to clone the initializer expression on each use that would
7154 // lifetime extend its temporaries.
7155 Diag(DiagLoc, diag::warn_unsupported_lifetime_extension)
7156 << RK << DiagRange;
7157 } else {
7158 // If the path goes through the initialization of a variable or field,
7159 // it can't possibly reach a temporary created in this full-expression.
7160 // We will have already diagnosed any problems with the initializer.
7161 if (pathContainsInit(Path))
7162 return false;
7163
7164 Diag(DiagLoc, diag::warn_dangling_variable)
7165 << RK << !Entity.getParent()
7166 << ExtendingEntity->getDecl()->isImplicit()
7167 << ExtendingEntity->getDecl() << Init->isGLValue() << DiagRange;
7168 }
7169 break;
7170 }
7171
7172 case LK_MemInitializer: {
7173 if (isa<MaterializeTemporaryExpr>(L)) {
7174 // Under C++ DR1696, if a mem-initializer (or a default member
7175 // initializer used by the absence of one) would lifetime-extend a
7176 // temporary, the program is ill-formed.
7177 if (auto *ExtendingDecl =
7178 ExtendingEntity ? ExtendingEntity->getDecl() : nullptr) {
7179 bool IsSubobjectMember = ExtendingEntity != &Entity;
7180 Diag(DiagLoc, shouldLifetimeExtendThroughPath(Path)
7181 ? diag::err_dangling_member
7182 : diag::warn_dangling_member)
7183 << ExtendingDecl << IsSubobjectMember << RK << DiagRange;
7184 // Don't bother adding a note pointing to the field if we're inside
7185 // its default member initializer; our primary diagnostic points to
7186 // the same place in that case.
7187 if (Path.empty() ||
7188 Path.back().Kind != IndirectLocalPathEntry::DefaultInit) {
7189 Diag(ExtendingDecl->getLocation(),
7190 diag::note_lifetime_extending_member_declared_here)
7191 << RK << IsSubobjectMember;
7192 }
7193 } else {
7194 // We have a mem-initializer but no particular field within it; this
7195 // is either a base class or a delegating initializer directly
7196 // initializing the base-class from something that doesn't live long
7197 // enough.
7198 //
7199 // FIXME: Warn on this.
7200 return false;
7201 }
7202 } else {
7203 // Paths via a default initializer can only occur during error recovery
7204 // (there's no other way that a default initializer can refer to a
7205 // local). Don't produce a bogus warning on those cases.
7206 if (pathContainsInit(Path))
7207 return false;
7208
7209 auto *DRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(L);
7210 auto *VD = DRE ? dyn_cast<VarDecl>(DRE->getDecl()) : nullptr;
7211 if (!VD) {
7212 // A member was initialized to a local block.
7213 // FIXME: Warn on this.
7214 return false;
7215 }
7216
7217 if (auto *Member =
7218 ExtendingEntity ? ExtendingEntity->getDecl() : nullptr) {
7219 bool IsPointer = Member->getType()->isAnyPointerType();
7220 Diag(DiagLoc, IsPointer ? diag::warn_init_ptr_member_to_parameter_addr
7221 : diag::warn_bind_ref_member_to_parameter)
7222 << Member << VD << isa<ParmVarDecl>(VD) << DiagRange;
7223 Diag(Member->getLocation(),
7224 diag::note_ref_or_ptr_member_declared_here)
7225 << (unsigned)IsPointer;
7226 }
7227 }
7228 break;
7229 }
7230
7231 case LK_New:
7232 if (isa<MaterializeTemporaryExpr>(L)) {
7233 Diag(DiagLoc, RK == RK_ReferenceBinding
7234 ? diag::warn_new_dangling_reference
7235 : diag::warn_new_dangling_initializer_list)
7236 << !Entity.getParent() << DiagRange;
7237 } else {
7238 // We can't determine if the allocation outlives the local declaration.
7239 return false;
7240 }
7241 break;
7242
7243 case LK_Return:
7244 case LK_StmtExprResult:
7245 if (auto *DRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(L)) {
7246 // We can't determine if the local variable outlives the statement
7247 // expression.
7248 if (LK == LK_StmtExprResult)
7249 return false;
7250 Diag(DiagLoc, diag::warn_ret_stack_addr_ref)
7251 << Entity.getType()->isReferenceType() << DRE->getDecl()
7252 << isa<ParmVarDecl>(DRE->getDecl()) << DiagRange;
7253 } else if (isa<BlockExpr>(L)) {
7254 Diag(DiagLoc, diag::err_ret_local_block) << DiagRange;
7255 } else if (isa<AddrLabelExpr>(L)) {
7256 // Don't warn when returning a label from a statement expression.
7257 // Leaving the scope doesn't end its lifetime.
7258 if (LK == LK_StmtExprResult)
7259 return false;
7260 Diag(DiagLoc, diag::warn_ret_addr_label) << DiagRange;
7261 } else {
7262 Diag(DiagLoc, diag::warn_ret_local_temp_addr_ref)
7263 << Entity.getType()->isReferenceType() << DiagRange;
7264 }
7265 break;
7266 }
7267
7268 for (unsigned I = 0; I != Path.size(); ++I) {
7269 auto Elem = Path[I];
7270
7271 switch (Elem.Kind) {
7272 case IndirectLocalPathEntry::AddressOf:
7273 case IndirectLocalPathEntry::LValToRVal:
7274 // These exist primarily to mark the path as not permitting or
7275 // supporting lifetime extension.
7276 break;
7277
7278 case IndirectLocalPathEntry::LifetimeBoundCall:
7279 // FIXME: Consider adding a note for this.
7280 break;
7281
7282 case IndirectLocalPathEntry::DefaultInit: {
7283 auto *FD = cast<FieldDecl>(Elem.D);
7284 Diag(FD->getLocation(), diag::note_init_with_default_member_initalizer)
7285 << FD << nextPathEntryRange(Path, I + 1, L);
7286 break;
7287 }
7288
7289 case IndirectLocalPathEntry::VarInit:
7290 const VarDecl *VD = cast<VarDecl>(Elem.D);
7291 Diag(VD->getLocation(), diag::note_local_var_initializer)
7292 << VD->getType()->isReferenceType()
7293 << VD->isImplicit() << VD->getDeclName()
7294 << nextPathEntryRange(Path, I + 1, L);
7295 break;
7296 }
7297 }
7298
7299 // We didn't lifetime-extend, so don't go any further; we don't need more
7300 // warnings or errors on inner temporaries within this one's initializer.
7301 return false;
7302 };
7303
7304 llvm::SmallVector<IndirectLocalPathEntry, 8> Path;
7305 if (Init->isGLValue())
7306 visitLocalsRetainedByReferenceBinding(Path, Init, RK_ReferenceBinding,
7307 TemporaryVisitor);
7308 else
7309 visitLocalsRetainedByInitializer(Path, Init, TemporaryVisitor, false);
7310}
7311
7312static void DiagnoseNarrowingInInitList(Sema &S,
7313 const ImplicitConversionSequence &ICS,
7314 QualType PreNarrowingType,
7315 QualType EntityType,
7316 const Expr *PostInit);
7317
7318/// Provide warnings when std::move is used on construction.
7319static void CheckMoveOnConstruction(Sema &S, const Expr *InitExpr,
7320 bool IsReturnStmt) {
7321 if (!InitExpr)
7322 return;
7323
7324 if (S.inTemplateInstantiation())
7325 return;
7326
7327 QualType DestType = InitExpr->getType();
7328 if (!DestType->isRecordType())
7329 return;
7330
7331 unsigned DiagID = 0;
7332 if (IsReturnStmt) {
7333 const CXXConstructExpr *CCE =
7334 dyn_cast<CXXConstructExpr>(InitExpr->IgnoreParens());
7335 if (!CCE || CCE->getNumArgs() != 1)
7336 return;
7337
7338 if (!CCE->getConstructor()->isCopyOrMoveConstructor())
7339 return;
7340
7341 InitExpr = CCE->getArg(0)->IgnoreImpCasts();
7342 }
7343
7344 // Find the std::move call and get the argument.
7345 const CallExpr *CE = dyn_cast<CallExpr>(InitExpr->IgnoreParens());
7346 if (!CE || !CE->isCallToStdMove())
7347 return;
7348
7349 const Expr *Arg = CE->getArg(0)->IgnoreImplicit();
7350
7351 if (IsReturnStmt) {
7352 const DeclRefExpr *DRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(Arg->IgnoreParenImpCasts());
7353 if (!DRE || DRE->refersToEnclosingVariableOrCapture())
7354 return;
7355
7356 const VarDecl *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(DRE->getDecl());
7357 if (!VD || !VD->hasLocalStorage())
7358 return;
7359
7360 // __block variables are not moved implicitly.
7361 if (VD->hasAttr<BlocksAttr>())
7362 return;
7363
7364 QualType SourceType = VD->getType();
7365 if (!SourceType->isRecordType())
7366 return;
7367
7368 if (!S.Context.hasSameUnqualifiedType(DestType, SourceType)) {
7369 return;
7370 }
7371
7372 // If we're returning a function parameter, copy elision
7373 // is not possible.
7374 if (isa<ParmVarDecl>(VD))
7375 DiagID = diag::warn_redundant_move_on_return;
7376 else
7377 DiagID = diag::warn_pessimizing_move_on_return;
7378 } else {
7379 DiagID = diag::warn_pessimizing_move_on_initialization;
7380 const Expr *ArgStripped = Arg->IgnoreImplicit()->IgnoreParens();
7381 if (!ArgStripped->isRValue() || !ArgStripped->getType()->isRecordType())
7382 return;
7383 }
7384
7385 S.Diag(CE->getBeginLoc(), DiagID);
7386
7387 // Get all the locations for a fix-it. Don't emit the fix-it if any location
7388 // is within a macro.
7389 SourceLocation CallBegin = CE->getCallee()->getBeginLoc();
7390 if (CallBegin.isMacroID())
7391 return;
7392 SourceLocation RParen = CE->getRParenLoc();
7393 if (RParen.isMacroID())
7394 return;
7395 SourceLocation LParen;
7396 SourceLocation ArgLoc = Arg->getBeginLoc();
7397
7398 // Special testing for the argument location. Since the fix-it needs the
7399 // location right before the argument, the argument location can be in a
7400 // macro only if it is at the beginning of the macro.
7401 while (ArgLoc.isMacroID() &&
7402 S.getSourceManager().isAtStartOfImmediateMacroExpansion(ArgLoc)) {
7403 ArgLoc = S.getSourceManager().getImmediateExpansionRange(ArgLoc).getBegin();
7404 }
7405
7406 if (LParen.isMacroID())
7407 return;
7408
7409 LParen = ArgLoc.getLocWithOffset(-1);
7410
7411 S.Diag(CE->getBeginLoc(), diag::note_remove_move)
7412 << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(SourceRange(CallBegin, LParen))
7413 << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(SourceRange(RParen, RParen));
7414}
7415
7416static void CheckForNullPointerDereference(Sema &S, const Expr *E) {
7417 // Check to see if we are dereferencing a null pointer. If so, this is
7418 // undefined behavior, so warn about it. This only handles the pattern
7419 // "*null", which is a very syntactic check.
7420 if (const UnaryOperator *UO = dyn_cast<UnaryOperator>(E->IgnoreParenCasts()))
7421 if (UO->getOpcode() == UO_Deref &&
7422 UO->getSubExpr()->IgnoreParenCasts()->
7423 isNullPointerConstant(S.Context, Expr::NPC_ValueDependentIsNotNull)) {
7424 S.DiagRuntimeBehavior(UO->getOperatorLoc(), UO,
7425 S.PDiag(diag::warn_binding_null_to_reference)
7426 << UO->getSubExpr()->getSourceRange());
7427 }
7428}
7429
7430MaterializeTemporaryExpr *
7431Sema::CreateMaterializeTemporaryExpr(QualType T, Expr *Temporary,
7432 bool BoundToLvalueReference) {
7433 auto MTE = new (Context)
7434 MaterializeTemporaryExpr(T, Temporary, BoundToLvalueReference);
7435
7436 // Order an ExprWithCleanups for lifetime marks.
7437 //
7438 // TODO: It'll be good to have a single place to check the access of the
7439 // destructor and generate ExprWithCleanups for various uses. Currently these
7440 // are done in both CreateMaterializeTemporaryExpr and MaybeBindToTemporary,
7441 // but there may be a chance to merge them.
7442 Cleanup.setExprNeedsCleanups(false);
7443 return MTE;
7444}
7445
7446ExprResult Sema::TemporaryMaterializationConversion(Expr *E) {
7447 // In C++98, we don't want to implicitly create an xvalue.
7448 // FIXME: This means that AST consumers need to deal with "prvalues" that
7449 // denote materialized temporaries. Maybe we should add another ValueKind
7450 // for "xvalue pretending to be a prvalue" for C++98 support.
7451 if (!E->isRValue() || !getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11)
7452 return E;
7453
7454 // C++1z [conv.rval]/1: T shall be a complete type.
7455 // FIXME: Does this ever matter (can we form a prvalue of incomplete type)?
7456 // If so, we should check for a non-abstract class type here too.
7457 QualType T = E->getType();
7458 if (RequireCompleteType(E->getExprLoc(), T, diag::err_incomplete_type))
7459 return ExprError();
7460
7461 return CreateMaterializeTemporaryExpr(E->getType(), E, false);
7462}
7463
7464ExprResult Sema::PerformQualificationConversion(Expr *E, QualType Ty,
7465 ExprValueKind VK,
7466 CheckedConversionKind CCK) {
7467
7468 CastKind CK = CK_NoOp;
7469
7470 if (VK == VK_RValue) {
7471 auto PointeeTy = Ty->getPointeeType();
7472 auto ExprPointeeTy = E->getType()->getPointeeType();
7473 if (!PointeeTy.isNull() &&
7474 PointeeTy.getAddressSpace() != ExprPointeeTy.getAddressSpace())
7475 CK = CK_AddressSpaceConversion;
7476 } else if (Ty.getAddressSpace() != E->getType().getAddressSpace()) {
7477 CK = CK_AddressSpaceConversion;
7478 }
7479
7480 return ImpCastExprToType(E, Ty, CK, VK, /*BasePath=*/nullptr, CCK);
7481}
7482
7483ExprResult InitializationSequence::Perform(Sema &S,
7484 const InitializedEntity &Entity,
7485 const InitializationKind &Kind,
7486 MultiExprArg Args,
7487 QualType *ResultType) {
7488 if (Failed()) {
7489 Diagnose(S, Entity, Kind, Args);
7490 return ExprError();
7491 }
7492 if (!ZeroInitializationFixit.empty()) {
7493 unsigned DiagID = diag::err_default_init_const;
7494 if (Decl *D = Entity.getDecl())
7495 if (S.getLangOpts().MSVCCompat && D->hasAttr<SelectAnyAttr>())
7496 DiagID = diag::ext_default_init_const;
7497
7498 // The initialization would have succeeded with this fixit. Since the fixit
7499 // is on the error, we need to build a valid AST in this case, so this isn't
7500 // handled in the Failed() branch above.
7501 QualType DestType = Entity.getType();
7502 S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), DiagID)
7503 << DestType << (bool)DestType->getAs<RecordType>()
7504 << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(ZeroInitializationFixitLoc,
7505 ZeroInitializationFixit);
7506 }
7507
7508 if (getKind() == DependentSequence) {
7509 // If the declaration is a non-dependent, incomplete array type
7510 // that has an initializer, then its type will be completed once
7511 // the initializer is instantiated.
7512 if (ResultType && !Entity.getType()->isDependentType() &&
7513 Args.size() == 1) {
7514 QualType DeclType = Entity.getType();
7515 if (const IncompleteArrayType *ArrayT
7516 = S.Context.getAsIncompleteArrayType(DeclType)) {
7517 // FIXME: We don't currently have the ability to accurately
7518 // compute the length of an initializer list without
7519 // performing full type-checking of the initializer list
7520 // (since we have to determine where braces are implicitly
7521 // introduced and such). So, we fall back to making the array
7522 // type a dependently-sized array type with no specified
7523 // bound.
7524 if (isa<InitListExpr>((Expr *)Args[0])) {
7525 SourceRange Brackets;
7526
7527 // Scavange the location of the brackets from the entity, if we can.
7528 if (auto *DD = dyn_cast_or_null<DeclaratorDecl>(Entity.getDecl())) {
7529 if (TypeSourceInfo *TInfo = DD->getTypeSourceInfo()) {
7530 TypeLoc TL = TInfo->getTypeLoc();
7531 if (IncompleteArrayTypeLoc ArrayLoc =
7532 TL.getAs<IncompleteArrayTypeLoc>())
7533 Brackets = ArrayLoc.getBracketsRange();
7534 }
7535 }
7536
7537 *ResultType
7538 = S.Context.getDependentSizedArrayType(ArrayT->getElementType(),
7539 /*NumElts=*/nullptr,
7540 ArrayT->getSizeModifier(),
7541 ArrayT->getIndexTypeCVRQualifiers(),
7542 Brackets);
7543 }
7544
7545 }
7546 }
7547 if (Kind.getKind() == InitializationKind::IK_Direct &&
7548 !Kind.isExplicitCast()) {
7549 // Rebuild the ParenListExpr.
7550 SourceRange ParenRange = Kind.getParenOrBraceRange();
7551 return S.ActOnParenListExpr(ParenRange.getBegin(), ParenRange.getEnd(),
7552 Args);
7553 }
7554 assert(Kind.getKind() == InitializationKind::IK_Copy ||
7555 Kind.isExplicitCast() ||
7556 Kind.getKind() == InitializationKind::IK_DirectList);
7557 return ExprResult(Args[0]);
7558 }
7559
7560 // No steps means no initialization.
7561 if (Steps.empty())
7562 return ExprResult((Expr *)nullptr);
7563
7564 if (S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11 && Entity.getType()->isReferenceType() &&
7565 Args.size() == 1 && isa<InitListExpr>(Args[0]) &&
7566 !Entity.isParameterKind()) {
7567 // Produce a C++98 compatibility warning if we are initializing a reference
7568 // from an initializer list. For parameters, we produce a better warning
7569 // elsewhere.
7570 Expr *Init = Args[0];
7571 S.Diag(Init->getBeginLoc(), diag::warn_cxx98_compat_reference_list_init)
7572 << Init->getSourceRange();
7573 }
7574
7575 // OpenCL v2.0 s6.13.11.1. atomic variables can be initialized in global scope
7576 QualType ETy = Entity.getType();
7577 Qualifiers TyQualifiers = ETy.getQualifiers();
7578 bool HasGlobalAS = TyQualifiers.hasAddressSpace() &&
7579 TyQualifiers.getAddressSpace() == LangAS::opencl_global;
7580
7581 if (S.getLangOpts().OpenCLVersion >= 200 &&
7582 ETy->isAtomicType() && !HasGlobalAS &&
7583 Entity.getKind() == InitializedEntity::EK_Variable && Args.size() > 0) {
7584 S.Diag(Args[0]->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_opencl_atomic_init)
7585 << 1
7586 << SourceRange(Entity.getDecl()->getBeginLoc(), Args[0]->getEndLoc());
7587 return ExprError();
7588 }
7589
7590 QualType DestType = Entity.getType().getNonReferenceType();
7591 // FIXME: Ugly hack around the fact that Entity.getType() is not
7592 // the same as Entity.getDecl()->getType() in cases involving type merging,
7593 // and we want latter when it makes sense.
7594 if (ResultType)
7595 *ResultType = Entity.getDecl() ? Entity.getDecl()->getType() :
7596 Entity.getType();
7597
7598 ExprResult CurInit((Expr *)nullptr);
7599 SmallVector<Expr*, 4> ArrayLoopCommonExprs;
7600
7601 // For initialization steps that start with a single initializer,
7602 // grab the only argument out the Args and place it into the "current"
7603 // initializer.
7604 switch (Steps.front().Kind) {
7605 case SK_ResolveAddressOfOverloadedFunction:
7606 case SK_CastDerivedToBaseRValue:
7607 case SK_CastDerivedToBaseXValue:
7608 case SK_CastDerivedToBaseLValue:
7609 case SK_BindReference:
7610 case SK_BindReferenceToTemporary:
7611 case SK_FinalCopy:
7612 case SK_ExtraneousCopyToTemporary:
7613 case SK_UserConversion:
7614 case SK_QualificationConversionLValue:
7615 case SK_QualificationConversionXValue:
7616 case SK_QualificationConversionRValue:
7617 case SK_AtomicConversion:
7618 case SK_LValueToRValue:
7619 case SK_ConversionSequence:
7620 case SK_ConversionSequenceNoNarrowing:
7621 case SK_ListInitialization:
7622 case SK_UnwrapInitList:
7623 case SK_RewrapInitList:
7624 case SK_CAssignment:
7625 case SK_StringInit:
7626 case SK_ObjCObjectConversion:
7627 case SK_ArrayLoopIndex:
7628 case SK_ArrayLoopInit:
7629 case SK_ArrayInit:
7630 case SK_GNUArrayInit:
7631 case SK_ParenthesizedArrayInit:
7632 case SK_PassByIndirectCopyRestore:
7633 case SK_PassByIndirectRestore:
7634 case SK_ProduceObjCObject:
7635 case SK_StdInitializerList:
7636 case SK_OCLSamplerInit:
7637 case SK_OCLZeroOpaqueType: {
7638 assert(Args.size() == 1);
7639 CurInit = Args[0];
7640 if (!CurInit.get()) return ExprError();
7641 break;
7642 }
7643
7644 case SK_ConstructorInitialization:
7645 case SK_ConstructorInitializationFromList:
7646 case SK_StdInitializerListConstructorCall:
7647 case SK_ZeroInitialization:
7648 break;
7649 }
7650
7651 // Promote from an unevaluated context to an unevaluated list context in
7652 // C++11 list-initialization; we need to instantiate entities usable in
7653 // constant expressions here in order to perform narrowing checks =(
7654 EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Evaluated(
7655 S, EnterExpressionEvaluationContext::InitList,
7656 CurInit.get() && isa<InitListExpr>(CurInit.get()));
7657
7658 // C++ [class.abstract]p2:
7659 // no objects of an abstract class can be created except as subobjects
7660 // of a class derived from it
7661 auto checkAbstractType = [&](QualType T) -> bool {
7662 if (Entity.getKind() == InitializedEntity::EK_Base ||
7663 Entity.getKind() == InitializedEntity::EK_Delegating)
7664 return false;
7665 return S.RequireNonAbstractType(Kind.getLocation(), T,
7666 diag::err_allocation_of_abstract_type);
7667 };
7668
7669 // Walk through the computed steps for the initialization sequence,
7670 // performing the specified conversions along the way.
7671 bool ConstructorInitRequiresZeroInit = false;
7672 for (step_iterator Step = step_begin(), StepEnd = step_end();
7673 Step != StepEnd; ++Step) {
7674 if (CurInit.isInvalid())
7675 return ExprError();
7676
7677 QualType SourceType = CurInit.get() ? CurInit.get()->getType() : QualType();
7678
7679 switch (Step->Kind) {
7680 case SK_ResolveAddressOfOverloadedFunction:
7681 // Overload resolution determined which function invoke; update the
7682 // initializer to reflect that choice.
7683 S.CheckAddressOfMemberAccess(CurInit.get(), Step->Function.FoundDecl);
7684 if (S.DiagnoseUseOfDecl(Step->Function.FoundDecl, Kind.getLocation()))
7685 return ExprError();
7686 CurInit = S.FixOverloadedFunctionReference(CurInit,
7687 Step->Function.FoundDecl,
7688 Step->Function.Function);
7689 break;
7690
7691 case SK_CastDerivedToBaseRValue:
7692 case SK_CastDerivedToBaseXValue:
7693 case SK_CastDerivedToBaseLValue: {
7694 // We have a derived-to-base cast that produces either an rvalue or an
7695 // lvalue. Perform that cast.
7696
7697 CXXCastPath BasePath;
7698
7699 // Casts to inaccessible base classes are allowed with C-style casts.
7700 bool IgnoreBaseAccess = Kind.isCStyleOrFunctionalCast();
7701 if (S.CheckDerivedToBaseConversion(
7702 SourceType, Step->Type, CurInit.get()->getBeginLoc(),
7703 CurInit.get()->getSourceRange(), &BasePath, IgnoreBaseAccess))
7704 return ExprError();
7705
7706 ExprValueKind VK =
7707 Step->Kind == SK_CastDerivedToBaseLValue ?
7708 VK_LValue :
7709 (Step->Kind == SK_CastDerivedToBaseXValue ?
7710 VK_XValue :
7711 VK_RValue);
7712 CurInit =
7713 ImplicitCastExpr::Create(S.Context, Step->Type, CK_DerivedToBase,
7714 CurInit.get(), &BasePath, VK);
7715 break;
7716 }
7717
7718 case SK_BindReference:
7719 // Reference binding does not have any corresponding ASTs.
7720
7721 // Check exception specifications
7722 if (S.CheckExceptionSpecCompatibility(CurInit.get(), DestType))
7723 return ExprError();
7724
7725 // We don't check for e.g. function pointers here, since address
7726 // availability checks should only occur when the function first decays
7727 // into a pointer or reference.
7728 if (CurInit.get()->getType()->isFunctionProtoType()) {
7729 if (auto *DRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(CurInit.get()->IgnoreParens())) {
7730 if (auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(DRE->getDecl())) {
7731 if (!S.checkAddressOfFunctionIsAvailable(FD, /*Complain=*/true,
7732 DRE->getBeginLoc()))
7733 return ExprError();
7734 }
7735 }
7736 }
7737
7738 CheckForNullPointerDereference(S, CurInit.get());
7739 break;
7740
7741 case SK_BindReferenceToTemporary: {
7742 // Make sure the "temporary" is actually an rvalue.
7743 assert(CurInit.get()->isRValue() && "not a temporary");
7744
7745 // Check exception specifications
7746 if (S.CheckExceptionSpecCompatibility(CurInit.get(), DestType))
7747 return ExprError();
7748
7749 // Materialize the temporary into memory.
7750 MaterializeTemporaryExpr *MTE = S.CreateMaterializeTemporaryExpr(
7751 Step->Type, CurInit.get(), Entity.getType()->isLValueReferenceType());
7752 CurInit = MTE;
7753
7754 // If we're extending this temporary to automatic storage duration -- we
7755 // need to register its cleanup during the full-expression's cleanups.
7756 if (MTE->getStorageDuration() == SD_Automatic &&
7757 MTE->getType().isDestructedType())
7758 S.Cleanup.setExprNeedsCleanups(true);
7759 break;
7760 }
7761
7762 case SK_FinalCopy:
7763 if (checkAbstractType(Step->Type))
7764 return ExprError();
7765
7766 // If the overall initialization is initializing a temporary, we already
7767 // bound our argument if it was necessary to do so. If not (if we're
7768 // ultimately initializing a non-temporary), our argument needs to be
7769 // bound since it's initializing a function parameter.
7770 // FIXME: This is a mess. Rationalize temporary destruction.
7771 if (!shouldBindAsTemporary(Entity))
7772 CurInit = S.MaybeBindToTemporary(CurInit.get());
7773 CurInit = CopyObject(S, Step->Type, Entity, CurInit,
7774 /*IsExtraneousCopy=*/false);
7775 break;
7776
7777 case SK_ExtraneousCopyToTemporary:
7778 CurInit = CopyObject(S, Step->Type, Entity, CurInit,
7779 /*IsExtraneousCopy=*/true);
7780 break;
7781
7782 case SK_UserConversion: {
7783 // We have a user-defined conversion that invokes either a constructor
7784 // or a conversion function.
7785 CastKind CastKind;
7786 FunctionDecl *Fn = Step->Function.Function;
7787 DeclAccessPair FoundFn = Step->Function.FoundDecl;
7788 bool HadMultipleCandidates = Step->Function.HadMultipleCandidates;
7789 bool CreatedObject = false;
7790 if (CXXConstructorDecl *Constructor = dyn_cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(Fn)) {
7791 // Build a call to the selected constructor.
7792 SmallVector<Expr*, 8> ConstructorArgs;
7793 SourceLocation Loc = CurInit.get()->getBeginLoc();
7794
7795 // Determine the arguments required to actually perform the constructor
7796 // call.
7797 Expr *Arg = CurInit.get();
7798 if (S.CompleteConstructorCall(Constructor,
7799 MultiExprArg(&Arg, 1),
7800 Loc, ConstructorArgs))
7801 return ExprError();
7802
7803 // Build an expression that constructs a temporary.
7804 CurInit = S.BuildCXXConstructExpr(Loc, Step->Type,
7805 FoundFn, Constructor,
7806 ConstructorArgs,
7807 HadMultipleCandidates,
7808 /*ListInit*/ false,
7809 /*StdInitListInit*/ false,
7810 /*ZeroInit*/ false,
7811 CXXConstructExpr::CK_Complete,
7812 SourceRange());
7813 if (CurInit.isInvalid())
7814 return ExprError();
7815
7816 S.CheckConstructorAccess(Kind.getLocation(), Constructor, FoundFn,
7817 Entity);
7818 if (S.DiagnoseUseOfDecl(FoundFn, Kind.getLocation()))
7819 return ExprError();
7820
7821 CastKind = CK_ConstructorConversion;
7822 CreatedObject = true;
7823 } else {
7824 // Build a call to the conversion function.
7825 CXXConversionDecl *Conversion = cast<CXXConversionDecl>(Fn);
7826 S.CheckMemberOperatorAccess(Kind.getLocation(), CurInit.get(), nullptr,
7827 FoundFn);
7828 if (S.DiagnoseUseOfDecl(FoundFn, Kind.getLocation()))
7829 return ExprError();
7830
7831 CurInit = S.BuildCXXMemberCallExpr(CurInit.get(), FoundFn, Conversion,
7832 HadMultipleCandidates);
7833 if (CurInit.isInvalid())
7834 return ExprError();
7835
7836 CastKind = CK_UserDefinedConversion;
7837 CreatedObject = Conversion->getReturnType()->isRecordType();
7838 }
7839
7840 if (CreatedObject && checkAbstractType(CurInit.get()->getType()))
7841 return ExprError();
7842
7843 CurInit = ImplicitCastExpr::Create(S.Context, CurInit.get()->getType(),
7844 CastKind, CurInit.get(), nullptr,
7845 CurInit.get()->getValueKind());
7846
7847 if (shouldBindAsTemporary(Entity))
7848 // The overall entity is temporary, so this expression should be
7849 // destroyed at the end of its full-expression.
7850 CurInit = S.MaybeBindToTemporary(CurInit.getAs<Expr>());
7851 else if (CreatedObject && shouldDestroyEntity(Entity)) {
7852 // The object outlasts the full-expression, but we need to prepare for
7853 // a destructor being run on it.
7854 // FIXME: It makes no sense to do this here. This should happen
7855 // regardless of how we initialized the entity.
7856 QualType T = CurInit.get()->getType();
7857 if (const RecordType *Record = T->getAs<RecordType>()) {
7858 CXXDestructorDecl *Destructor
7859 = S.LookupDestructor(cast<CXXRecordDecl>(Record->getDecl()));
7860 S.CheckDestructorAccess(CurInit.get()->getBeginLoc(), Destructor,
7861 S.PDiag(diag::err_access_dtor_temp) << T);
7862 S.MarkFunctionReferenced(CurInit.get()->getBeginLoc(), Destructor);
7863 if (S.DiagnoseUseOfDecl(Destructor, CurInit.get()->getBeginLoc()))
7864 return ExprError();
7865 }
7866 }
7867 break;
7868 }
7869
7870 case SK_QualificationConversionLValue:
7871 case SK_QualificationConversionXValue:
7872 case SK_QualificationConversionRValue: {
7873 // Perform a qualification conversion; these can never go wrong.
7874 ExprValueKind VK =
7875 Step->Kind == SK_QualificationConversionLValue
7876 ? VK_LValue
7877 : (Step->Kind == SK_QualificationConversionXValue ? VK_XValue
7878 : VK_RValue);
7879 CurInit = S.PerformQualificationConversion(CurInit.get(), Step->Type, VK);
7880 break;
7881 }
7882
7883 case SK_AtomicConversion: {
7884 assert(CurInit.get()->isRValue() && "cannot convert glvalue to atomic");
7885 CurInit = S.ImpCastExprToType(CurInit.get(), Step->Type,
7886 CK_NonAtomicToAtomic, VK_RValue);
7887 break;
7888 }
7889
7890 case SK_LValueToRValue: {
7891 assert(CurInit.get()->isGLValue() && "cannot load from a prvalue");
7892 CurInit = ImplicitCastExpr::Create(S.Context, Step->Type,
7893 CK_LValueToRValue, CurInit.get(),
7894 /*BasePath=*/nullptr, VK_RValue);
7895 break;
7896 }
7897
7898 case SK_ConversionSequence:
7899 case SK_ConversionSequenceNoNarrowing: {
7900 if (const auto *FromPtrType =
7901 CurInit.get()->getType()->getAs<PointerType>()) {
7902 if (const auto *ToPtrType = Step->Type->getAs<PointerType>()) {
7903 if (FromPtrType->getPointeeType()->hasAttr(attr::NoDeref) &&
7904 !ToPtrType->getPointeeType()->hasAttr(attr::NoDeref)) {
7905 S.Diag(CurInit.get()->getExprLoc(),
7906 diag::warn_noderef_to_dereferenceable_pointer)
7907 << CurInit.get()->getSourceRange();
7908 }
7909 }
7910 }
7911
7912 Sema::CheckedConversionKind CCK
7913 = Kind.isCStyleCast()? Sema::CCK_CStyleCast
7914 : Kind.isFunctionalCast()? Sema::CCK_FunctionalCast
7915 : Kind.isExplicitCast()? Sema::CCK_OtherCast
7916 : Sema::CCK_ImplicitConversion;
7917 ExprResult CurInitExprRes =
7918 S.PerformImplicitConversion(CurInit.get(), Step->Type, *Step->ICS,
7919 getAssignmentAction(Entity), CCK);
7920 if (CurInitExprRes.isInvalid())
7921 return ExprError();
7922
7923 S.DiscardMisalignedMemberAddress(Step->Type.getTypePtr(), CurInit.get());
7924
7925 CurInit = CurInitExprRes;
7926
7927 if (Step->Kind == SK_ConversionSequenceNoNarrowing &&
7928 S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus)
7929 DiagnoseNarrowingInInitList(S, *Step->ICS, SourceType, Entity.getType(),
7930 CurInit.get());
7931
7932 break;
7933 }
7934
7935 case SK_ListInitialization: {
7936 if (checkAbstractType(Step->Type))
7937 return ExprError();
7938
7939 InitListExpr *InitList = cast<InitListExpr>(CurInit.get());
7940 // If we're not initializing the top-level entity, we need to create an
7941 // InitializeTemporary entity for our target type.
7942 QualType Ty = Step->Type;
7943 bool IsTemporary = !S.Context.hasSameType(Entity.getType(), Ty);
7944 InitializedEntity TempEntity = InitializedEntity::InitializeTemporary(Ty);
7945 InitializedEntity InitEntity = IsTemporary ? TempEntity : Entity;
7946 InitListChecker PerformInitList(S, InitEntity,
7947 InitList, Ty, /*VerifyOnly=*/false,
7948 /*TreatUnavailableAsInvalid=*/false);
7949 if (PerformInitList.HadError())
7950 return ExprError();
7951
7952 // Hack: We must update *ResultType if available in order to set the
7953 // bounds of arrays, e.g. in 'int ar[] = {1, 2, 3};'.
7954 // Worst case: 'const int (&arref)[] = {1, 2, 3};'.
7955 if (ResultType &&
7956 ResultType->getNonReferenceType()->isIncompleteArrayType()) {
7957 if ((*ResultType)->isRValueReferenceType())
7958 Ty = S.Context.getRValueReferenceType(Ty);
7959 else if ((*ResultType)->isLValueReferenceType())
7960 Ty = S.Context.getLValueReferenceType(Ty,
7961 (*ResultType)->getAs<LValueReferenceType>()->isSpelledAsLValue());
7962 *ResultType = Ty;
7963 }
7964
7965 InitListExpr *StructuredInitList =
7966 PerformInitList.getFullyStructuredList();
7967 CurInit.get();
7968 CurInit = shouldBindAsTemporary(InitEntity)
7969 ? S.MaybeBindToTemporary(StructuredInitList)
7970 : StructuredInitList;
7971 break;
7972 }
7973
7974 case SK_ConstructorInitializationFromList: {
7975 if (checkAbstractType(Step->Type))
7976 return ExprError();
7977
7978 // When an initializer list is passed for a parameter of type "reference
7979 // to object", we don't get an EK_Temporary entity, but instead an
7980 // EK_Parameter entity with reference type.
7981 // FIXME: This is a hack. What we really should do is create a user
7982 // conversion step for this case, but this makes it considerably more
7983 // complicated. For now, this will do.
7984 InitializedEntity TempEntity = InitializedEntity::InitializeTemporary(
7985 Entity.getType().getNonReferenceType());
7986 bool UseTemporary = Entity.getType()->isReferenceType();
7987 assert(Args.size() == 1 && "expected a single argument for list init");
7988 InitListExpr *InitList = cast<InitListExpr>(Args[0]);
7989 S.Diag(InitList->getExprLoc(), diag::warn_cxx98_compat_ctor_list_init)
7990 << InitList->getSourceRange();
7991 MultiExprArg Arg(InitList->getInits(), InitList->getNumInits());
7992 CurInit = PerformConstructorInitialization(S, UseTemporary ? TempEntity :
7993 Entity,
7994 Kind, Arg, *Step,
7995 ConstructorInitRequiresZeroInit,
7996 /*IsListInitialization*/true,
7997 /*IsStdInitListInit*/false,
7998 InitList->getLBraceLoc(),
7999 InitList->getRBraceLoc());
8000 break;
8001 }
8002
8003 case SK_UnwrapInitList:
8004 CurInit = cast<InitListExpr>(CurInit.get())->getInit(0);
8005 break;
8006
8007 case SK_RewrapInitList: {
8008 Expr *E = CurInit.get();
8009 InitListExpr *Syntactic = Step->WrappingSyntacticList;
8010 InitListExpr *ILE = new (S.Context) InitListExpr(S.Context,
8011 Syntactic->getLBraceLoc(), E, Syntactic->getRBraceLoc());
8012 ILE->setSyntacticForm(Syntactic);
8013 ILE->setType(E->getType());
8014 ILE->setValueKind(E->getValueKind());
8015 CurInit = ILE;
8016 break;
8017 }
8018
8019 case SK_ConstructorInitialization:
8020 case SK_StdInitializerListConstructorCall: {
8021 if (checkAbstractType(Step->Type))
8022 return ExprError();
8023
8024 // When an initializer list is passed for a parameter of type "reference
8025 // to object", we don't get an EK_Temporary entity, but instead an
8026 // EK_Parameter entity with reference type.
8027 // FIXME: This is a hack. What we really should do is create a user
8028 // conversion step for this case, but this makes it considerably more
8029 // complicated. For now, this will do.
8030 InitializedEntity TempEntity = InitializedEntity::InitializeTemporary(
8031 Entity.getType().getNonReferenceType());
8032 bool UseTemporary = Entity.getType()->isReferenceType();
8033 bool IsStdInitListInit =
8034 Step->Kind == SK_StdInitializerListConstructorCall;
8035 Expr *Source = CurInit.get();
8036 SourceRange Range = Kind.hasParenOrBraceRange()
8037 ? Kind.getParenOrBraceRange()
8038 : SourceRange();
8039 CurInit = PerformConstructorInitialization(
8040 S, UseTemporary ? TempEntity : Entity, Kind,
8041 Source ? MultiExprArg(Source) : Args, *Step,
8042 ConstructorInitRequiresZeroInit,
8043 /*IsListInitialization*/ IsStdInitListInit,
8044 /*IsStdInitListInitialization*/ IsStdInitListInit,
8045 /*LBraceLoc*/ Range.getBegin(),
8046 /*RBraceLoc*/ Range.getEnd());
8047 break;
8048 }
8049
8050 case SK_ZeroInitialization: {
8051 step_iterator NextStep = Step;
8052 ++NextStep;
8053 if (NextStep != StepEnd &&
8054 (NextStep->Kind == SK_ConstructorInitialization ||
8055 NextStep->Kind == SK_ConstructorInitializationFromList)) {
8056 // The need for zero-initialization is recorded directly into
8057 // the call to the object's constructor within the next step.
8058 ConstructorInitRequiresZeroInit = true;
8059 } else if (Kind.getKind() == InitializationKind::IK_Value &&
8060 S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus &&
8061 !Kind.isImplicitValueInit()) {
8062 TypeSourceInfo *TSInfo = Entity.getTypeSourceInfo();
8063 if (!TSInfo)
8064 TSInfo = S.Context.getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(Step->Type,
8065 Kind.getRange().getBegin());
8066
8067 CurInit = new (S.Context) CXXScalarValueInitExpr(
8068 Entity.getType().getNonLValueExprType(S.Context), TSInfo,
8069 Kind.getRange().getEnd());
8070 } else {
8071 CurInit = new (S.Context) ImplicitValueInitExpr(Step->Type);
8072 }
8073 break;
8074 }
8075
8076 case SK_CAssignment: {
8077 QualType SourceType = CurInit.get()->getType();
8078
8079 // Save off the initial CurInit in case we need to emit a diagnostic
8080 ExprResult InitialCurInit = CurInit;
8081 ExprResult Result = CurInit;
8082 Sema::AssignConvertType ConvTy =
8083 S.CheckSingleAssignmentConstraints(Step->Type, Result, true,
8084 Entity.getKind() == InitializedEntity::EK_Parameter_CF_Audited);
8085 if (Result.isInvalid())
8086 return ExprError();
8087 CurInit = Result;
8088
8089 // If this is a call, allow conversion to a transparent union.
8090 ExprResult CurInitExprRes = CurInit;
8091 if (ConvTy != Sema::Compatible &&
8092 Entity.isParameterKind() &&
8093 S.CheckTransparentUnionArgumentConstraints(Step->Type, CurInitExprRes)
8094 == Sema::Compatible)
8095 ConvTy = Sema::Compatible;
8096 if (CurInitExprRes.isInvalid())
8097 return ExprError();
8098 CurInit = CurInitExprRes;
8099
8100 bool Complained;
8101 if (S.DiagnoseAssignmentResult(ConvTy, Kind.getLocation(),
8102 Step->Type, SourceType,
8103 InitialCurInit.get(),
8104 getAssignmentAction(Entity, true),
8105 &Complained)) {
8106 PrintInitLocationNote(S, Entity);
8107 return ExprError();
8108 } else if (Complained)
8109 PrintInitLocationNote(S, Entity);
8110 break;
8111 }
8112
8113 case SK_StringInit: {
8114 QualType Ty = Step->Type;
8115 CheckStringInit(CurInit.get(), ResultType ? *ResultType : Ty,
8116 S.Context.getAsArrayType(Ty), S);
8117 break;
8118 }
8119
8120 case SK_ObjCObjectConversion:
8121 CurInit = S.ImpCastExprToType(CurInit.get(), Step->Type,
8122 CK_ObjCObjectLValueCast,
8123 CurInit.get()->getValueKind());
8124 break;
8125
8126 case SK_ArrayLoopIndex: {
8127 Expr *Cur = CurInit.get();
8128 Expr *BaseExpr = new (S.Context)
8129 OpaqueValueExpr(Cur->getExprLoc(), Cur->getType(),
8130 Cur->getValueKind(), Cur->getObjectKind(), Cur);
8131 Expr *IndexExpr =
8132 new (S.Context) ArrayInitIndexExpr(S.Context.getSizeType());
8133 CurInit = S.CreateBuiltinArraySubscriptExpr(
8134 BaseExpr, Kind.getLocation(), IndexExpr, Kind.getLocation());
8135 ArrayLoopCommonExprs.push_back(BaseExpr);
8136 break;
8137 }
8138
8139 case SK_ArrayLoopInit: {
8140 assert(!ArrayLoopCommonExprs.empty() &&
8141 "mismatched SK_ArrayLoopIndex and SK_ArrayLoopInit");
8142 Expr *Common = ArrayLoopCommonExprs.pop_back_val();
8143 CurInit = new (S.Context) ArrayInitLoopExpr(Step->Type, Common,
8144 CurInit.get());
8145 break;
8146 }
8147
8148 case SK_GNUArrayInit:
8149 // Okay: we checked everything before creating this step. Note that
8150 // this is a GNU extension.
8151 S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::ext_array_init_copy)
8152 << Step->Type << CurInit.get()->getType()
8153 << CurInit.get()->getSourceRange();
8154 updateGNUCompoundLiteralRValue(CurInit.get());
8155 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
8156 case SK_ArrayInit:
8157 // If the destination type is an incomplete array type, update the
8158 // type accordingly.
8159 if (ResultType) {
8160 if (const IncompleteArrayType *IncompleteDest
8161 = S.Context.getAsIncompleteArrayType(Step->Type)) {
8162 if (const ConstantArrayType *ConstantSource
8163 = S.Context.getAsConstantArrayType(CurInit.get()->getType())) {
8164 *ResultType = S.Context.getConstantArrayType(
8165 IncompleteDest->getElementType(),
8166 ConstantSource->getSize(),
8167 ArrayType::Normal, 0);
8168 }
8169 }
8170 }
8171 break;
8172
8173 case SK_ParenthesizedArrayInit:
8174 // Okay: we checked everything before creating this step. Note that
8175 // this is a GNU extension.
8176 S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::ext_array_init_parens)
8177 << CurInit.get()->getSourceRange();
8178 break;
8179
8180 case SK_PassByIndirectCopyRestore:
8181 case SK_PassByIndirectRestore:
8182 checkIndirectCopyRestoreSource(S, CurInit.get());
8183 CurInit = new (S.Context) ObjCIndirectCopyRestoreExpr(
8184 CurInit.get(), Step->Type,
8185 Step->Kind == SK_PassByIndirectCopyRestore);
8186 break;
8187
8188 case SK_ProduceObjCObject:
8189 CurInit =
8190 ImplicitCastExpr::Create(S.Context, Step->Type, CK_ARCProduceObject,
8191 CurInit.get(), nullptr, VK_RValue);
8192 break;
8193
8194 case SK_StdInitializerList: {
8195 S.Diag(CurInit.get()->getExprLoc(),
8196 diag::warn_cxx98_compat_initializer_list_init)
8197 << CurInit.get()->getSourceRange();
8198
8199 // Materialize the temporary into memory.
8200 MaterializeTemporaryExpr *MTE = S.CreateMaterializeTemporaryExpr(
8201 CurInit.get()->getType(), CurInit.get(),
8202 /*BoundToLvalueReference=*/false);
8203
8204 // Wrap it in a construction of a std::initializer_list<T>.
8205 CurInit = new (S.Context) CXXStdInitializerListExpr(Step->Type, MTE);
8206
8207 // Bind the result, in case the library has given initializer_list a
8208 // non-trivial destructor.
8209 if (shouldBindAsTemporary(Entity))
8210 CurInit = S.MaybeBindToTemporary(CurInit.get());
8211 break;
8212 }
8213
8214 case SK_OCLSamplerInit: {
8215 // Sampler initialization have 5 cases:
8216 // 1. function argument passing
8217 // 1a. argument is a file-scope variable
8218 // 1b. argument is a function-scope variable
8219 // 1c. argument is one of caller function's parameters
8220 // 2. variable initialization
8221 // 2a. initializing a file-scope variable
8222 // 2b. initializing a function-scope variable
8223 //
8224 // For file-scope variables, since they cannot be initialized by function
8225 // call of __translate_sampler_initializer in LLVM IR, their references
8226 // need to be replaced by a cast from their literal initializers to
8227 // sampler type. Since sampler variables can only be used in function
8228 // calls as arguments, we only need to replace them when handling the
8229 // argument passing.
8230 assert(Step->Type->isSamplerT() &&
8231 "Sampler initialization on non-sampler type.");
8232 Expr *Init = CurInit.get();
8233 QualType SourceType = Init->getType();
8234 // Case 1
8235 if (Entity.isParameterKind()) {
8236 if (!SourceType->isSamplerT() && !SourceType->isIntegerType()) {
8237 S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_sampler_argument_required)
8238 << SourceType;
8239 break;
8240 } else if (const DeclRefExpr *DRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(Init)) {
8241 auto Var = cast<VarDecl>(DRE->getDecl());
8242 // Case 1b and 1c
8243 // No cast from integer to sampler is needed.
8244 if (!Var->hasGlobalStorage()) {
8245 CurInit = ImplicitCastExpr::Create(S.Context, Step->Type,
8246 CK_LValueToRValue, Init,
8247 /*BasePath=*/nullptr, VK_RValue);
8248 break;
8249 }
8250 // Case 1a
8251 // For function call with a file-scope sampler variable as argument,
8252 // get the integer literal.
8253 // Do not diagnose if the file-scope variable does not have initializer
8254 // since this has already been diagnosed when parsing the variable
8255 // declaration.
8256 if (!Var->getInit() || !isa<ImplicitCastExpr>(Var->getInit()))
8257 break;
8258 Init = cast<ImplicitCastExpr>(const_cast<Expr*>(
8259 Var->getInit()))->getSubExpr();
8260 SourceType = Init->getType();
8261 }
8262 } else {
8263 // Case 2
8264 // Check initializer is 32 bit integer constant.
8265 // If the initializer is taken from global variable, do not diagnose since
8266 // this has already been done when parsing the variable declaration.
8267 if (!Init->isConstantInitializer(S.Context, false))
8268 break;
8269
8270 if (!SourceType->isIntegerType() ||
8271 32 != S.Context.getIntWidth(SourceType)) {
8272 S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_sampler_initializer_not_integer)
8273 << SourceType;
8274 break;
8275 }
8276
8277 Expr::EvalResult EVResult;
8278 Init->EvaluateAsInt(EVResult, S.Context);
8279 llvm::APSInt Result = EVResult.Val.getInt();
8280 const uint64_t SamplerValue = Result.getLimitedValue();
8281 // 32-bit value of sampler's initializer is interpreted as
8282 // bit-field with the following structure:
8283 // |unspecified|Filter|Addressing Mode| Normalized Coords|
8284 // |31 6|5 4|3 1| 0|
8285 // This structure corresponds to enum values of sampler properties
8286 // defined in SPIR spec v1.2 and also opencl-c.h
8287 unsigned AddressingMode = (0x0E & SamplerValue) >> 1;
8288 unsigned FilterMode = (0x30 & SamplerValue) >> 4;
8289 if (FilterMode != 1 && FilterMode != 2 &&
8290 !S.getOpenCLOptions().isEnabled(
8291 "cl_intel_device_side_avc_motion_estimation"))
8292 S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(),
8293 diag::warn_sampler_initializer_invalid_bits)
8294 << "Filter Mode";
8295 if (AddressingMode > 4)
8296 S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(),
8297 diag::warn_sampler_initializer_invalid_bits)
8298 << "Addressing Mode";
8299 }
8300
8301 // Cases 1a, 2a and 2b
8302 // Insert cast from integer to sampler.
8303 CurInit = S.ImpCastExprToType(Init, S.Context.OCLSamplerTy,
8304 CK_IntToOCLSampler);
8305 break;
8306 }
8307 case SK_OCLZeroOpaqueType: {
8308 assert((Step->Type->isEventT() || Step->Type->isQueueT() ||
8309 Step->Type->isOCLIntelSubgroupAVCType()) &&
8310 "Wrong type for initialization of OpenCL opaque type.");
8311
8312 CurInit = S.ImpCastExprToType(CurInit.get(), Step->Type,
8313 CK_ZeroToOCLOpaqueType,
8314 CurInit.get()->getValueKind());
8315 break;
8316 }
8317 }
8318 }
8319
8320 // Check whether the initializer has a shorter lifetime than the initialized
8321 // entity, and if not, either lifetime-extend or warn as appropriate.
8322 if (auto *Init = CurInit.get())
8323 S.checkInitializerLifetime(Entity, Init);
8324
8325 // Diagnose non-fatal problems with the completed initialization.
8326 if (Entity.getKind() == InitializedEntity::EK_Member &&
8327 cast<FieldDecl>(Entity.getDecl())->isBitField())
8328 S.CheckBitFieldInitialization(Kind.getLocation(),
8329 cast<FieldDecl>(Entity.getDecl()),
8330 CurInit.get());
8331
8332 // Check for std::move on construction.
8333 if (const Expr *E = CurInit.get()) {
8334 CheckMoveOnConstruction(S, E,
8335 Entity.getKind() == InitializedEntity::EK_Result);
8336 }
8337
8338 return CurInit;
8339}
8340
8341/// Somewhere within T there is an uninitialized reference subobject.
8342/// Dig it out and diagnose it.
8343static bool DiagnoseUninitializedReference(Sema &S, SourceLocation Loc,
8344 QualType T) {
8345 if (T->isReferenceType()) {
8346 S.Diag(Loc, diag::err_reference_without_init)
8347 << T.getNonReferenceType();
8348 return true;
8349 }
8350
8351 CXXRecordDecl *RD = T->getBaseElementTypeUnsafe()->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
8352 if (!RD || !RD->hasUninitializedReferenceMember())
8353 return false;
8354
8355 for (const auto *FI : RD->fields()) {
8356 if (FI->isUnnamedBitfield())
8357 continue;
8358
8359 if (DiagnoseUninitializedReference(S, FI->getLocation(), FI->getType())) {
8360 S.Diag(Loc, diag::note_value_initialization_here) << RD;
8361 return true;
8362 }
8363 }
8364
8365 for (const auto &BI : RD->bases()) {
8366 if (DiagnoseUninitializedReference(S, BI.getBeginLoc(), BI.getType())) {
8367 S.Diag(Loc, diag::note_value_initialization_here) << RD;
8368 return true;
8369 }
8370 }
8371
8372 return false;
8373}
8374
8375
8376//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
8377// Diagnose initialization failures
8378//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
8379
8380/// Emit notes associated with an initialization that failed due to a
8381/// "simple" conversion failure.
8382static void emitBadConversionNotes(Sema &S, const InitializedEntity &entity,
8383 Expr *op) {
8384 QualType destType = entity.getType();
8385 if (destType.getNonReferenceType()->isObjCObjectPointerType() &&
8386 op->getType()->isObjCObjectPointerType()) {
8387
8388 // Emit a possible note about the conversion failing because the
8389 // operand is a message send with a related result type.
8390 S.EmitRelatedResultTypeNote(op);
8391
8392 // Emit a possible note about a return failing because we're
8393 // expecting a related result type.
8394 if (entity.getKind() == InitializedEntity::EK_Result)
8395 S.EmitRelatedResultTypeNoteForReturn(destType);
8396 }
8397}
8398
8399static void diagnoseListInit(Sema &S, const InitializedEntity &Entity,
8400 InitListExpr *InitList) {
8401 QualType DestType = Entity.getType();
8402
8403 QualType E;
8404 if (S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11 && S.isStdInitializerList(DestType, &E)) {
8405 QualType ArrayType = S.Context.getConstantArrayType(
8406 E.withConst(),
8407 llvm::APInt(S.Context.getTypeSize(S.Context.getSizeType()),
8408 InitList->getNumInits()),
8409 clang::ArrayType::Normal, 0);
8410 InitializedEntity HiddenArray =
8411 InitializedEntity::InitializeTemporary(ArrayType);
8412 return diagnoseListInit(S, HiddenArray, InitList);
8413 }
8414
8415 if (DestType->isReferenceType()) {
8416 // A list-initialization failure for a reference means that we tried to
8417 // create a temporary of the inner type (per [dcl.init.list]p3.6) and the
8418 // inner initialization failed.
8419 QualType T = DestType->getAs<ReferenceType>()->getPointeeType();
8420 diagnoseListInit(S, InitializedEntity::InitializeTemporary(T), InitList);
8421 SourceLocation Loc = InitList->getBeginLoc();
8422 if (auto *D = Entity.getDecl())
8423 Loc = D->getLocation();
8424 S.Diag(Loc, diag::note_in_reference_temporary_list_initializer) << T;
8425 return;
8426 }
8427
8428 InitListChecker DiagnoseInitList(S, Entity, InitList, DestType,
8429 /*VerifyOnly=*/false,
8430 /*TreatUnavailableAsInvalid=*/false);
8431 assert(DiagnoseInitList.HadError() &&
8432 "Inconsistent init list check result.");
8433}
8434
8435bool InitializationSequence::Diagnose(Sema &S,
8436 const InitializedEntity &Entity,
8437 const InitializationKind &Kind,
8438 ArrayRef<Expr *> Args) {
8439 if (!Failed())
8440 return false;
8441
8442 // When we want to diagnose only one element of a braced-init-list,
8443 // we need to factor it out.
8444 Expr *OnlyArg;
8445 if (Args.size() == 1) {
8446 auto *List = dyn_cast<InitListExpr>(Args[0]);
8447 if (List && List->getNumInits() == 1)
8448 OnlyArg = List->getInit(0);
8449 else
8450 OnlyArg = Args[0];
8451 }
8452 else
8453 OnlyArg = nullptr;
8454
8455 QualType DestType = Entity.getType();
8456 switch (Failure) {
8457 case FK_TooManyInitsForReference:
8458 // FIXME: Customize for the initialized entity?
8459 if (Args.empty()) {
8460 // Dig out the reference subobject which is uninitialized and diagnose it.
8461 // If this is value-initialization, this could be nested some way within
8462 // the target type.
8463 assert(Kind.getKind() == InitializationKind::IK_Value ||
8464 DestType->isReferenceType());
8465 bool Diagnosed =
8466 DiagnoseUninitializedReference(S, Kind.getLocation(), DestType);
8467 assert(Diagnosed && "couldn't find uninitialized reference to diagnose");
8468 (void)Diagnosed;
8469 } else // FIXME: diagnostic below could be better!
8470 S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_reference_has_multiple_inits)
8471 << SourceRange(Args.front()->getBeginLoc(), Args.back()->getEndLoc());
8472 break;
8473 case FK_ParenthesizedListInitForReference:
8474 S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_list_init_in_parens)
8475 << 1 << Entity.getType() << Args[0]->getSourceRange();
8476 break;
8477
8478 case FK_ArrayNeedsInitList:
8479 S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_array_init_not_init_list) << 0;
8480 break;
8481 case FK_ArrayNeedsInitListOrStringLiteral:
8482 S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_array_init_not_init_list) << 1;
8483 break;
8484 case FK_ArrayNeedsInitListOrWideStringLiteral:
8485 S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_array_init_not_init_list) << 2;
8486 break;
8487 case FK_NarrowStringIntoWideCharArray:
8488 S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_array_init_narrow_string_into_wchar);
8489 break;
8490 case FK_WideStringIntoCharArray:
8491 S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_array_init_wide_string_into_char);
8492 break;
8493 case FK_IncompatWideStringIntoWideChar:
8494 S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(),
8495 diag::err_array_init_incompat_wide_string_into_wchar);
8496 break;
8497 case FK_PlainStringIntoUTF8Char:
8498 S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(),
8499 diag::err_array_init_plain_string_into_char8_t);
8500 S.Diag(Args.front()->getBeginLoc(),
8501 diag::note_array_init_plain_string_into_char8_t)
8502 << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(Args.front()->getBeginLoc(), "u8");
8503 break;
8504 case FK_UTF8StringIntoPlainChar:
8505 S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(),
8506 diag::err_array_init_utf8_string_into_char)
8507 << S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus2a;
8508 break;
8509 case FK_ArrayTypeMismatch:
8510 case FK_NonConstantArrayInit:
8511 S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(),
8512 (Failure == FK_ArrayTypeMismatch
8513 ? diag::err_array_init_different_type
8514 : diag::err_array_init_non_constant_array))
8515 << DestType.getNonReferenceType()
8516 << OnlyArg->getType()
8517 << Args[0]->getSourceRange();
8518 break;
8519
8520 case FK_VariableLengthArrayHasInitializer:
8521 S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_variable_object_no_init)
8522 << Args[0]->getSourceRange();
8523 break;
8524
8525 case FK_AddressOfOverloadFailed: {
8526 DeclAccessPair Found;
8527 S.ResolveAddressOfOverloadedFunction(OnlyArg,
8528 DestType.getNonReferenceType(),
8529 true,
8530 Found);
8531 break;
8532 }
8533
8534 case FK_AddressOfUnaddressableFunction: {
8535 auto *FD = cast<FunctionDecl>(cast<DeclRefExpr>(OnlyArg)->getDecl());
8536 S.checkAddressOfFunctionIsAvailable(FD, /*Complain=*/true,
8537 OnlyArg->getBeginLoc());
8538 break;
8539 }
8540
8541 case FK_ReferenceInitOverloadFailed:
8542 case FK_UserConversionOverloadFailed:
8543 switch (FailedOverloadResult) {
8544 case OR_Ambiguous:
8545
8546 FailedCandidateSet.NoteCandidates(
8547 PartialDiagnosticAt(
8548 Kind.getLocation(),
8549 Failure == FK_UserConversionOverloadFailed
8550 ? (S.PDiag(diag::err_typecheck_ambiguous_condition)
8551 << OnlyArg->getType() << DestType
8552 << Args[0]->getSourceRange())
8553 : (S.PDiag(diag::err_ref_init_ambiguous)
8554 << DestType << OnlyArg->getType()
8555 << Args[0]->getSourceRange())),
8556 S, OCD_ViableCandidates, Args);
8557 break;
8558
8559 case OR_No_Viable_Function: {
8560 auto Cands = FailedCandidateSet.CompleteCandidates(S, OCD_AllCandidates, Args);
8561 if (!S.RequireCompleteType(Kind.getLocation(),
8562 DestType.getNonReferenceType(),
8563 diag::err_typecheck_nonviable_condition_incomplete,
8564 OnlyArg->getType(), Args[0]->getSourceRange()))
8565 S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_typecheck_nonviable_condition)
8566 << (Entity.getKind() == InitializedEntity::EK_Result)
8567 << OnlyArg->getType() << Args[0]->getSourceRange()
8568 << DestType.getNonReferenceType();
8569
8570 FailedCandidateSet.NoteCandidates(S, Args, Cands);
8571 break;
8572 }
8573 case OR_Deleted: {
8574 S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_typecheck_deleted_function)
8575 << OnlyArg->getType() << DestType.getNonReferenceType()
8576 << Args[0]->getSourceRange();
8577 OverloadCandidateSet::iterator Best;
8578 OverloadingResult Ovl
8579 = FailedCandidateSet.BestViableFunction(S, Kind.getLocation(), Best);
8580 if (Ovl == OR_Deleted) {
8581 S.NoteDeletedFunction(Best->Function);
8582 } else {
8583 llvm_unreachable("Inconsistent overload resolution?");
8584 }
8585 break;
8586 }
8587
8588 case OR_Success:
8589 llvm_unreachable("Conversion did not fail!");
8590 }
8591 break;
8592
8593 case FK_NonConstLValueReferenceBindingToTemporary:
8594 if (isa<InitListExpr>(Args[0])) {
8595 S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(),
8596 diag::err_lvalue_reference_bind_to_initlist)
8597 << DestType.getNonReferenceType().isVolatileQualified()
8598 << DestType.getNonReferenceType()
8599 << Args[0]->getSourceRange();
8600 break;
8601 }
8602 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
8603
8604 case FK_NonConstLValueReferenceBindingToUnrelated:
8605 S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(),
8606 Failure == FK_NonConstLValueReferenceBindingToTemporary
8607 ? diag::err_lvalue_reference_bind_to_temporary
8608 : diag::err_lvalue_reference_bind_to_unrelated)
