8609 << DestType.getNonReferenceType().isVolatileQualified()
8610 << DestType.getNonReferenceType()
8611 << OnlyArg->getType()
8612 << Args[0]->getSourceRange();
8613 break;
8614
8615 case FK_NonConstLValueReferenceBindingToBitfield: {
8616 // We don't necessarily have an unambiguous source bit-field.
8617 FieldDecl *BitField = Args[0]->getSourceBitField();
8618 S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_reference_bind_to_bitfield)
8619 << DestType.isVolatileQualified()
8620 << (BitField ? BitField->getDeclName() : DeclarationName())
8621 << (BitField != nullptr)
8622 << Args[0]->getSourceRange();
8623 if (BitField)
8624 S.Diag(BitField->getLocation(), diag::note_bitfield_decl);
8625 break;
8626 }
8627
8628 case FK_NonConstLValueReferenceBindingToVectorElement:
8629 S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_reference_bind_to_vector_element)
8630 << DestType.isVolatileQualified()
8631 << Args[0]->getSourceRange();
8632 break;
8633
8634 case FK_RValueReferenceBindingToLValue:
8635 S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_lvalue_to_rvalue_ref)
8636 << DestType.getNonReferenceType() << OnlyArg->getType()
8637 << Args[0]->getSourceRange();
8638 break;
8639
8640 case FK_ReferenceAddrspaceMismatchTemporary:
8641 S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_reference_bind_temporary_addrspace)
8642 << DestType << Args[0]->getSourceRange();
8643 break;
8644
8645 case FK_ReferenceInitDropsQualifiers: {
8646 QualType SourceType = OnlyArg->getType();
8647 QualType NonRefType = DestType.getNonReferenceType();
8648 Qualifiers DroppedQualifiers =
8649 SourceType.getQualifiers() - NonRefType.getQualifiers();
8650
8651 S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_reference_bind_drops_quals)
8652 << SourceType
8653 << NonRefType
8654 << DroppedQualifiers.getCVRQualifiers()
8655 << Args[0]->getSourceRange();
8656 break;
8657 }
8658
8659 case FK_ReferenceInitFailed:
8660 S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_reference_bind_failed)
8661 << DestType.getNonReferenceType()
8662 << DestType.getNonReferenceType()->isIncompleteType()
8663 << OnlyArg->isLValue()
8664 << OnlyArg->getType()
8665 << Args[0]->getSourceRange();
8666 emitBadConversionNotes(S, Entity, Args[0]);
8667 break;
8668
8669 case FK_ReferenceInitChangesCapabilityQualifier:
8670 case FK_ConversionFromCapabilityFailed:
8671 case FK_ConversionToCapabilityFailed: {
8672 QualType FromType = Args[0]->getRealReferenceType(S.getASTContext());
8673 bool PrintRefInMessage = false;
8674 // Failure == FK_ConversionFromCapabilityFailed
8675 bool PtrToCap = DestType->isCHERICapabilityType(S.getASTContext());
8676 unsigned DiagID = PtrToCap ? diag::err_typecheck_convert_ptr_to_cap
8677 : diag::err_typecheck_convert_cap_to_ptr;
8678 if (Failure == FK_ReferenceInitChangesCapabilityQualifier) {
8679 PrintRefInMessage = !FromType->isReferenceType();
8680 }
8681
8682 S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), DiagID) << FromType << DestType << PrintRefInMessage
8683 << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(Kind.getLocation(), "(__cheri_" +
8684 std::string(PtrToCap ? "to" : "from") +
8685 "cap " + DestType.getAsString() + ")");
8686 break;
8687 }
8688 case FK_ConversionFailed: {
8689 QualType FromType = Args[0]->getType();
8690
8691 // CHERI: in the case of initializing a capability from a pointer,
8692 // output error message here if the types are not compatible, so that we
8693 // get the same error message for both C and C++.
8694 Expr *SrcExpr = Args[0];
8695 if (FromType->isPointerType()
8696 && !FromType->isCHERICapabilityType(S.Context, false)
8697 && DestType->isCHERICapabilityType(S.Context, false)) {
8698 S.Diag(SrcExpr->getExprLoc(), diag::err_typecheck_convert_ptr_to_cap_unrelated_type)
8699 << FromType << DestType << false;
8700 return true;
8701 } else {
8702 QualType FromType = OnlyArg->getType();
8703 PartialDiagnostic PDiag = S.PDiag(diag::err_init_conversion_failed)
8704 << (int)Entity.getKind()
8705 << DestType
8706 << OnlyArg->isLValue()
8707 << FromType
8708 << Args[0]->getSourceRange();
8709 S.HandleFunctionTypeMismatch(PDiag, FromType, DestType);
8710 S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), PDiag);
8711 }
8712 emitBadConversionNotes(S, Entity, Args[0]);
8713 break;
8714 }
8715
8716 case FK_ConversionFromPropertyFailed:
8717 // No-op. This error has already been reported.
8718 break;
8719
8720 case FK_TooManyInitsForScalar: {
8721 SourceRange R;
8722
8723 auto *InitList = dyn_cast<InitListExpr>(Args[0]);
8724 if (InitList && InitList->getNumInits() >= 1) {
8725 R = SourceRange(InitList->getInit(0)->getEndLoc(), InitList->getEndLoc());
8726 } else {
8727 assert(Args.size() > 1 && "Expected multiple initializers!");
8728 R = SourceRange(Args.front()->getEndLoc(), Args.back()->getEndLoc());
8729 }
8730
8731 R.setBegin(S.getLocForEndOfToken(R.getBegin()));
8732 if (Kind.isCStyleOrFunctionalCast())
8733 S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_builtin_func_cast_more_than_one_arg)
8734 << R;
8735 else
8736 S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_excess_initializers)
8737 << /*scalar=*/2 << R;
8738 break;
8739 }
8740
8741 case FK_ParenthesizedListInitForScalar:
8742 S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_list_init_in_parens)
8743 << 0 << Entity.getType() << Args[0]->getSourceRange();
8744 break;
8745
8746 case FK_ReferenceBindingToInitList:
8747 S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_reference_bind_init_list)
8748 << DestType.getNonReferenceType() << Args[0]->getSourceRange();
8749 break;
8750
8751 case FK_InitListBadDestinationType:
8752 S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_init_list_bad_dest_type)
8753 << (DestType->isRecordType()) << DestType << Args[0]->getSourceRange();
8754 break;
8755
8756 case FK_ListConstructorOverloadFailed:
8757 case FK_ConstructorOverloadFailed: {
8758 SourceRange ArgsRange;
8759 if (Args.size())
8760 ArgsRange =
8761 SourceRange(Args.front()->getBeginLoc(), Args.back()->getEndLoc());
8762
8763 if (Failure == FK_ListConstructorOverloadFailed) {
8764 assert(Args.size() == 1 &&
8765 "List construction from other than 1 argument.");
8766 InitListExpr *InitList = cast<InitListExpr>(Args[0]);
8767 Args = MultiExprArg(InitList->getInits(), InitList->getNumInits());
8768 }
8769
8770 // FIXME: Using "DestType" for the entity we're printing is probably
8771 // bad.
8772 switch (FailedOverloadResult) {
8773 case OR_Ambiguous:
8774 FailedCandidateSet.NoteCandidates(
8775 PartialDiagnosticAt(Kind.getLocation(),
8776 S.PDiag(diag::err_ovl_ambiguous_init)
8777 << DestType << ArgsRange),
8778 S, OCD_ViableCandidates, Args);
8779 break;
8780
8781 case OR_No_Viable_Function:
8782 if (Kind.getKind() == InitializationKind::IK_Default &&
8783 (Entity.getKind() == InitializedEntity::EK_Base ||
8784 Entity.getKind() == InitializedEntity::EK_Member) &&
8785 isa<CXXConstructorDecl>(S.CurContext)) {
8786 // This is implicit default initialization of a member or
8787 // base within a constructor. If no viable function was
8788 // found, notify the user that they need to explicitly
8789 // initialize this base/member.
8790 CXXConstructorDecl *Constructor
8791 = cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(S.CurContext);
8792 const CXXRecordDecl *InheritedFrom = nullptr;
8793 if (auto Inherited = Constructor->getInheritedConstructor())
8794 InheritedFrom = Inherited.getShadowDecl()->getNominatedBaseClass();
8795 if (Entity.getKind() == InitializedEntity::EK_Base) {
8796 S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_missing_default_ctor)
8797 << (InheritedFrom ? 2 : Constructor->isImplicit() ? 1 : 0)
8798 << S.Context.getTypeDeclType(Constructor->getParent())
8799 << /*base=*/0
8800 << Entity.getType()
8801 << InheritedFrom;
8802
8803 RecordDecl *BaseDecl
8804 = Entity.getBaseSpecifier()->getType()->getAs<RecordType>()
8805 ->getDecl();
8806 S.Diag(BaseDecl->getLocation(), diag::note_previous_decl)
8807 << S.Context.getTagDeclType(BaseDecl);
8808 } else {
8809 S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_missing_default_ctor)
8810 << (InheritedFrom ? 2 : Constructor->isImplicit() ? 1 : 0)
8811 << S.Context.getTypeDeclType(Constructor->getParent())
8812 << /*member=*/1
8813 << Entity.getName()
8814 << InheritedFrom;
8815 S.Diag(Entity.getDecl()->getLocation(),
8816 diag::note_member_declared_at);
8817
8818 if (const RecordType *Record
8819 = Entity.getType()->getAs<RecordType>())
8820 S.Diag(Record->getDecl()->getLocation(),
8821 diag::note_previous_decl)
8822 << S.Context.getTagDeclType(Record->getDecl());
8823 }
8824 break;
8825 }
8826
8827 FailedCandidateSet.NoteCandidates(
8828 PartialDiagnosticAt(
8829 Kind.getLocation(),
8830 S.PDiag(diag::err_ovl_no_viable_function_in_init)
8831 << DestType << ArgsRange),
8832 S, OCD_AllCandidates, Args);
8833 break;
8834
8835 case OR_Deleted: {
8836 OverloadCandidateSet::iterator Best;
8837 OverloadingResult Ovl
8838 = FailedCandidateSet.BestViableFunction(S, Kind.getLocation(), Best);
8839 if (Ovl != OR_Deleted) {
8840 S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_ovl_deleted_init)
8841 << DestType << ArgsRange;
8842 llvm_unreachable("Inconsistent overload resolution?");
8843 break;
8844 }
8845
8846 // If this is a defaulted or implicitly-declared function, then
8847 // it was implicitly deleted. Make it clear that the deletion was
8848 // implicit.
8849 if (S.isImplicitlyDeleted(Best->Function))
8850 S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_ovl_deleted_special_init)
8851 << S.getSpecialMember(cast<CXXMethodDecl>(Best->Function))
8852 << DestType << ArgsRange;
8853 else
8854 S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_ovl_deleted_init)
8855 << DestType << ArgsRange;
8856
8857 S.NoteDeletedFunction(Best->Function);
8858 break;
8859 }
8860
8861 case OR_Success:
8862 llvm_unreachable("Conversion did not fail!");
8863 }
8864 }
8865 break;
8866
8867 case FK_DefaultInitOfConst:
8868 if (Entity.getKind() == InitializedEntity::EK_Member &&
8869 isa<CXXConstructorDecl>(S.CurContext)) {
8870 // This is implicit default-initialization of a const member in
8871 // a constructor. Complain that it needs to be explicitly
8872 // initialized.
8873 CXXConstructorDecl *Constructor = cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(S.CurContext);
8874 S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_uninitialized_member_in_ctor)
8875 << (Constructor->getInheritedConstructor() ? 2 :
8876 Constructor->isImplicit() ? 1 : 0)
8877 << S.Context.getTypeDeclType(Constructor->getParent())
8878 << /*const=*/1
8879 << Entity.getName();
8880 S.Diag(Entity.getDecl()->getLocation(), diag::note_previous_decl)
8881 << Entity.getName();
8882 } else {
8883 S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_default_init_const)
8884 << DestType << (bool)DestType->getAs<RecordType>();
8885 }
8886 break;
8887
8888 case FK_Incomplete:
8889 S.RequireCompleteType(Kind.getLocation(), FailedIncompleteType,
8890 diag::err_init_incomplete_type);
8891 break;
8892
8893 case FK_ListInitializationFailed: {
8894 // Run the init list checker again to emit diagnostics.
8895 InitListExpr *InitList = cast<InitListExpr>(Args[0]);
8896 diagnoseListInit(S, Entity, InitList);
8897 break;
8898 }
8899
8900 case FK_PlaceholderType: {
8901 // FIXME: Already diagnosed!
8902 break;
8903 }
8904
8905 case FK_ExplicitConstructor: {
8906 S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_selected_explicit_constructor)
8907 << Args[0]->getSourceRange();
8908 OverloadCandidateSet::iterator Best;
8909 OverloadingResult Ovl
8910 = FailedCandidateSet.BestViableFunction(S, Kind.getLocation(), Best);
8911 (void)Ovl;
8912 assert(Ovl == OR_Success && "Inconsistent overload resolution");
8913 CXXConstructorDecl *CtorDecl = cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(Best->Function);
8914 S.Diag(CtorDecl->getLocation(),
8915 diag::note_explicit_ctor_deduction_guide_here) << false;
8916 break;
8917 }
8918 }
8919
8920 PrintInitLocationNote(S, Entity);
8921 return true;
8922}

9271void InitializationSequence::dump() const {

9274
9275static bool NarrowingErrs(const LangOptions &L) {
9276 return L.CPlusPlus11 &&
9277 (!L.MicrosoftExt || L.isCompatibleWithMSVC(LangOptions::MSVC2015));
9278}
9279
9280static void DiagnoseNarrowingInInitList(Sema &S,
9281 const ImplicitConversionSequence &ICS,
9282 QualType PreNarrowingType,
9283 QualType EntityType,
9284 const Expr *PostInit) {
9285 const StandardConversionSequence *SCS = nullptr;
9286 switch (ICS.getKind()) {
9287 case ImplicitConversionSequence::StandardConversion:
9288 SCS = &ICS.Standard;
9289 break;
9290 case ImplicitConversionSequence::UserDefinedConversion:
9291 SCS = &ICS.UserDefined.After;
9292 break;
9293 case ImplicitConversionSequence::AmbiguousConversion:
9294 case ImplicitConversionSequence::EllipsisConversion:
9295 case ImplicitConversionSequence::BadConversion:
9296 return;
9297 }
9298
9299 // C++11 [dcl.init.list]p7: Check whether this is a narrowing conversion.
9300 APValue ConstantValue;
9301 QualType ConstantType;
9302 switch (SCS->getNarrowingKind(S.Context, PostInit, ConstantValue,
9303 ConstantType)) {
9304 case NK_Not_Narrowing:
9305 case NK_Dependent_Narrowing:
9306 // No narrowing occurred.
9307 return;
9308
9309 case NK_Type_Narrowing:
9310 // This was a floating-to-integer conversion, which is always considered a
9311 // narrowing conversion even if the value is a constant and can be
9312 // represented exactly as an integer.
9313 S.Diag(PostInit->getBeginLoc(), NarrowingErrs(S.getLangOpts())
9314 ? diag::ext_init_list_type_narrowing
9315 : diag::warn_init_list_type_narrowing)
9316 << PostInit->getSourceRange()
9317 << PreNarrowingType.getLocalUnqualifiedType()
9318 << EntityType.getLocalUnqualifiedType();
9319 break;
9320
9321 case NK_Constant_Narrowing:
9322 // A constant value was narrowed.
9323 S.Diag(PostInit->getBeginLoc(),
9324 NarrowingErrs(S.getLangOpts())
9325 ? diag::ext_init_list_constant_narrowing
9326 : diag::warn_init_list_constant_narrowing)
9327 << PostInit->getSourceRange()
9328 << ConstantValue.getAsString(S.getASTContext(), ConstantType)
9329 << EntityType.getLocalUnqualifiedType();
9330 break;
9331
9332 case NK_Variable_Narrowing:
9333 // A variable's value may have been narrowed.
9334 S.Diag(PostInit->getBeginLoc(),
9335 NarrowingErrs(S.getLangOpts())
9336 ? diag::ext_init_list_variable_narrowing
9337 : diag::warn_init_list_variable_narrowing)
9338 << PostInit->getSourceRange()
9339 << PreNarrowingType.getLocalUnqualifiedType()
9340 << EntityType.getLocalUnqualifiedType();
9341 break;
9342 }
9343
9344 SmallString<128> StaticCast;
9345 llvm::raw_svector_ostream OS(StaticCast);
9346 OS << "static_cast<";
9347 if (const TypedefType *TT = EntityType->getAs<TypedefType>()) {
9348 // It's important to use the typedef's name if there is one so that the
9349 // fixit doesn't break code using types like int64_t.
9350 //
9351 // FIXME: This will break if the typedef requires qualification. But
9352 // getQualifiedNameAsString() includes non-machine-parsable components.
9353 OS << *TT->getDecl();
9354 } else if (const BuiltinType *BT = EntityType->getAs<BuiltinType>())
9355 OS << BT->getName(S.getLangOpts());
9356 else {
9357 // Oops, we didn't find the actual type of the variable. Don't emit a fixit
9358 // with a broken cast.
9359 return;
9360 }
9361 OS << ">(";
9362 S.Diag(PostInit->getBeginLoc(), diag::note_init_list_narrowing_silence)
9363 << PostInit->getSourceRange()
9364 << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(PostInit->getBeginLoc(), OS.str())
9365 << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(
9366 S.getLocForEndOfToken(PostInit->getEndLoc()), ")");
9367}
9368
9369//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
9370// Initialization helper functions
9371//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
9372bool
9373Sema::CanPerformCopyInitialization(const InitializedEntity &Entity,
9374 ExprResult Init) {
9375 if (Init.isInvalid())
9376 return false;
9377
9378 Expr *InitE = Init.get();
9379 assert(InitE && "No initialization expression");
9380
9381 InitializationKind Kind =
9382 InitializationKind::CreateCopy(InitE->getBeginLoc(), SourceLocation());
9383 InitializationSequence Seq(*this, Entity, Kind, InitE);
9384 return !Seq.Failed();
9385}
9386
9387ExprResult
9388Sema::PerformCopyInitialization(const InitializedEntity &Entity,
9389 SourceLocation EqualLoc,
9390 ExprResult Init,
9391 bool TopLevelOfInitList,
9392 bool AllowExplicit) {
9393 if (Init.isInvalid())
9394 return ExprError();
9395
9396 Expr *InitE = Init.get();
9397 assert(InitE && "No initialization expression?");
9398
9399 if (EqualLoc.isInvalid())
9400 EqualLoc = InitE->getBeginLoc();
9401
9402 InitializationKind Kind = InitializationKind::CreateCopy(
9403 InitE->getBeginLoc(), EqualLoc, AllowExplicit);
9404 InitializationSequence Seq(*this, Entity, Kind, InitE, TopLevelOfInitList);
9405
9406 // Prevent infinite recursion when performing parameter copy-initialization.
9407 const bool ShouldTrackCopy =
9408 Entity.isParameterKind() && Seq.isConstructorInitialization();
9409 if (ShouldTrackCopy) {
9410 if (llvm::find(CurrentParameterCopyTypes, Entity.getType()) !=
9411 CurrentParameterCopyTypes.end()) {
9412 Seq.SetOverloadFailure(
9413 InitializationSequence::FK_ConstructorOverloadFailed,
9414 OR_No_Viable_Function);
9415
9416 // Try to give a meaningful diagnostic note for the problematic
9417 // constructor.
9418 const auto LastStep = Seq.step_end() - 1;
9419 assert(LastStep->Kind ==
9420 InitializationSequence::SK_ConstructorInitialization);
9421 const FunctionDecl *Function = LastStep->Function.Function;
9422 auto Candidate =
9423 llvm::find_if(Seq.getFailedCandidateSet(),
9424 [Function](const OverloadCandidate &Candidate) -> bool {
9425 return Candidate.Viable &&
9426 Candidate.Function == Function &&
9427 Candidate.Conversions.size() > 0;
9428 });
9429 if (Candidate != Seq.getFailedCandidateSet().end() &&
9430 Function->getNumParams() > 0) {
9431 Candidate->Viable = false;
9432 Candidate->FailureKind = ovl_fail_bad_conversion;
9433 Candidate->Conversions[0].setBad(BadConversionSequence::no_conversion,
9434 InitE,
9435 Function->getParamDecl(0)->getType());
9436 }
9437 }
9438 CurrentParameterCopyTypes.push_back(Entity.getType());
9439 }
9440
9441 ExprResult Result = Seq.Perform(*this, Entity, Kind, InitE);
9442
9443 if (ShouldTrackCopy)
9444 CurrentParameterCopyTypes.pop_back();
9445
9446 return Result;
9447}
9448
9449/// Determine whether RD is, or is derived from, a specialization of CTD.
9450static bool isOrIsDerivedFromSpecializationOf(CXXRecordDecl *RD,
9451 ClassTemplateDecl *CTD) {
9452 auto NotSpecialization = [&] (const CXXRecordDecl *Candidate) {
9453 auto *CTSD = dyn_cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(Candidate);
9454 return !CTSD || !declaresSameEntity(CTSD->getSpecializedTemplate(), CTD);
9455 };
9456 return !(NotSpecialization(RD) && RD->forallBases(NotSpecialization));
9457}
9458
9459QualType Sema::DeduceTemplateSpecializationFromInitializer(
9460 TypeSourceInfo *TSInfo, const InitializedEntity &Entity,
9461 const InitializationKind &Kind, MultiExprArg Inits) {
9462 auto *DeducedTST = dyn_cast<DeducedTemplateSpecializationType>(
9463 TSInfo->getType()->getContainedDeducedType());
9464 assert(DeducedTST && "not a deduced template specialization type");
9465
9466 auto TemplateName = DeducedTST->getTemplateName();
9467 if (TemplateName.isDependent())
9468 return Context.DependentTy;
9469
9470 // We can only perform deduction for class templates.
9471 auto *Template =
9472 dyn_cast_or_null<ClassTemplateDecl>(TemplateName.getAsTemplateDecl());
9473 if (!Template) {
9474 Diag(Kind.getLocation(),
9475 diag::err_deduced_non_class_template_specialization_type)
9476 << (int)getTemplateNameKindForDiagnostics(TemplateName) << TemplateName;
9477 if (auto *TD = TemplateName.getAsTemplateDecl())
9478 Diag(TD->getLocation(), diag::note_template_decl_here);
9479 return QualType();
9480 }
9481
9482 // Can't deduce from dependent arguments.
9483 if (Expr::hasAnyTypeDependentArguments(Inits)) {
9484 Diag(TSInfo->getTypeLoc().getBeginLoc(),
9485 diag::warn_cxx14_compat_class_template_argument_deduction)
9486 << TSInfo->getTypeLoc().getSourceRange() << 0;
9487 return Context.DependentTy;
9488 }
9489
9490 // FIXME: Perform "exact type" matching first, per CWG discussion?
9491 // Or implement this via an implied 'T(T) -> T' deduction guide?
9492
9493 // FIXME: Do we need/want a std::initializer_list<T> special case?
9494
9495 // Look up deduction guides, including those synthesized from constructors.
9496 //
9497 // C++1z [over.match.class.deduct]p1:
9498 // A set of functions and function templates is formed comprising:
9499 // - For each constructor of the class template designated by the
9500 // template-name, a function template [...]
9501 // - For each deduction-guide, a function or function template [...]
9502 DeclarationNameInfo NameInfo(
9503 Context.DeclarationNames.getCXXDeductionGuideName(Template),
9504 TSInfo->getTypeLoc().getEndLoc());
9505 LookupResult Guides(*this, NameInfo, LookupOrdinaryName);
9506 LookupQualifiedName(Guides, Template->getDeclContext());
9507
9508 // FIXME: Do not diagnose inaccessible deduction guides. The standard isn't
9509 // clear on this, but they're not found by name so access does not apply.
9510 Guides.suppressDiagnostics();
9511
9512 // Figure out if this is list-initialization.
9513 InitListExpr *ListInit =
9514 (Inits.size() == 1 && Kind.getKind() != InitializationKind::IK_Direct)
9515 ? dyn_cast<InitListExpr>(Inits[0])
9516 : nullptr;
9517
9518 // C++1z [over.match.class.deduct]p1:
9519 // Initialization and overload resolution are performed as described in
9520 // [dcl.init] and [over.match.ctor], [over.match.copy], or [over.match.list]
9521 // (as appropriate for the type of initialization performed) for an object
9522 // of a hypothetical class type, where the selected functions and function
9523 // templates are considered to be the constructors of that class type
9524 //
9525 // Since we know we're initializing a class type of a type unrelated to that
9526 // of the initializer, this reduces to something fairly reasonable.
9527 OverloadCandidateSet Candidates(Kind.getLocation(),
9528 OverloadCandidateSet::CSK_Normal);
9529 OverloadCandidateSet::iterator Best;
9530
9531 bool HasAnyDeductionGuide = false;
9532 bool AllowExplicit = !Kind.isCopyInit() || ListInit;
9533
9534 auto tryToResolveOverload =
9535 [&](bool OnlyListConstructors) -> OverloadingResult {
9536 Candidates.clear(OverloadCandidateSet::CSK_Normal);
9537 HasAnyDeductionGuide = false;
9538
9539 for (auto I = Guides.begin(), E = Guides.end(); I != E; ++I) {
9540 NamedDecl *D = (*I)->getUnderlyingDecl();
9541 if (D->isInvalidDecl())
9542 continue;
9543
9544 auto *TD = dyn_cast<FunctionTemplateDecl>(D);
9545 auto *GD = dyn_cast_or_null<CXXDeductionGuideDecl>(
9546 TD ? TD->getTemplatedDecl() : dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D));
9547 if (!GD)
9548 continue;
9549
9550 if (!GD->isImplicit())
9551 HasAnyDeductionGuide = true;
9552
9553 // C++ [over.match.ctor]p1: (non-list copy-initialization from non-class)
9554 // For copy-initialization, the candidate functions are all the
9555 // converting constructors (12.3.1) of that class.
9556 // C++ [over.match.copy]p1: (non-list copy-initialization from class)
9557 // The converting constructors of T are candidate functions.
9558 if (!AllowExplicit) {
9559 // Only consider converting constructors.
9560 if (GD->isExplicit())
9561 continue;
9562
9563 // When looking for a converting constructor, deduction guides that
9564 // could never be called with one argument are not interesting to
9565 // check or note.
9566 if (GD->getMinRequiredArguments() > 1 ||
9567 (GD->getNumParams() == 0 && !GD->isVariadic()))
9568 continue;
9569 }
9570
9571 // C++ [over.match.list]p1.1: (first phase list initialization)
9572 // Initially, the candidate functions are the initializer-list
9573 // constructors of the class T
9574 if (OnlyListConstructors && !isInitListConstructor(GD))
9575 continue;
9576
9577 // C++ [over.match.list]p1.2: (second phase list initialization)
9578 // the candidate functions are all the constructors of the class T
9579 // C++ [over.match.ctor]p1: (all other cases)
9580 // the candidate functions are all the constructors of the class of
9581 // the object being initialized
9582
9583 // C++ [over.best.ics]p4:
9584 // When [...] the constructor [...] is a candidate by
9585 // - [over.match.copy] (in all cases)
9586 // FIXME: The "second phase of [over.match.list] case can also
9587 // theoretically happen here, but it's not clear whether we can
9588 // ever have a parameter of the right type.
9589 bool SuppressUserConversions = Kind.isCopyInit();
9590
9591 if (TD)
9592 AddTemplateOverloadCandidate(TD, I.getPair(), /*ExplicitArgs*/ nullptr,
9593 Inits, Candidates, SuppressUserConversions,
9594 /*PartialOverloading*/ false,
9595 AllowExplicit);
9596 else
9597 AddOverloadCandidate(GD, I.getPair(), Inits, Candidates,
9598 SuppressUserConversions,
9599 /*PartialOverloading*/ false, AllowExplicit);
9600 }
9601 return Candidates.BestViableFunction(*this, Kind.getLocation(), Best);
9602 };
9603
9604 OverloadingResult Result = OR_No_Viable_Function;
9605
9606 // C++11 [over.match.list]p1, per DR1467: for list-initialization, first
9607 // try initializer-list constructors.
9608 if (ListInit) {
9609 bool TryListConstructors = true;
9610
9611 // Try list constructors unless the list is empty and the class has one or
9612 // more default constructors, in which case those constructors win.
9613 if (!ListInit->getNumInits()) {
9614 for (NamedDecl *D : Guides) {
9615 auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D->getUnderlyingDecl());
9616 if (FD && FD->getMinRequiredArguments() == 0) {
9617 TryListConstructors = false;
9618 break;
9619 }
9620 }
9621 } else if (ListInit->getNumInits() == 1) {
9622 // C++ [over.match.class.deduct]:
9623 // As an exception, the first phase in [over.match.list] (considering
9624 // initializer-list constructors) is omitted if the initializer list
9625 // consists of a single expression of type cv U, where U is a
9626 // specialization of C or a class derived from a specialization of C.
9627 Expr *E = ListInit->getInit(0);
9628 auto *RD = E->getType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
9629 if (!isa<InitListExpr>(E) && RD &&
9630 isCompleteType(Kind.getLocation(), E->getType()) &&
9631 isOrIsDerivedFromSpecializationOf(RD, Template))
9632 TryListConstructors = false;
9633 }
9634
9635 if (TryListConstructors)
9636 Result = tryToResolveOverload(/*OnlyListConstructor*/true);
9637 // Then unwrap the initializer list and try again considering all
9638 // constructors.
9639 Inits = MultiExprArg(ListInit->getInits(), ListInit->getNumInits());
9640 }
9641
9642 // If list-initialization fails, or if we're doing any other kind of
9643 // initialization, we (eventually) consider constructors.
9644 if (Result == OR_No_Viable_Function)
9645 Result = tryToResolveOverload(/*OnlyListConstructor*/false);
9646
9647 switch (Result) {
9648 case OR_Ambiguous:
9649 // FIXME: For list-initialization candidates, it'd usually be better to
9650 // list why they were not viable when given the initializer list itself as
9651 // an argument.
9652 Candidates.NoteCandidates(
9653 PartialDiagnosticAt(
9654 Kind.getLocation(),
9655 PDiag(diag::err_deduced_class_template_ctor_ambiguous)
9656 << TemplateName),
9657 *this, OCD_ViableCandidates, Inits);
9658 return QualType();
9659
9660 case OR_No_Viable_Function: {
9661 CXXRecordDecl *Primary =
9662 cast<ClassTemplateDecl>(Template)->getTemplatedDecl();
9663 bool Complete =
9664 isCompleteType(Kind.getLocation(), Context.getTypeDeclType(Primary));
9665 Candidates.NoteCandidates(
9666 PartialDiagnosticAt(
9667 Kind.getLocation(),
9668 PDiag(Complete ? diag::err_deduced_class_template_ctor_no_viable
9669 : diag::err_deduced_class_template_incomplete)
9670 << TemplateName << !Guides.empty()),
9671 *this, OCD_AllCandidates, Inits);
9672 return QualType();
9673 }
9674
9675 case OR_Deleted: {
9676 Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_deduced_class_template_deleted)
9677 << TemplateName;
9678 NoteDeletedFunction(Best->Function);
9679 return QualType();
9680 }
9681
9682 case OR_Success:
9683 // C++ [over.match.list]p1:
9684 // In copy-list-initialization, if an explicit constructor is chosen, the
9685 // initialization is ill-formed.
9686 if (Kind.isCopyInit() && ListInit &&
9687 cast<CXXDeductionGuideDecl>(Best->Function)->isExplicit()) {
9688 bool IsDeductionGuide = !Best->Function->isImplicit();
9689 Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_deduced_class_template_explicit)
9690 << TemplateName << IsDeductionGuide;
9691 Diag(Best->Function->getLocation(),
9692 diag::note_explicit_ctor_deduction_guide_here)
9693 << IsDeductionGuide;
9694 return QualType();
9695 }
9696
9697 // Make sure we didn't select an unusable deduction guide, and mark it
9698 // as referenced.
9699 DiagnoseUseOfDecl(Best->Function, Kind.getLocation());
9700 MarkFunctionReferenced(Kind.getLocation(), Best->Function);
9701 break;
9702 }
9703
9704 // C++ [dcl.type.class.deduct]p1:
9705 // The placeholder is replaced by the return type of the function selected
9706 // by overload resolution for class template deduction.
9707 QualType DeducedType =
9708 SubstAutoType(TSInfo->getType(), Best->Function->getReturnType());
9709 Diag(TSInfo->getTypeLoc().getBeginLoc(),
9710 diag::warn_cxx14_compat_class_template_argument_deduction)
9711 << TSInfo->getTypeLoc().getSourceRange() << 1 << DeducedType;
9712
9713 // Warn if CTAD was used on a type that does not have any user-defined
9714 // deduction guides.
9715 if (!HasAnyDeductionGuide) {
9716 Diag(TSInfo->getTypeLoc().getBeginLoc(),
9717 diag::warn_ctad_maybe_unsupported)
9718 << TemplateName;
9719 Diag(Template->getLocation(), diag::note_suppress_ctad_maybe_unsupported);
9720 }
9721
9722 return DeducedType;
9723}
